72 /// CreateTempAlloca - This creates a alloca and inserts it into the entry
73 /// block.
74 RawAddress
75 CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(llvm::Type *Ty, CharUnits Align,
76  const Twine &Name,
77  llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
78  auto Alloca = CreateTempAlloca(Ty, Name, ArraySize);
79  Alloca->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
80  return RawAddress(Alloca, Ty, Align, KnownNonNull);
81 }
82 
83 /// CreateTempAlloca - This creates a alloca and inserts it into the entry
84 /// block. The alloca is casted to default address space if necessary.
85 RawAddress CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty, CharUnits Align,
86  const Twine &Name,
87  llvm::Value *ArraySize,
88  RawAddress *AllocaAddr) {
89  auto Alloca = CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(Ty, Align, Name, ArraySize);
90  if (AllocaAddr)
91  *AllocaAddr = Alloca;
92  llvm::Value *V = Alloca.getPointer();
93  // Alloca always returns a pointer in alloca address space, which may
94  // be different from the type defined by the language. For example,
95  // in C++ the auto variables are in the default address space. Therefore
96  // cast alloca to the default address space when necessary.
97  if (getASTAllocaAddressSpace() != LangAS::Default) {
98  auto DestAddrSpace = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default);
99  llvm::IRBuilderBase::InsertPointGuard IPG(Builder);
100  // When ArraySize is nullptr, alloca is inserted at AllocaInsertPt,
101  // otherwise alloca is inserted at the current insertion point of the
102  // builder.
103  if (!ArraySize)
104  Builder.SetInsertPoint(getPostAllocaInsertPoint());
105  V = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
106  *this, V, getASTAllocaAddressSpace(), LangAS::Default,
107  Ty->getPointerTo(DestAddrSpace), /*non-null*/ true);
108  }
109 
110  return RawAddress(V, Ty, Align, KnownNonNull);
111 }
112 
113 /// CreateTempAlloca - This creates an alloca and inserts it into the entry
114 /// block if \p ArraySize is nullptr, otherwise inserts it at the current
115 /// insertion point of the builder.
116 llvm::AllocaInst *CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty,
117  const Twine &Name,
118  llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
119  if (ArraySize)
120  return Builder.CreateAlloca(Ty, ArraySize, Name);
121  return new llvm::AllocaInst(Ty, CGM.getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace(),
122  ArraySize, Name, AllocaInsertPt);
123 }
124 
125 /// CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca - This creates an alloca with the
126 /// default alignment of the corresponding LLVM type, which is *not*
127 /// guaranteed to be related in any way to the expected alignment of
128 /// an AST type that might have been lowered to Ty.
129 RawAddress CodeGenFunction::CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty,
130  const Twine &Name) {
131  CharUnits Align =
132  CharUnits::fromQuantity(CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(Ty));
133  return CreateTempAlloca(Ty, Align, Name);
134 }

136 RawAddress CodeGenFunction::CreateIRTemp(QualType Ty, const Twine &Name) {
137  CharUnits Align = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
138  return CreateTempAlloca(ConvertType(Ty), Align, Name);
139 }

141 RawAddress CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTemp(QualType Ty, const Twine &Name,
142  RawAddress *Alloca) {
143  // FIXME: Should we prefer the preferred type alignment here?
144  return CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty), Name, Alloca);
145 }
146 
147 RawAddress CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTemp(QualType Ty, CharUnits Align,
148  const Twine &Name,
149  RawAddress *Alloca) {
150  RawAddress Result = CreateTempAlloca(ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), Align, Name,
151  /*ArraySize=*/nullptr, Alloca);
152 
153  if (Ty->isConstantMatrixType()) {
154  auto *ArrayTy = cast<llvm::ArrayType>(Result.getElementType());
155  auto *VectorTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(ArrayTy->getElementType(),
156  ArrayTy->getNumElements());
157 
158  Result = Address(Result.getPointer(), VectorTy, Result.getAlignment(),
159  KnownNonNull);
160  }
161  return Result;
162 }
163 
164 RawAddress CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTempWithoutCast(QualType Ty,
165  CharUnits Align,
166  const Twine &Name) {
167  return CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), Align, Name);
168 }

170 RawAddress CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTempWithoutCast(QualType Ty,
171  const Twine &Name) {
172  return CreateMemTempWithoutCast(Ty, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty),
173  Name);
174 }

176 /// EvaluateExprAsBool - Perform the usual unary conversions on the specified
177 /// expression and compare the result against zero, returning an Int1Ty value.
178 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EvaluateExprAsBool(const Expr *E) {
179  PGO.setCurrentStmt(E);
180  if (const MemberPointerType *MPT = E->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
181  llvm::Value *MemPtr = EmitScalarExpr(E);
182  return CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(*this, MemPtr, MPT);
183  }
184 
185  QualType BoolTy = getContext().BoolTy;
186  SourceLocation Loc = E->getExprLoc();
187  CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
188  if (!E->getType()->isAnyComplexType())
189  return EmitScalarConversion(EmitScalarExpr(E), E->getType(), BoolTy, Loc);
190 
191  return EmitComplexToScalarConversion(EmitComplexExpr(E), E->getType(), BoolTy,
192  Loc);
193 }
194 
195 /// EmitIgnoredExpr - Emit code to compute the specified expression,
196 /// ignoring the result.
197 void CodeGenFunction::EmitIgnoredExpr(const Expr *E) {
198  if (E->isPRValue())
199  return (void)EmitAnyExpr(E, AggValueSlot::ignored(), true);
200 
201  // if this is a bitfield-resulting conditional operator, we can special case
202  // emit this. The normal 'EmitLValue' version of this is particularly
203  // difficult to codegen for, since creating a single "LValue" for two
204  // different sized arguments here is not particularly doable.
205  if (const auto *CondOp = dyn_cast<AbstractConditionalOperator>(
206  E->IgnoreParenNoopCasts(getContext()))) {
207  if (CondOp->getObjectKind() == OK_BitField)
208  return EmitIgnoredConditionalOperator(CondOp);
209  }
210 
211  // Just emit it as an l-value and drop the result.
212  EmitLValue(E);
213 }
214 
215 /// EmitAnyExpr - Emit code to compute the specified expression which
216 /// can have any type. The result is returned as an RValue struct.
217 /// If this is an aggregate expression, AggSlot indicates where the
218 /// result should be returned.
219 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExpr(const Expr *E,
220  AggValueSlot aggSlot,
221  bool ignoreResult) {
222  switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
223  case TEK_Scalar:
224  return RValue::get(EmitScalarExpr(E, ignoreResult));
225  case TEK_Complex:
226  return RValue::getComplex(EmitComplexExpr(E, ignoreResult, ignoreResult));
227  case TEK_Aggregate:
228  if (!ignoreResult && aggSlot.isIgnored())
229  aggSlot = CreateAggTemp(E->getType(), "agg-temp");
230  EmitAggExpr(E, aggSlot);
231  return aggSlot.asRValue();
232  }
233  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
234 }
235 
236 /// EmitAnyExprToTemp - Similar to EmitAnyExpr(), however, the result will
237 /// always be accessible even if no aggregate location is provided.
238 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExprToTemp(const Expr *E) {
239  AggValueSlot AggSlot = AggValueSlot::ignored();
240 
241  if (hasAggregateEvaluationKind(E->getType()))
242  AggSlot = CreateAggTemp(E->getType(), "agg.tmp");
243  return EmitAnyExpr(E, AggSlot);
244 }
245 
246 /// EmitAnyExprToMem - Evaluate an expression into a given memory
247 /// location.
248 void CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExprToMem(const Expr *E,
249  Address Location,
250  Qualifiers Quals,
251  bool IsInit) {
252  // FIXME: This function should take an LValue as an argument.
253  switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
254  case TEK_Complex:
255  EmitComplexExprIntoLValue(E, MakeAddrLValue(Location, E->getType()),
256  /*isInit*/ false);
257  return;
258 
259  case TEK_Aggregate: {
260  EmitAggExpr(E, AggValueSlot::forAddr(Location, Quals,
261  AggValueSlot::IsDestructed_t(IsInit),
262  AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
263  AggValueSlot::IsAliased_t(!IsInit),
264  AggValueSlot::MayOverlap));
265  return;
266  }
267 
268  case TEK_Scalar: {
269  RValue RV = RValue::get(EmitScalarExpr(E, /*Ignore*/ false));
270  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Location, E->getType());
271  EmitStoreThroughLValue(RV, LV);
272  return;
273  }
274  }
275  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
276 }
277 
278 static void
279 pushTemporaryCleanup(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M,
280  const Expr *E, Address ReferenceTemporary) {
281  // Objective-C++ ARC:
282  // If we are binding a reference to a temporary that has ownership, we
283  // need to perform retain/release operations on the temporary.
284  //
285  // FIXME: This should be looking at E, not M.
286  if (auto Lifetime = M->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
287  switch (Lifetime) {
288  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
289  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
290  // Carry on to normal cleanup handling.
291  break;
292 
293  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
294  // Nothing to do; cleaned up by an autorelease pool.
295  return;
296 
297  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
298  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
299  switch (StorageDuration Duration = M->getStorageDuration()) {
300  case SD_Static:
301  // Note: we intentionally do not register a cleanup to release
302  // the object on program termination.
303  return;
304 
305  case SD_Thread:
306  // FIXME: We should probably register a cleanup in this case.
307  return;
308 
309  case SD_Automatic:
310  case SD_FullExpression:
311  CodeGenFunction::Destroyer *Destroy;
312  CleanupKind CleanupKind;
313  if (Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong) {
314  const ValueDecl *VD = M->getExtendingDecl();
315  bool Precise =
316  VD && isa<VarDecl>(VD) && VD->hasAttr<ObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr>();
317  CleanupKind = CGF.getARCCleanupKind();
318  Destroy = Precise ? &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCStrongPrecise
319  : &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCStrongImprecise;
320  } else {
321  // __weak objects always get EH cleanups; otherwise, exceptions
322  // could cause really nasty crashes instead of mere leaks.
323  CleanupKind = NormalAndEHCleanup;
324  Destroy = &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCWeak;
325  }
326  if (Duration == SD_FullExpression)
327  CGF.pushDestroy(CleanupKind, ReferenceTemporary,
328  M->getType(), *Destroy,
329  CleanupKind & EHCleanup);
330  else
331  CGF.pushLifetimeExtendedDestroy(CleanupKind, ReferenceTemporary,
332  M->getType(),
333  *Destroy, CleanupKind & EHCleanup);
334  return;
335 
336  case SD_Dynamic:
337  llvm_unreachable("temporary cannot have dynamic storage duration");
338  }
339  llvm_unreachable("unknown storage duration");
340  }
341  }
342 
343  CXXDestructorDecl *ReferenceTemporaryDtor = nullptr;
344  if (const RecordType *RT =
345  E->getType()->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
346  // Get the destructor for the reference temporary.
347  auto *ClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
348  if (!ClassDecl->hasTrivialDestructor())
349  ReferenceTemporaryDtor = ClassDecl->getDestructor();
350  }
351 
352  if (!ReferenceTemporaryDtor)
353  return;
354 
355  // Call the destructor for the temporary.
356  switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
357  case SD_Static:
358  case SD_Thread: {
359  llvm::FunctionCallee CleanupFn;
360  llvm::Constant *CleanupArg;
361  if (E->getType()->isArrayType()) {
362  CleanupFn = CodeGenFunction(CGF.CGM).generateDestroyHelper(
363  ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
364  CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject, CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions,
365  dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()));
366  CleanupArg = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.Int8PtrTy);
367  } else {
368  CleanupFn = CGF.CGM.getAddrAndTypeOfCXXStructor(
369  GlobalDecl(ReferenceTemporaryDtor, Dtor_Complete));
370  CleanupArg = cast<llvm::Constant>(ReferenceTemporary.emitRawPointer(CGF));
371  }
372  CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().registerGlobalDtor(
373  CGF, *cast<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()), CleanupFn, CleanupArg);
374  break;
375  }
376 
377  case SD_FullExpression:
378  CGF.pushDestroy(NormalAndEHCleanup, ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
379  CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject,
380  CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions);
381  break;
382 
383  case SD_Automatic:
384  CGF.pushLifetimeExtendedDestroy(NormalAndEHCleanup,
385  ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
386  CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject,
387  CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions);
388  break;
389 
390  case SD_Dynamic:
391  llvm_unreachable("temporary cannot have dynamic storage duration");
392  }
393 }
394 
395 static RawAddress createReferenceTemporary(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
396  const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M,
397  const Expr *Inner,
398  RawAddress *Alloca = nullptr) {
399  auto &TCG = CGF.getTargetHooks();
400  switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
401  case SD_FullExpression:
402  case SD_Automatic: {
403  // If we have a constant temporary array or record try to promote it into a
404  // constant global under the same rules a normal constant would've been
405  // promoted. This is easier on the optimizer and generally emits fewer
406  // instructions.
407  QualType Ty = Inner->getType();
408  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().MergeAllConstants &&
409  (Ty->isArrayType() || Ty->isRecordType()) &&
410  Ty.isConstantStorage(CGF.getContext(), true, false))
411  if (auto Init = ConstantEmitter(CGF).tryEmitAbstract(Inner, Ty)) {
412  auto AS = CGF.CGM.GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace();
413  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
414  CGF.CGM.getModule(), Init->getType(), /*isConstant=*/true,
415  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, Init, ".ref.tmp", nullptr,
416  llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal,
417  CGF.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(AS));
418  CharUnits alignment = CGF.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
419  GV->setAlignment(alignment.getAsAlign());
420  llvm::Constant *C = GV;
421  if (AS != LangAS::Default)
422  C = TCG.performAddrSpaceCast(
423  CGF.CGM, GV, AS, LangAS::Default,
424  GV->getValueType()->getPointerTo(
425  CGF.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default)));
426  // FIXME: Should we put the new global into a COMDAT?
427  return RawAddress(C, GV->getValueType(), alignment);
428  }
429  return CGF.CreateMemTemp(Ty, "ref.tmp", Alloca);
430  }
431  case SD_Thread:
432  case SD_Static:
433  return CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalTemporary(M, Inner);
434 
435  case SD_Dynamic:
436  llvm_unreachable("temporary can't have dynamic storage duration");
437  }
438  llvm_unreachable("unknown storage duration");
439 }

441 /// Helper method to check if the underlying ABI is AAPCS
442 static bool isAAPCS(const TargetInfo &TargetInfo) {
443  return TargetInfo.getABI().starts_with("aapcs");
444 }
445 
446 LValue CodeGenFunction::
447 EmitMaterializeTemporaryExpr(const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M) {
448  const Expr *E = M->getSubExpr();
449 
450  assert((!M->getExtendingDecl() || !isa<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()) ||
451  !cast<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl())->isARCPseudoStrong()) &&
452  "Reference should never be pseudo-strong!");
453 
454  // FIXME: ideally this would use EmitAnyExprToMem, however, we cannot do so
455  // as that will cause the lifetime adjustment to be lost for ARC
456  auto ownership = M->getType().getObjCLifetime();
457  if (ownership != Qualifiers::OCL_None &&
458  ownership != Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone) {
459  RawAddress Object = createReferenceTemporary(*this, M, E);
460  if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Object.getPointer())) {
461  llvm::Type *Ty = ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType());
462  Object = Object.withElementType(Ty);
463 
464  // createReferenceTemporary will promote the temporary to a global with a
465  // constant initializer if it can. It can only do this to a value of
466  // ARC-manageable type if the value is global and therefore "immune" to
467  // ref-counting operations. Therefore we have no need to emit either a
468  // dynamic initialization or a cleanup and we can just return the address
469  // of the temporary.
470  if (Var->hasInitializer())
471  return MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
472 
473  Var->setInitializer(CGM.EmitNullConstant(E->getType()));
474  }
475  LValue RefTempDst = MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(),
476  AlignmentSource::Decl);
477 
478  switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
479  default: llvm_unreachable("expected scalar or aggregate expression");
480  case TEK_Scalar:
481  EmitScalarInit(E, M->getExtendingDecl(), RefTempDst, false);
482  break;
483  case TEK_Aggregate: {
484  EmitAggExpr(E, AggValueSlot::forAddr(Object,
485  E->getType().getQualifiers(),
486  AggValueSlot::IsDestructed,
487  AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
488  AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
489  AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap));
490  break;
491  }
492  }
493 
494  pushTemporaryCleanup(*this, M, E, Object);
495  return RefTempDst;
496  }
497 
498  SmallVector<const Expr *, 2> CommaLHSs;
499  SmallVector<SubobjectAdjustment, 2> Adjustments;
500  E = E->skipRValueSubobjectAdjustments(CommaLHSs, Adjustments);
501 
502  for (const auto &Ignored : CommaLHSs)
503  EmitIgnoredExpr(Ignored);
504 
505  if (const auto *opaque = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(E)) {
506  if (opaque->getType()->isRecordType()) {
507  assert(Adjustments.empty());
508  return EmitOpaqueValueLValue(opaque);
509  }
510  }
511 
512  // Create and initialize the reference temporary.
513  RawAddress Alloca = Address::invalid();
514  RawAddress Object = createReferenceTemporary(*this, M, E, &Alloca);
515  if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
516  Object.getPointer()->stripPointerCasts())) {
517  llvm::Type *TemporaryType = ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType());
518  Object = Object.withElementType(TemporaryType);
519  // If the temporary is a global and has a constant initializer or is a
520  // constant temporary that we promoted to a global, we may have already
521  // initialized it.
522  if (!Var->hasInitializer()) {
523  Var->setInitializer(CGM.EmitNullConstant(E->getType()));
524  EmitAnyExprToMem(E, Object, Qualifiers(), /*IsInit*/true);
525  }
526  } else {
527  switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
528  case SD_Automatic:
529  if (auto *Size = EmitLifetimeStart(
530  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Alloca.getElementType()),
531  Alloca.getPointer())) {
532  pushCleanupAfterFullExpr<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker,
533  Alloca, Size);
534  }
535  break;
536 
537  case SD_FullExpression: {
538  if (!ShouldEmitLifetimeMarkers)
539  break;
540 
541  // Avoid creating a conditional cleanup just to hold an llvm.lifetime.end
542  // marker. Instead, start the lifetime of a conditional temporary earlier
543  // so that it's unconditional. Don't do this with sanitizers which need
544  // more precise lifetime marks. However when inside an "await.suspend"
545  // block, we should always avoid conditional cleanup because it creates
546  // boolean marker that lives across await_suspend, which can destroy coro
547  // frame.
548  ConditionalEvaluation *OldConditional = nullptr;
549  CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint OldIP;
550  if (isInConditionalBranch() && !E->getType().isDestructedType() &&
551  ((!SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::HWAddress) &&
552  !SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Memory) &&
553  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeAddressUseAfterScope) ||
554  inSuspendBlock())) {
555  OldConditional = OutermostConditional;
556  OutermostConditional = nullptr;
557 
558  OldIP = Builder.saveIP();
559  llvm::BasicBlock *Block = OldConditional->getStartingBlock();
560  Builder.restoreIP(CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint(
561  Block, llvm::BasicBlock::iterator(Block->back())));
562  }
563 
564  if (auto *Size = EmitLifetimeStart(
565  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Alloca.getElementType()),
566  Alloca.getPointer())) {
567  pushFullExprCleanup<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker, Alloca,
568  Size);
569  }
570 
571  if (OldConditional) {
572  OutermostConditional = OldConditional;
573  Builder.restoreIP(OldIP);
574  }
575  break;
576  }
577 
578  default:
579  break;
580  }
581  EmitAnyExprToMem(E, Object, Qualifiers(), /*IsInit*/true);
582  }
583  pushTemporaryCleanup(*this, M, E, Object);
584 
585  // Perform derived-to-base casts and/or field accesses, to get from the
586  // temporary object we created (and, potentially, for which we extended
587  // the lifetime) to the subobject we're binding the reference to.
588  for (SubobjectAdjustment &Adjustment : llvm::reverse(Adjustments)) {
589  switch (Adjustment.Kind) {
590  case SubobjectAdjustment::DerivedToBaseAdjustment:
591  Object =
592  GetAddressOfBaseClass(Object, Adjustment.DerivedToBase.DerivedClass,
593  Adjustment.DerivedToBase.BasePath->path_begin(),
594  Adjustment.DerivedToBase.BasePath->path_end(),
595  /*NullCheckValue=*/ false, E->getExprLoc());
596  break;
597 
598  case SubobjectAdjustment::FieldAdjustment: {
599  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Object, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
600  LV = EmitLValueForField(LV, Adjustment.Field);
601  assert(LV.isSimple() &&
602  "materialized temporary field is not a simple lvalue");
603  Object = LV.getAddress(*this);
604  break;
605  }
606 
607  case SubobjectAdjustment::MemberPointerAdjustment: {
608  llvm::Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(Adjustment.Ptr.RHS);
609  Object = EmitCXXMemberDataPointerAddress(E, Object, Ptr,
610  Adjustment.Ptr.MPT);
611  break;
612  }
613  }
614  }
615 
616  return MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
617 }
618 
619 RValue
620 CodeGenFunction::EmitReferenceBindingToExpr(const Expr *E) {
621  // Emit the expression as an lvalue.
622  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E);
623  assert(LV.isSimple());
624  llvm::Value *Value = LV.getPointer(*this);
625 
626  if (sanitizePerformTypeCheck() && !E->getType()->isFunctionType()) {
627  // C++11 [dcl.ref]p5 (as amended by core issue 453):
628  // If a glvalue to which a reference is directly bound designates neither
629  // an existing object or function of an appropriate type nor a region of
630  // storage of suitable size and alignment to contain an object of the
631  // reference's type, the behavior is undefined.
632  QualType Ty = E->getType();
633  EmitTypeCheck(TCK_ReferenceBinding, E->getExprLoc(), Value, Ty);
634  }
635 
636  return RValue::get(Value);
637 }
638 
639 
640 /// getAccessedFieldNo - Given an encoded value and a result number, return the
641 /// input field number being accessed.
642 unsigned CodeGenFunction::getAccessedFieldNo(unsigned Idx,
643  const llvm::Constant *Elts) {
644  return cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Elts->getAggregateElement(Idx))
645  ->getZExtValue();
646 }
647 
648 /// Emit the hash_16_bytes function from include/llvm/ADT/Hashing.h.
649 static llvm::Value *emitHash16Bytes(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Value *Low,
650  llvm::Value *High) {
651  llvm::Value *KMul = Builder.getInt64(0x9ddfea08eb382d69ULL);
652  llvm::Value *K47 = Builder.getInt64(47);
653  llvm::Value *A0 = Builder.CreateMul(Builder.CreateXor(Low, High), KMul);
654  llvm::Value *A1 = Builder.CreateXor(Builder.CreateLShr(A0, K47), A0);
655  llvm::Value *B0 = Builder.CreateMul(Builder.CreateXor(High, A1), KMul);
656  llvm::Value *B1 = Builder.CreateXor(Builder.CreateLShr(B0, K47), B0);
657  return Builder.CreateMul(B1, KMul);
658 }
659 
660 bool CodeGenFunction::isNullPointerAllowed(TypeCheckKind TCK) {
661  return TCK == TCK_DowncastPointer || TCK == TCK_Upcast ||
662  TCK == TCK_UpcastToVirtualBase || TCK == TCK_DynamicOperation;
663 }
664 
665 bool CodeGenFunction::isVptrCheckRequired(TypeCheckKind TCK, QualType Ty) {
666  CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
667  return (RD && RD->hasDefinition() && RD->isDynamicClass()) &&
668  (TCK == TCK_MemberAccess || TCK == TCK_MemberCall ||
669  TCK == TCK_DowncastPointer || TCK == TCK_DowncastReference ||
670  TCK == TCK_UpcastToVirtualBase || TCK == TCK_DynamicOperation);
671 }
672 
673 bool CodeGenFunction::sanitizePerformTypeCheck() const {
674  return SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Null) ||
675  SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment) ||
676  SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) ||
677  SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr);
678 }
679 
680 void CodeGenFunction::EmitTypeCheck(TypeCheckKind TCK, SourceLocation Loc,
681  llvm::Value *Ptr, QualType Ty,
682  CharUnits Alignment,
683  SanitizerSet SkippedChecks,
684  llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
685  if (!sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
686  return;
687 
688  // Don't check pointers outside the default address space. The null check
689  // isn't correct, the object-size check isn't supported by LLVM, and we can't
690  // communicate the addresses to the runtime handler for the vptr check.
691  if (Ptr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())
692  return;
693 
694  // Don't check pointers to volatile data. The behavior here is implementation-
695  // defined.
696  if (Ty.isVolatileQualified())
697  return;
698 
699  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
700 
701  SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 3> Checks;
702  llvm::BasicBlock *Done = nullptr;
703 
704  // Quickly determine whether we have a pointer to an alloca. It's possible
705  // to skip null checks, and some alignment checks, for these pointers. This
706  // can reduce compile-time significantly.
707  auto PtrToAlloca = dyn_cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(Ptr->stripPointerCasts());
708 
709  llvm::Value *True = llvm::ConstantInt::getTrue(getLLVMContext());
710  llvm::Value *IsNonNull = nullptr;
711  bool IsGuaranteedNonNull =
712  SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Null) || PtrToAlloca;
713  bool AllowNullPointers = isNullPointerAllowed(TCK);
714  if ((SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Null) || AllowNullPointers) &&
715  !IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
716  // The glvalue must not be an empty glvalue.
717  IsNonNull = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr);
718 
719  // The IR builder can constant-fold the null check if the pointer points to
720  // a constant.
721  IsGuaranteedNonNull = IsNonNull == True;
722 
723  // Skip the null check if the pointer is known to be non-null.
724  if (!IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
725  if (AllowNullPointers) {
726  // When performing pointer casts, it's OK if the value is null.
727  // Skip the remaining checks in that case.
728  Done = createBasicBlock("null");
729  llvm::BasicBlock *Rest = createBasicBlock("not.null");
730  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNonNull, Rest, Done);
731  EmitBlock(Rest);
732  } else {
733  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(IsNonNull, SanitizerKind::Null));
734  }
735  }
736  }
737 
738  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) &&
739  !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) &&
740  !Ty->isIncompleteType()) {
741  uint64_t TySize = CGM.getMinimumObjectSize(Ty).getQuantity();
742  llvm::Value *Size = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, TySize);
743  if (ArraySize)
744  Size = Builder.CreateMul(Size, ArraySize);
745 
746  // Degenerate case: new X[0] does not need an objectsize check.
747  llvm::Constant *ConstantSize = dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(Size);
748  if (!ConstantSize || !ConstantSize->isNullValue()) {
749  // The glvalue must refer to a large enough storage region.
750  // FIXME: If Address Sanitizer is enabled, insert dynamic instrumentation
751  // to check this.
752  // FIXME: Get object address space
753  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { IntPtrTy, Int8PtrTy };
754  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::objectsize, Tys);
755  llvm::Value *Min = Builder.getFalse();
756  llvm::Value *NullIsUnknown = Builder.getFalse();
757  llvm::Value *Dynamic = Builder.getFalse();
758  llvm::Value *LargeEnough = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(
759  Builder.CreateCall(F, {Ptr, Min, NullIsUnknown, Dynamic}), Size);
760  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(LargeEnough, SanitizerKind::ObjectSize));
761  }
762  }
763 
764  llvm::MaybeAlign AlignVal;
765  llvm::Value *PtrAsInt = nullptr;
766 
767  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment) &&
768  !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment)) {
769  AlignVal = Alignment.getAsMaybeAlign();
770  if (!Ty->isIncompleteType() && !AlignVal)
771  AlignVal = CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(Ty, nullptr, nullptr,
772  /*ForPointeeType=*/true)
773  .getAsMaybeAlign();
774 
775  // The glvalue must be suitably aligned.
776  if (AlignVal && *AlignVal > llvm::Align(1) &&
777  (!PtrToAlloca || PtrToAlloca->getAlign() < *AlignVal)) {
778  PtrAsInt = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Ptr, IntPtrTy);
779  llvm::Value *Align = Builder.CreateAnd(
780  PtrAsInt, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, AlignVal->value() - 1));
781  llvm::Value *Aligned =
782  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Align, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, 0));
783  if (Aligned != True)
784  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(Aligned, SanitizerKind::Alignment));
785  }
786  }
787 
788  if (Checks.size() > 0) {
789  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
790  EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc), EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty),
791  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, AlignVal ? llvm::Log2(*AlignVal) : 1),
792  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, TCK)};
793  EmitCheck(Checks, SanitizerHandler::TypeMismatch, StaticData,
794  PtrAsInt ? PtrAsInt : Ptr);
795  }
796 
797  // If possible, check that the vptr indicates that there is a subobject of
798  // type Ty at offset zero within this object.
799  //
800  // C++11 [basic.life]p5,6:
801  // [For storage which does not refer to an object within its lifetime]
802  // The program has undefined behavior if:
803  // -- the [pointer or glvalue] is used to access a non-static data member
804  // or call a non-static member function
805  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr) &&
806  !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr) && isVptrCheckRequired(TCK, Ty)) {
807  // Ensure that the pointer is non-null before loading it. If there is no
808  // compile-time guarantee, reuse the run-time null check or emit a new one.
809  if (!IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
810  if (!IsNonNull)
811  IsNonNull = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr);
812  if (!Done)
813  Done = createBasicBlock("vptr.null");
814  llvm::BasicBlock *VptrNotNull = createBasicBlock("vptr.not.null");
815  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNonNull, VptrNotNull, Done);
816  EmitBlock(VptrNotNull);
817  }
818 
819  // Compute a hash of the mangled name of the type.
820  //
821  // FIXME: This is not guaranteed to be deterministic! Move to a
822  // fingerprinting mechanism once LLVM provides one. For the time
823  // being the implementation happens to be deterministic.
824  SmallString<64> MangledName;
825  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledName);
826  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty.getUnqualifiedType(),
827  Out);
828 
829  // Contained in NoSanitizeList based on the mangled type.
830  if (!CGM.getContext().getNoSanitizeList().containsType(SanitizerKind::Vptr,
831  Out.str())) {
832  llvm::hash_code TypeHash = hash_value(Out.str());
833 
834  // Load the vptr, and compute hash_16_bytes(TypeHash, vptr).
835  llvm::Value *Low = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, TypeHash);
836  Address VPtrAddr(Ptr, IntPtrTy, getPointerAlign());
837  llvm::Value *VPtrVal = Builder.CreateLoad(VPtrAddr);
838  llvm::Value *High = Builder.CreateZExt(VPtrVal, Int64Ty);
839 
840  llvm::Value *Hash = emitHash16Bytes(Builder, Low, High);
841  Hash = Builder.CreateTrunc(Hash, IntPtrTy);
842 
843  // Look the hash up in our cache.
844  const int CacheSize = 128;
845  llvm::Type *HashTable = llvm::ArrayType::get(IntPtrTy, CacheSize);
846  llvm::Value *Cache = CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(HashTable,
847  "__ubsan_vptr_type_cache");
848  llvm::Value *Slot = Builder.CreateAnd(Hash,
849  llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy,
850  CacheSize-1));
851  llvm::Value *Indices[] = { Builder.getInt32(0), Slot };
852  llvm::Value *CacheVal = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
853  IntPtrTy, Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(HashTable, Cache, Indices),
854  getPointerAlign());
855 
856  // If the hash isn't in the cache, call a runtime handler to perform the
857  // hard work of checking whether the vptr is for an object of the right
858  // type. This will either fill in the cache and return, or produce a
859  // diagnostic.
860  llvm::Value *EqualHash = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CacheVal, Hash);
861  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
862  EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc),
863  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty),
864  CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(Ty.getUnqualifiedType()),
865  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, TCK)
866  };
867  llvm::Value *DynamicData[] = { Ptr, Hash };
868  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(EqualHash, SanitizerKind::Vptr),
869  SanitizerHandler::DynamicTypeCacheMiss, StaticData,
870  DynamicData);
871  }
872  }
873 
874  if (Done) {
875  Builder.CreateBr(Done);
876  EmitBlock(Done);
877  }
878 }
879 
880 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::LoadPassedObjectSize(const Expr *E,
881  QualType EltTy) {
882  ASTContext &C = getContext();
883  uint64_t EltSize = C.getTypeSizeInChars(EltTy).getQuantity();
884  if (!EltSize)
885  return nullptr;
886 
887  auto *ArrayDeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
888  if (!ArrayDeclRef)
889  return nullptr;
890 
891  auto *ParamDecl = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(ArrayDeclRef->getDecl());
892  if (!ParamDecl)
893  return nullptr;
894 
895  auto *POSAttr = ParamDecl->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>();
896  if (!POSAttr)
897  return nullptr;
898 
899  // Don't load the size if it's a lower bound.
900  int POSType = POSAttr->getType();
901  if (POSType != 0 && POSType != 1)
902  return nullptr;
903 
904  // Find the implicit size parameter.
905  auto PassedSizeIt = SizeArguments.find(ParamDecl);
906  if (PassedSizeIt == SizeArguments.end())
907  return nullptr;
908 
909  const ImplicitParamDecl *PassedSizeDecl = PassedSizeIt->second;
910  assert(LocalDeclMap.count(PassedSizeDecl) && "Passed size not loadable");
911  Address AddrOfSize = LocalDeclMap.find(PassedSizeDecl)->second;
912  llvm::Value *SizeInBytes = EmitLoadOfScalar(AddrOfSize, /*Volatile=*/false,
913  C.getSizeType(), E->getExprLoc());
914  llvm::Value *SizeOfElement =
915  llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeInBytes->getType(), EltSize);
916  return Builder.CreateUDiv(SizeInBytes, SizeOfElement);
917 }
918 
919 /// If Base is known to point to the start of an array, return the length of
920 /// that array. Return 0 if the length cannot be determined.
921 static llvm::Value *getArrayIndexingBound(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
922  const Expr *Base,
923  QualType &IndexedType,
924  LangOptions::StrictFlexArraysLevelKind
925  StrictFlexArraysLevel) {
926  // For the vector indexing extension, the bound is the number of elements.
927  if (const VectorType *VT = Base->getType()->getAs<VectorType>()) {
928  IndexedType = Base->getType();
929  return CGF.Builder.getInt32(VT->getNumElements());
930  }
931 
932  Base = Base->IgnoreParens();
933 
934  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Base)) {
935  if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_ArrayToPointerDecay &&
936  !CE->getSubExpr()->isFlexibleArrayMemberLike(CGF.getContext(),
937  StrictFlexArraysLevel)) {
938  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
939 
940  IndexedType = CE->getSubExpr()->getType();
941  const ArrayType *AT = IndexedType->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe();
942  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
943  return CGF.Builder.getInt(CAT->getSize());
944 
945  if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(AT))
946  return CGF.getVLASize(VAT).NumElts;
947  // Ignore pass_object_size here. It's not applicable on decayed pointers.
948  }
949  }
950 
951  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
952 
953  QualType EltTy{Base->getType()->getPointeeOrArrayElementType(), 0};
954  if (llvm::Value *POS = CGF.LoadPassedObjectSize(Base, EltTy)) {
955  IndexedType = Base->getType();
956  return POS;
957  }
958 
959  return nullptr;
960 }
