962 namespace {
963 
964 /// \p StructAccessBase returns the base \p Expr of a field access. It returns
965 /// either a \p DeclRefExpr, representing the base pointer to the struct, i.e.:
966 ///
967 /// p in p-> a.b.c
968 ///
969 /// or a \p MemberExpr, if the \p MemberExpr has the \p RecordDecl we're
970 /// looking for:
971 ///
972 /// struct s {
973 /// struct s *ptr;
974 /// int count;
975 /// char array[] __attribute__((counted_by(count)));
976 /// };
977 ///
978 /// If we have an expression like \p p->ptr->array[index], we want the
979 /// \p MemberExpr for \p p->ptr instead of \p p.
980 class StructAccessBase
981  : public ConstStmtVisitor<StructAccessBase, const Expr *> {
982  const RecordDecl *ExpectedRD;
983 
984  bool IsExpectedRecordDecl(const Expr *E) const {
985  QualType Ty = E->getType();
986  if (Ty->isPointerType())
987  Ty = Ty->getPointeeType();
988  return ExpectedRD == Ty->getAsRecordDecl();
989  }
990 
991 public:
992  StructAccessBase(const RecordDecl *ExpectedRD) : ExpectedRD(ExpectedRD) {}
993 
994  //===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//
995  // Visitor Methods
996  //===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//
997 
998  // NOTE: If we build C++ support for counted_by, then we'll have to handle
999  // horrors like this:
1000  //
1001  // struct S {
1002  // int x, y;
1003  // int blah[] __attribute__((counted_by(x)));
1004  // } s;
1005  //
1006  // int foo(int index, int val) {
1007  // int (S::*IHatePMDs)[] = &S::blah;
1008  // (s.*IHatePMDs)[index] = val;
1009  // }
1010 
1011  const Expr *Visit(const Expr *E) {
1012  return ConstStmtVisitor<StructAccessBase, const Expr *>::Visit(E);
1013  }
1014 
1015  const Expr *VisitStmt(const Stmt *S) { return nullptr; }
1016 
1017  // These are the types we expect to return (in order of most to least
1018  // likely):
1019  //
1020  // 1. DeclRefExpr - This is the expression for the base of the structure.
1021  // It's exactly what we want to build an access to the \p counted_by
1022  // field.
1023  // 2. MemberExpr - This is the expression that has the same \p RecordDecl
1024  // as the flexble array member's lexical enclosing \p RecordDecl. This
1025  // allows us to catch things like: "p->p->array"
1026  // 3. CompoundLiteralExpr - This is for people who create something
1027  // heretical like (struct foo has a flexible array member):
1028  //
1029  // (struct foo){ 1, 2 }.blah[idx];
1030  const Expr *VisitDeclRefExpr(const DeclRefExpr *E) {
1031  return IsExpectedRecordDecl(E) ? E : nullptr;
1032  }
1033  const Expr *VisitMemberExpr(const MemberExpr *E) {
1034  if (IsExpectedRecordDecl(E) && E->isArrow())
1035  return E;
1036  const Expr *Res = Visit(E->getBase());
1037  return !Res && IsExpectedRecordDecl(E) ? E : Res;
1038  }
1039  const Expr *VisitCompoundLiteralExpr(const CompoundLiteralExpr *E) {
1040  return IsExpectedRecordDecl(E) ? E : nullptr;
1041  }
1042  const Expr *VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
1043  return IsExpectedRecordDecl(E) ? E : nullptr;
1044  }
1045 
1046  const Expr *VisitArraySubscriptExpr(const ArraySubscriptExpr *E) {
1047  if (IsExpectedRecordDecl(E))
1048  return E;
1049  return Visit(E->getBase());
1050  }
1051  const Expr *VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
1052  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
1053  }
1054  const Expr *VisitParenExpr(const ParenExpr *E) {
1055  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
1056  }
1057  const Expr *VisitUnaryAddrOf(const UnaryOperator *E) {
1058  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
1059  }
1060  const Expr *VisitUnaryDeref(const UnaryOperator *E) {
1061  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
1062  }
1063 };
1064 
1065 } // end anonymous namespace
1066 
1067 using RecIndicesTy =
1068  SmallVector<std::pair<const RecordDecl *, llvm::Value *>, 8>;
1069 
1070 static bool getGEPIndicesToField(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const RecordDecl *RD,
1071  const FieldDecl *FD, RecIndicesTy &Indices) {
1072  const CGRecordLayout &Layout = CGF.CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(RD);
1073  int64_t FieldNo = -1;
1074  for (const Decl *D : RD->decls()) {
1075  if (const auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D)) {
1076  FieldNo = Layout.getLLVMFieldNo(Field);
1077  if (FD == Field) {
1078  Indices.emplace_back(std::make_pair(RD, CGF.Builder.getInt32(FieldNo)));
1079  return true;
1080  }
1081  }
1082 
1083  if (const auto *Record = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(D)) {
1084  ++FieldNo;
1085  if (getGEPIndicesToField(CGF, Record, FD, Indices)) {
1086  if (RD->isUnion())
1087  FieldNo = 0;
1088  Indices.emplace_back(std::make_pair(RD, CGF.Builder.getInt32(FieldNo)));
1089  return true;
1090  }
1091  }
1092  }
1093 
1094  return false;
1095 }
1096 
1097 /// This method is typically called in contexts where we can't generate
1098 /// side-effects, like in __builtin_dynamic_object_size. When finding
1099 /// expressions, only choose those that have either already been emitted or can
1100 /// be loaded without side-effects.
1101 ///
1102 /// - \p FAMDecl: the \p Decl for the flexible array member. It may not be
1103 /// within the top-level struct.
1104 /// - \p CountDecl: must be within the same non-anonymous struct as \p FAMDecl.
1105 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCountedByFieldExpr(
1106  const Expr *Base, const FieldDecl *FAMDecl, const FieldDecl *CountDecl) {
1107  const RecordDecl *RD = CountDecl->getParent()->getOuterLexicalRecordContext();
1108 
1109  // Find the base struct expr (i.e. p in p->a.b.c.d).
1110  const Expr *StructBase = StructAccessBase(RD).Visit(Base);
1111  if (!StructBase || StructBase->HasSideEffects(getContext()))
1112  return nullptr;
1113 
1114  llvm::Value *Res = nullptr;
1115  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(StructBase)) {
1116  Res = EmitDeclRefLValue(DRE).getPointer(*this);
1117  Res = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ConvertType(DRE->getType()), Res,
1118  getPointerAlign(), "dre.load");
1119  } else if (const MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(StructBase)) {
1120  LValue LV = EmitMemberExpr(ME);
1121  Address Addr = LV.getAddress(*this);
1122  Res = Addr.emitRawPointer(*this);
1123  } else if (StructBase->getType()->isPointerType()) {
1124  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
1125  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
1126  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(StructBase, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
1127  Res = Addr.emitRawPointer(*this);
1128  } else {
1129  return nullptr;
1130  }
1131 
1132  llvm::Value *Zero = Builder.getInt32(0);
1133  RecIndicesTy Indices;
1134 
1135  getGEPIndicesToField(*this, RD, CountDecl, Indices);
1136 
1137  for (auto I = Indices.rbegin(), E = Indices.rend(); I != E; ++I)
1138  Res = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(
1139  ConvertType(QualType(I->first->getTypeForDecl(), 0)), Res,
1140  {Zero, I->second}, "..counted_by.gep");
1141 
1142  return Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ConvertType(CountDecl->getType()), Res,
1143  getIntAlign(), "..counted_by.load");
1144 }
1145 
1146 const FieldDecl *CodeGenFunction::FindCountedByField(const FieldDecl *FD) {
1147  if (!FD)
1148  return nullptr;
1149 
1150  const auto *CAT = FD->getType()->getAs<CountAttributedType>();
1151  if (!CAT)
1152  return nullptr;
1153 
1154  const auto *CountDRE = cast<DeclRefExpr>(CAT->getCountExpr());
1155  const auto *CountDecl = CountDRE->getDecl();
1156  if (const auto *IFD = dyn_cast<IndirectFieldDecl>(CountDecl))
1157  CountDecl = IFD->getAnonField();
1158 
1159  return dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(CountDecl);
1160 }
1161 
1162 void CodeGenFunction::EmitBoundsCheck(const Expr *E, const Expr *Base,
1163  llvm::Value *Index, QualType IndexType,
1164  bool Accessed) {
1165  assert(SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds) &&
1166  "should not be called unless adding bounds checks");
1167  const LangOptions::StrictFlexArraysLevelKind StrictFlexArraysLevel =
1168  getLangOpts().getStrictFlexArraysLevel();
1169  QualType IndexedType;
1170  llvm::Value *Bound =
1171  getArrayIndexingBound(*this, Base, IndexedType, StrictFlexArraysLevel);
1172 
1173  EmitBoundsCheckImpl(E, Bound, Index, IndexType, IndexedType, Accessed);
1174 }
1175 
1176 void CodeGenFunction::EmitBoundsCheckImpl(const Expr *E, llvm::Value *Bound,
1177  llvm::Value *Index,
1178  QualType IndexType,
1179  QualType IndexedType, bool Accessed) {
1180  if (!Bound)
1181  return;
1182 
1183  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
1184 
1185  bool IndexSigned = IndexType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1186  llvm::Value *IndexVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(Index, SizeTy, IndexSigned);
1187  llvm::Value *BoundVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(Bound, SizeTy, false);
1188 
1189  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
1190  EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getExprLoc()),
1191  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(IndexedType),
1192  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(IndexType)
1193  };
1194  llvm::Value *Check = Accessed ? Builder.CreateICmpULT(IndexVal, BoundVal)
1195  : Builder.CreateICmpULE(IndexVal, BoundVal);
1196  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Check, SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds),
1197  SanitizerHandler::OutOfBounds, StaticData, Index);
1198 }
1199 
1200 CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy CodeGenFunction::
1201 EmitComplexPrePostIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E, LValue LV,
1202  bool isInc, bool isPre) {
1203  ComplexPairTy InVal = EmitLoadOfComplex(LV, E->getExprLoc());
1204 
1205  llvm::Value *NextVal;
1206  if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(InVal.first->getType())) {
1207  uint64_t AmountVal = isInc ? 1 : -1;
1208  NextVal = llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal.first->getType(), AmountVal, true);
1209 
1210  // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
1211  NextVal = Builder.CreateAdd(InVal.first, NextVal, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
1212  } else {
1213  QualType ElemTy = E->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
1214  llvm::APFloat FVal(getContext().getFloatTypeSemantics(ElemTy), 1);
1215  if (!isInc)
1216  FVal.changeSign();
1217  NextVal = llvm::ConstantFP::get(getLLVMContext(), FVal);
1218 
1219  // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
1220  NextVal = Builder.CreateFAdd(InVal.first, NextVal, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
1221  }
1222 
1223  ComplexPairTy IncVal(NextVal, InVal.second);
1224 
1225  // Store the updated result through the lvalue.
1226  EmitStoreOfComplex(IncVal, LV, /*init*/ false);
1227  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP)
1228  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().checkAndEmitLastprivateConditional(*this,
1229  E->getSubExpr());
1230 
1231  // If this is a postinc, return the value read from memory, otherwise use the
1232  // updated value.
1233  return isPre ? IncVal : InVal;
1234 }
1235 
1236 void CodeGenModule::EmitExplicitCastExprType(const ExplicitCastExpr *E,
1237  CodeGenFunction *CGF) {
1238  // Bind VLAs in the cast type.
1239  if (CGF && E->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType())
1240  CGF->EmitVariablyModifiedType(E->getType());
1241 
1242  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
1243  DI->EmitExplicitCastType(E->getType());
1244 }
1245 
1246 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1247 // LValue Expression Emission
1248 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1249 
1250 static Address EmitPointerWithAlignment(const Expr *E, LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
1251  TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo,
1252  KnownNonNull_t IsKnownNonNull,
1253  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1254  // We allow this with ObjC object pointers because of fragile ABIs.
1255  assert(E->getType()->isPointerType() ||
1256  E->getType()->isObjCObjectPointerType());
1257  E = E->IgnoreParens();
1258 
1259  // Casts:
1260  if (const CastExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(E)) {
1261  if (const auto *ECE = dyn_cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(CE))
1262  CGF.CGM.EmitExplicitCastExprType(ECE, &CGF);
1263 
1264  switch (CE->getCastKind()) {
1265  // Non-converting casts (but not C's implicit conversion from void*).
1266  case CK_BitCast:
1267  case CK_NoOp:
1268  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion:
1269  if (auto PtrTy = CE->getSubExpr()->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
1270  if (PtrTy->getPointeeType()->isVoidType())
1271  break;
1272 
1273  LValueBaseInfo InnerBaseInfo;
1274  TBAAAccessInfo InnerTBAAInfo;
1275  Address Addr = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(
1276  CE->getSubExpr(), &InnerBaseInfo, &InnerTBAAInfo, IsKnownNonNull);
1277  if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = InnerBaseInfo;
1278  if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = InnerTBAAInfo;
1279 
1280  if (isa<ExplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
1281  LValueBaseInfo TargetTypeBaseInfo;
1282  TBAAAccessInfo TargetTypeTBAAInfo;
1283  CharUnits Align = CGF.CGM.getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(
1284  E->getType(), &TargetTypeBaseInfo, &TargetTypeTBAAInfo);
1285  if (TBAAInfo)
1286  *TBAAInfo =
1287  CGF.CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForCast(*TBAAInfo, TargetTypeTBAAInfo);
1288  // If the source l-value is opaque, honor the alignment of the
1289  // casted-to type.
1290  if (InnerBaseInfo.getAlignmentSource() != AlignmentSource::Decl) {
1291  if (BaseInfo)
1292  BaseInfo->mergeForCast(TargetTypeBaseInfo);
1293  Addr.setAlignment(Align);
1294  }
1295  }
1296 
1297  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast) &&
1298  CE->getCastKind() == CK_BitCast) {
1299  if (auto PT = E->getType()->getAs<PointerType>())
1300  CGF.EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(PT->getPointeeType(), Addr,
1301  /*MayBeNull=*/true,
1302  CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_UnrelatedCast,
1303  CE->getBeginLoc());
1304  }
1305 
1306  llvm::Type *ElemTy =
1307  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType()->getPointeeType());
1308  Addr = Addr.withElementType(ElemTy);
1309  if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_AddressSpaceConversion)
1310  Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(
1311  Addr, CGF.ConvertType(E->getType()), ElemTy);
1312  return Addr;
1313  }
1314  break;
1315 
1316  // Array-to-pointer decay.
1317  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
1318  return CGF.EmitArrayToPointerDecay(CE->getSubExpr(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
1319 
1320  // Derived-to-base conversions.
1321  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
1322  case CK_DerivedToBase: {
1323  // TODO: Support accesses to members of base classes in TBAA. For now, we
1324  // conservatively pretend that the complete object is of the base class
1325  // type.
1326  if (TBAAInfo)
1327  *TBAAInfo = CGF.CGM.getTBAAAccessInfo(E->getType());
1328  Address Addr = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(
1329  CE->getSubExpr(), BaseInfo, nullptr,
1330  (KnownNonNull_t)(IsKnownNonNull ||
1331  CE->getCastKind() == CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase));
1332  auto Derived = CE->getSubExpr()->getType()->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
1333  return CGF.GetAddressOfBaseClass(
1334  Addr, Derived, CE->path_begin(), CE->path_end(),
1335  CGF.ShouldNullCheckClassCastValue(CE), CE->getExprLoc());
1336  }
1337 
1338  // TODO: Is there any reason to treat base-to-derived conversions
1339  // specially?
1340  default:
1341  break;
1342  }
1343  }
1344 
1345  // Unary &.
1346  if (const UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
1347  if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf) {
1348  LValue LV = CGF.EmitLValue(UO->getSubExpr(), IsKnownNonNull);
1349  if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = LV.getBaseInfo();
1350  if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = LV.getTBAAInfo();
1351  return LV.getAddress(CGF);
1352  }
1353  }
1354 
1355  // std::addressof and variants.
1356  if (auto *Call = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(E)) {
1357  switch (Call->getBuiltinCallee()) {
1358  default:
1359  break;
1360  case Builtin::BIaddressof:
1361  case Builtin::BI__addressof:
1362  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addressof: {
1363  LValue LV = CGF.EmitLValue(Call->getArg(0), IsKnownNonNull);
1364  if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = LV.getBaseInfo();
1365  if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = LV.getTBAAInfo();
1366  return LV.getAddress(CGF);
1367  }
1368  }
1369  }
1370 
1371  // TODO: conditional operators, comma.
1372 
1373  // Otherwise, use the alignment of the type.
1374  return CGF.makeNaturalAddressForPointer(
1375  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E), E->getType()->getPointeeType(), CharUnits(),
1376  /*ForPointeeType=*/true, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo, IsKnownNonNull);
1377 }
1378 
1379 /// EmitPointerWithAlignment - Given an expression of pointer type, try to
1380 /// derive a more accurate bound on the alignment of the pointer.
1381 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitPointerWithAlignment(
1382  const Expr *E, LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo, TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo,
1383  KnownNonNull_t IsKnownNonNull) {
1384  Address Addr =
1385  ::EmitPointerWithAlignment(E, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo, IsKnownNonNull, *this);
1386  if (IsKnownNonNull && !Addr.isKnownNonNull())
1387  Addr.setKnownNonNull();
1388  return Addr;
1389 }
1390 
1391 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitNonNullRValueCheck(RValue RV, QualType T) {
1392  llvm::Value *V = RV.getScalarVal();
1393  if (auto MPT = T->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
1394  return CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(*this, V, MPT);
1395  return Builder.CreateICmpNE(V, llvm::Constant::getNullValue(V->getType()));
1396 }
1397 
1398 RValue CodeGenFunction::GetUndefRValue(QualType Ty) {
1399  if (Ty->isVoidType())
1400  return RValue::get(nullptr);
1401 
1402  switch (getEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
1403  case TEK_Complex: {
1404  llvm::Type *EltTy =
1405  ConvertType(Ty->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType());
1406  llvm::Value *U = llvm::UndefValue::get(EltTy);
1407  return RValue::getComplex(std::make_pair(U, U));
1408  }
1409 
1410  // If this is a use of an undefined aggregate type, the aggregate must have an
1411  // identifiable address. Just because the contents of the value are undefined
1412  // doesn't mean that the address can't be taken and compared.
1413  case TEK_Aggregate: {
1414  Address DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(Ty, "undef.agg.tmp");
1415  return RValue::getAggregate(DestPtr);
1416  }
1417 
1418  case TEK_Scalar:
1419  return RValue::get(llvm::UndefValue::get(ConvertType(Ty)));
1420  }
1421  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
1422 }
1423 
1424 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitUnsupportedRValue(const Expr *E,
1425  const char *Name) {
1426  ErrorUnsupported(E, Name);
1427  return GetUndefRValue(E->getType());
1428 }
1429 
1430 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitUnsupportedLValue(const Expr *E,
1431  const char *Name) {
1432  ErrorUnsupported(E, Name);
1433  llvm::Type *ElTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
1434  llvm::Type *Ty = UnqualPtrTy;
1435  return MakeAddrLValue(
1436  Address(llvm::UndefValue::get(Ty), ElTy, CharUnits::One()), E->getType());
1437 }
1438 
1439 bool CodeGenFunction::IsWrappedCXXThis(const Expr *Obj) {
1440  const Expr *Base = Obj;
1441  while (!isa<CXXThisExpr>(Base)) {
1442  // The result of a dynamic_cast can be null.
1443  if (isa<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(Base))
1444  return false;
1445 
1446  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Base)) {
1447  Base = CE->getSubExpr();
1448  } else if (const auto *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(Base)) {
1449  Base = PE->getSubExpr();
1450  } else if (const auto *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Base)) {
1451  if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_Extension)
1452  Base = UO->getSubExpr();
1453  else
1454  return false;
1455  } else {
1456  return false;
1457  }
1458  }
1459  return true;
1460 }
1461 
1462 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckedLValue(const Expr *E, TypeCheckKind TCK) {
1463  LValue LV;
1464  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds) && isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E))
1465  LV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E), /*Accessed*/true);
1466  else
1467  LV = EmitLValue(E);
1468  if (!isa<DeclRefExpr>(E) && !LV.isBitField() && LV.isSimple()) {
1469  SanitizerSet SkippedChecks;
1470  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
1471  bool IsBaseCXXThis = IsWrappedCXXThis(ME->getBase());
1472  if (IsBaseCXXThis)
1473  SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Alignment, true);
1474  if (IsBaseCXXThis || isa<DeclRefExpr>(ME->getBase()))
1475  SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Null, true);
1476  }
1477  EmitTypeCheck(TCK, E->getExprLoc(), LV, E->getType(), SkippedChecks);
1478  }
1479  return LV;
1480 }
1481 
1482 /// EmitLValue - Emit code to compute a designator that specifies the location
1483 /// of the expression.
1484 ///
1485 /// This can return one of two things: a simple address or a bitfield reference.
1486 /// In either case, the LLVM Value* in the LValue structure is guaranteed to be
1487 /// an LLVM pointer type.
1488 ///
1489 /// If this returns a bitfield reference, nothing about the pointee type of the
1490 /// LLVM value is known: For example, it may not be a pointer to an integer.
1491 ///
1492 /// If this returns a normal address, and if the lvalue's C type is fixed size,
1493 /// this method guarantees that the returned pointer type will point to an LLVM
1494 /// type of the same size of the lvalue's type. If the lvalue has a variable
1495 /// length type, this is not possible.
1496 ///
1497 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValue(const Expr *E,
1498  KnownNonNull_t IsKnownNonNull) {
1499  LValue LV = EmitLValueHelper(E, IsKnownNonNull);
1500  if (IsKnownNonNull && !LV.isKnownNonNull())
1501  LV.setKnownNonNull();
1502  return LV;
1503 }
1504 
1505 static QualType getConstantExprReferredType(const FullExpr *E,
1506  const ASTContext &Ctx) {
1507  const Expr *SE = E->getSubExpr()->IgnoreImplicit();
1508  if (isa<OpaqueValueExpr>(SE))
1509  return SE->getType();
1510  return cast<CallExpr>(SE)->getCallReturnType(Ctx)->getPointeeType();
1511 }
1512 
1513 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueHelper(const Expr *E,
1514  KnownNonNull_t IsKnownNonNull) {
1515  ApplyDebugLocation DL(*this, E);
1516  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
1517  default: return EmitUnsupportedLValue(E, "l-value expression");
1518 
1519  case Expr::ObjCPropertyRefExprClass:
1520  llvm_unreachable("cannot emit a property reference directly");
1521 
1522  case Expr::ObjCSelectorExprClass:
1523  return EmitObjCSelectorLValue(cast<ObjCSelectorExpr>(E));
1524  case Expr::ObjCIsaExprClass:
1525  return EmitObjCIsaExpr(cast<ObjCIsaExpr>(E));
1526  case Expr::BinaryOperatorClass:
1527  return EmitBinaryOperatorLValue(cast<BinaryOperator>(E));
1528  case Expr::CompoundAssignOperatorClass: {
1529  QualType Ty = E->getType();
1530  if (const AtomicType *AT = Ty->getAs<AtomicType>())
1531  Ty = AT->getValueType();
1532  if (!Ty->isAnyComplexType())
1533  return EmitCompoundAssignmentLValue(cast<CompoundAssignOperator>(E));
1534  return EmitComplexCompoundAssignmentLValue(cast<CompoundAssignOperator>(E));
1535  }
1536  case Expr::CallExprClass:
1537  case Expr::CXXMemberCallExprClass:
1538  case Expr::CXXOperatorCallExprClass:
1539  case Expr::UserDefinedLiteralClass:
1540  return EmitCallExprLValue(cast<CallExpr>(E));
1541  case Expr::CXXRewrittenBinaryOperatorClass:
1542  return EmitLValue(cast<CXXRewrittenBinaryOperator>(E)->getSemanticForm(),
1543  IsKnownNonNull);
1544  case Expr::VAArgExprClass:
1545  return EmitVAArgExprLValue(cast<VAArgExpr>(E));
1546  case Expr::DeclRefExprClass:
1547  return EmitDeclRefLValue(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E));
1548  case Expr::ConstantExprClass: {
1549  const ConstantExpr *CE = cast<ConstantExpr>(E);
1550  if (llvm::Value *Result = ConstantEmitter(*this).tryEmitConstantExpr(CE)) {
1551  QualType RetType = getConstantExprReferredType(CE, getContext());
1552  return MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(Result, RetType);
1553  }
1554  return EmitLValue(cast<ConstantExpr>(E)->getSubExpr(), IsKnownNonNull);
1555  }
1556  case Expr::ParenExprClass:
1557  return EmitLValue(cast<ParenExpr>(E)->getSubExpr(), IsKnownNonNull);
1558  case Expr::GenericSelectionExprClass:
1559  return EmitLValue(cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)->getResultExpr(),
1560  IsKnownNonNull);
1561  case Expr::PredefinedExprClass:
1562  return EmitPredefinedLValue(cast<PredefinedExpr>(E));
1563  case Expr::StringLiteralClass:
1564  return EmitStringLiteralLValue(cast<StringLiteral>(E));
1565  case Expr::ObjCEncodeExprClass:
1566  return EmitObjCEncodeExprLValue(cast<ObjCEncodeExpr>(E));
1567  case Expr::PseudoObjectExprClass:
1568  return EmitPseudoObjectLValue(cast<PseudoObjectExpr>(E));
1569  case Expr::InitListExprClass:
1570  return EmitInitListLValue(cast<InitListExpr>(E));
1571  case Expr::CXXTemporaryObjectExprClass:
1572  case Expr::CXXConstructExprClass:
1573  return EmitCXXConstructLValue(cast<CXXConstructExpr>(E));
1574  case Expr::CXXBindTemporaryExprClass:
1575  return EmitCXXBindTemporaryLValue(cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E));
1576  case Expr::CXXUuidofExprClass:
1577  return EmitCXXUuidofLValue(cast<CXXUuidofExpr>(E));
1578  case Expr::LambdaExprClass:
1579  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
1580 
1581  case Expr::ExprWithCleanupsClass: {
1582  const auto *cleanups = cast<ExprWithCleanups>(E);
1583  RunCleanupsScope Scope(*this);
1584  LValue LV = EmitLValue(cleanups->getSubExpr(), IsKnownNonNull);
1585  if (LV.isSimple()) {
1586  // Defend against branches out of gnu statement expressions surrounded by
1587  // cleanups.
1588  Address Addr = LV.getAddress(*this);
1589  llvm::Value *V = Addr.getBasePointer();
1590  Scope.ForceCleanup({&V});
1591  Addr.replaceBasePointer(V);
1592  return LValue::MakeAddr(Addr, LV.getType(), getContext(),
1593  LV.getBaseInfo(), LV.getTBAAInfo());
1594  }
1595  // FIXME: Is it possible to create an ExprWithCleanups that produces a
1596  // bitfield lvalue or some other non-simple lvalue?
1597  return LV;
1598  }
1599 
1600  case Expr::CXXDefaultArgExprClass: {
1601  auto *DAE = cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(E);
1602  CXXDefaultArgExprScope Scope(*this, DAE);
1603  return EmitLValue(DAE->getExpr(), IsKnownNonNull);
1604  }
1605  case Expr::CXXDefaultInitExprClass: {
1606  auto *DIE = cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(E);
1607  CXXDefaultInitExprScope Scope(*this, DIE);
1608  return EmitLValue(DIE->getExpr(), IsKnownNonNull);
1609  }
1610  case Expr::CXXTypeidExprClass:
1611  return EmitCXXTypeidLValue(cast<CXXTypeidExpr>(E));
1612 
1613  case Expr::ObjCMessageExprClass:
1614  return EmitObjCMessageExprLValue(cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(E));
1615  case Expr::ObjCIvarRefExprClass:
1616  return EmitObjCIvarRefLValue(cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E));
1617  case Expr::StmtExprClass:
1618  return EmitStmtExprLValue(cast<StmtExpr>(E));
1619  case Expr::UnaryOperatorClass:
1620  return EmitUnaryOpLValue(cast<UnaryOperator>(E));
1621  case Expr::ArraySubscriptExprClass:
1622  return EmitArraySubscriptExpr(cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E));
1623  case Expr::MatrixSubscriptExprClass:
1624  return EmitMatrixSubscriptExpr(cast<MatrixSubscriptExpr>(E));
1625  case Expr::OMPArraySectionExprClass:
1626  return EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(E));
1627  case Expr::ExtVectorElementExprClass:
1628  return EmitExtVectorElementExpr(cast<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E));
1629  case Expr::CXXThisExprClass:
1630  return MakeAddrLValue(LoadCXXThisAddress(), E->getType());
1631  case Expr::MemberExprClass:
1632  return EmitMemberExpr(cast<MemberExpr>(E));
1633  case Expr::CompoundLiteralExprClass:
1634  return EmitCompoundLiteralLValue(cast<CompoundLiteralExpr>(E));
1635  case Expr::ConditionalOperatorClass:
1636  return EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(cast<ConditionalOperator>(E));
1637  case Expr::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass:
1638  return EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(cast<BinaryConditionalOperator>(E));
1639  case Expr::ChooseExprClass:
1640  return EmitLValue(cast<ChooseExpr>(E)->getChosenSubExpr(), IsKnownNonNull);
1641  case Expr::OpaqueValueExprClass:
1642  return EmitOpaqueValueLValue(cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(E));
1643  case Expr::SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExprClass:
1644  return EmitLValue(cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)->getReplacement(),
1645  IsKnownNonNull);
1646  case Expr::ImplicitCastExprClass:
1647  case Expr::CStyleCastExprClass:
1648  case Expr::CXXFunctionalCastExprClass:
1649  case Expr::CXXStaticCastExprClass:
1650  case Expr::CXXDynamicCastExprClass:
1651  case Expr::CXXReinterpretCastExprClass:
1652  case Expr::CXXConstCastExprClass:
1653  case Expr::CXXAddrspaceCastExprClass:
1654  case Expr::ObjCBridgedCastExprClass:
1655  return EmitCastLValue(cast<CastExpr>(E));
1656 
1657  case Expr::MaterializeTemporaryExprClass:
1658  return EmitMaterializeTemporaryExpr(cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(E));
1659 
1660  case Expr::CoawaitExprClass:
1661  return EmitCoawaitLValue(cast<CoawaitExpr>(E));
1662  case Expr::CoyieldExprClass:
1663  return EmitCoyieldLValue(cast<CoyieldExpr>(E));
1664  case Expr::PackIndexingExprClass:
1665  return EmitLValue(cast<PackIndexingExpr>(E)->getSelectedExpr());
1666  }
1667 }
1668 
1669 /// Given an object of the given canonical type, can we safely copy a
1670 /// value out of it based on its initializer?
1671 static bool isConstantEmittableObjectType(QualType type) {
1672  assert(type.isCanonical());
1673  assert(!type->isReferenceType());
1674 
1675  // Must be const-qualified but non-volatile.
1676  Qualifiers qs = type.getLocalQualifiers();
1677  if (!qs.hasConst() || qs.hasVolatile()) return false;
1678 
1679  // Otherwise, all object types satisfy this except C++ classes with
1680  // mutable subobjects or non-trivial copy/destroy behavior.
1681  if (const auto *RT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(type))
1682  if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()))
1683  if (RD->hasMutableFields() || !RD->isTrivial())
1684  return false;
1685 
1686  return true;
1687 }
1688 
1689 /// Can we constant-emit a load of a reference to a variable of the
1690 /// given type? This is different from predicates like
1691 /// Decl::mightBeUsableInConstantExpressions because we do want it to apply
1692 /// in situations that don't necessarily satisfy the language's rules
1693 /// for this (e.g. C++'s ODR-use rules). For example, we want to able
1694 /// to do this with const float variables even if those variables
1695 /// aren't marked 'constexpr'.
1696 enum ConstantEmissionKind {
1697  CEK_None,
1698  CEK_AsReferenceOnly,
1699  CEK_AsValueOrReference,
1700  CEK_AsValueOnly
1701 };
1702 static ConstantEmissionKind checkVarTypeForConstantEmission(QualType type) {
1703  type = type.getCanonicalType();
1704  if (const auto *ref = dyn_cast<ReferenceType>(type)) {
1705  if (isConstantEmittableObjectType(ref->getPointeeType()))
1706  return CEK_AsValueOrReference;
1707  return CEK_AsReferenceOnly;
1708  }
1709  if (isConstantEmittableObjectType(type))
1710  return CEK_AsValueOnly;
1711  return CEK_None;
1712 }
1713 
1714 /// Try to emit a reference to the given value without producing it as
1715 /// an l-value. This is just an optimization, but it avoids us needing
1716 /// to emit global copies of variables if they're named without triggering
1717 /// a formal use in a context where we can't emit a direct reference to them,
1718 /// for instance if a block or lambda or a member of a local class uses a
1719 /// const int variable or constexpr variable from an enclosing function.
1720 CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission
1721 CodeGenFunction::tryEmitAsConstant(DeclRefExpr *refExpr) {
1722  ValueDecl *value = refExpr->getDecl();
1723 
1724  // The value needs to be an enum constant or a constant variable.
1725  ConstantEmissionKind CEK;
1726  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(value)) {
1727  CEK = CEK_None;
1728  } else if (auto *var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(value)) {
1729  CEK = checkVarTypeForConstantEmission(var->getType());
1730  } else if (isa<EnumConstantDecl>(value)) {
1731  CEK = CEK_AsValueOnly;
1732  } else {
1733  CEK = CEK_None;
1734  }
1735  if (CEK == CEK_None) return ConstantEmission();
1736 
1737  Expr::EvalResult result;
1738  bool resultIsReference;
1739  QualType resultType;
1740 
1741  // It's best to evaluate all the way as an r-value if that's permitted.
1742  if (CEK != CEK_AsReferenceOnly &&
1743  refExpr->EvaluateAsRValue(result, getContext())) {
1744  resultIsReference = false;
1745  resultType = refExpr->getType();
1746 
1747  // Otherwise, try to evaluate as an l-value.
1748  } else if (CEK != CEK_AsValueOnly &&
1749  refExpr->EvaluateAsLValue(result, getContext())) {
1750  resultIsReference = true;
1751  resultType = value->getType();
1752 
1753  // Failure.
1754  } else {
1755  return ConstantEmission();
1756  }
1757 
1758  // In any case, if the initializer has side-effects, abandon ship.
1759  if (result.HasSideEffects)
1760  return ConstantEmission();
1761 
1762  // In CUDA/HIP device compilation, a lambda may capture a reference variable
1763  // referencing a global host variable by copy. In this case the lambda should
1764  // make a copy of the value of the global host variable. The DRE of the
1765  // captured reference variable cannot be emitted as load from the host
1766  // global variable as compile time constant, since the host variable is not
1767  // accessible on device. The DRE of the captured reference variable has to be
1768  // loaded from captures.
1769  if (CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && result.Val.isLValue() &&
1770  refExpr->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture()) {
1771  auto *MD = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl);
1772  if (MD && MD->getParent()->isLambda() &&
1773  MD->getOverloadedOperator() == OO_Call) {
1774  const APValue::LValueBase &base = result.Val.getLValueBase();
1775  if (const ValueDecl *D = base.dyn_cast<const ValueDecl *>()) {
1776  if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<const VarDecl>(D)) {
1777  if (!VD->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
1778  return ConstantEmission();
1779  }
1780  }
1781  }
1782  }
1783  }
1784 
1785  // Emit as a constant.
1786  auto C = ConstantEmitter(*this).emitAbstract(refExpr->getLocation(),
1787  result.Val, resultType);
1788 
1789  // Make sure we emit a debug reference to the global variable.
1790  // This should probably fire even for
1791  if (isa<VarDecl>(value)) {
1792  if (!getContext().DeclMustBeEmitted(cast<VarDecl>(value)))
1793  EmitDeclRefExprDbgValue(refExpr, result.Val);
1794  } else {
1795  assert(isa<EnumConstantDecl>(value));
1796  EmitDeclRefExprDbgValue(refExpr, result.Val);
1797  }
1798 
1799  // If we emitted a reference constant, we need to dereference that.
1800  if (resultIsReference)
1801  return ConstantEmission::forReference(C);
1802 
1803  return ConstantEmission::forValue(C);
1804 }
1805 
1806 static DeclRefExpr *tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1807  const MemberExpr *ME) {
1808  if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
1809  // Try to emit static variable member expressions as DREs.
1810  return DeclRefExpr::Create(
1811  CGF.getContext(), NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), SourceLocation(), VD,
1812  /*RefersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture=*/false, ME->getExprLoc(),
1813  ME->getType(), ME->getValueKind(), nullptr, nullptr, ME->isNonOdrUse());
1814  }
1815  return nullptr;
1816 }
1817 
1818 CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission
1819 CodeGenFunction::tryEmitAsConstant(const MemberExpr *ME) {
1820  if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(*this, ME))
1821  return tryEmitAsConstant(DRE);
1822  return ConstantEmission();
1823 }
1824 
1825 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::emitScalarConstant(
1826  const CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission &Constant, Expr *E) {
1827  assert(Constant && "not a constant");
1828  if (Constant.isReference())
1829  return EmitLoadOfLValue(Constant.getReferenceLValue(*this, E),
1830  E->getExprLoc())
1831  .getScalarVal();
1832  return Constant.getValue();
1833 }
1834 
1835 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfScalar(LValue lvalue,
1836  SourceLocation Loc) {
1837  return EmitLoadOfScalar(lvalue.getAddress(*this), lvalue.isVolatile(),
1838  lvalue.getType(), Loc, lvalue.getBaseInfo(),
1839  lvalue.getTBAAInfo(), lvalue.isNontemporal());
1840 }
1841 
1842 static bool hasBooleanRepresentation(QualType Ty) {
1843  if (Ty->isBooleanType())
1844  return true;
1845 
1846  if (const EnumType *ET = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
1847  return ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType()->isBooleanType();
1848 
1849  if (const AtomicType *AT = Ty->getAs<AtomicType>())
1850  return hasBooleanRepresentation(AT->getValueType());
1851 
1852  return false;
1853 }
1854 
1855 static bool getRangeForType(CodeGenFunction &CGF, QualType Ty,
1856  llvm::APInt &Min, llvm::APInt &End,
1857  bool StrictEnums, bool IsBool) {
1858  const EnumType *ET = Ty->getAs<EnumType>();
1859  bool IsRegularCPlusPlusEnum = CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && StrictEnums &&
1860  ET && !ET->getDecl()->isFixed();
1861  if (!IsBool && !IsRegularCPlusPlusEnum)
1862  return false;
1863 
1864  if (IsBool) {
1865  Min = llvm::APInt(CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty), 0);
1866  End = llvm::APInt(CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty), 2);
1867  } else {
1868  const EnumDecl *ED = ET->getDecl();
1869  ED->getValueRange(End, Min);
1870  }
1871  return true;
1872 }
1873 
1874 llvm::MDNode *CodeGenFunction::getRangeForLoadFromType(QualType Ty) {
1875  llvm::APInt Min, End;
1876  if (!getRangeForType(*this, Ty, Min, End, CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictEnums,
1877  hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)))
1878  return nullptr;
1879 
1880  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
1881  return MDHelper.createRange(Min, End);
1882 }
1883 
1884 bool CodeGenFunction::EmitScalarRangeCheck(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty,
1885  SourceLocation Loc) {
1886  bool HasBoolCheck = SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Bool);
1887  bool HasEnumCheck = SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Enum);
1888  if (!HasBoolCheck && !HasEnumCheck)
1889  return false;
1890 
1891  bool IsBool = hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty) ||
1892  NSAPI(CGM.getContext()).isObjCBOOLType(Ty);
1893  bool NeedsBoolCheck = HasBoolCheck && IsBool;
1894  bool NeedsEnumCheck = HasEnumCheck && Ty->getAs<EnumType>();
1895  if (!NeedsBoolCheck && !NeedsEnumCheck)
1896  return false;
1897 
1898  // Single-bit booleans don't need to be checked. Special-case this to avoid
1899  // a bit width mismatch when handling bitfield values. This is handled by
1900  // EmitFromMemory for the non-bitfield case.
1901  if (IsBool &&
1902  cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Value->getType())->getBitWidth() == 1)
1903  return false;
1904 
1905  llvm::APInt Min, End;
1906  if (!getRangeForType(*this, Ty, Min, End, /*StrictEnums=*/true, IsBool))
1907  return true;
1908 
1909  auto &Ctx = getLLVMContext();
1910  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
1911  llvm::Value *Check;
1912  --End;
1913  if (!Min) {
1914  Check = Builder.CreateICmpULE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, End));
1915  } else {
1916  llvm::Value *Upper =
1917  Builder.CreateICmpSLE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, End));
1918  llvm::Value *Lower =
1919  Builder.CreateICmpSGE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, Min));
1920  Check = Builder.CreateAnd(Upper, Lower);
1921  }
1922  llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc),
1923  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty)};
1924  SanitizerMask Kind =
1925  NeedsEnumCheck ? SanitizerKind::Enum : SanitizerKind::Bool;
1926  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Check, Kind), SanitizerHandler::LoadInvalidValue,
1927  StaticArgs, EmitCheckValue(Value));
1928  return true;
1929 }
1930 
1931 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfScalar(Address Addr, bool Volatile,
1932  QualType Ty,
1933  SourceLocation Loc,
1934  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo,
1935  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo,
1936  bool isNontemporal) {
1937  if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Addr.getBasePointer()))
1938  if (GV->isThreadLocal())
1939  Addr = Addr.withPointer(Builder.CreateThreadLocalAddress(GV),
1940  NotKnownNonNull);
1941 
1942  if (const auto *ClangVecTy = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
1943  // Boolean vectors use `iN` as storage type.
1944  if (ClangVecTy->isExtVectorBoolType()) {
1945  llvm::Type *ValTy = ConvertType(Ty);
1946  unsigned ValNumElems =
1947  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(ValTy)->getNumElements();
1948  // Load the `iP` storage object (P is the padded vector size).
1949  auto *RawIntV = Builder.CreateLoad(Addr, Volatile, "load_bits");
1950  const auto *RawIntTy = RawIntV->getType();
1951  assert(RawIntTy->isIntegerTy() && "compressed iN storage for bitvectors");
1952  // Bitcast iP --> <P x i1>.
1953  auto *PaddedVecTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
1954  Builder.getInt1Ty(), RawIntTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
1955  llvm::Value *V = Builder.CreateBitCast(RawIntV, PaddedVecTy);
1956  // Shuffle <P x i1> --> <N x i1> (N is the actual bit size).
1957  V = emitBoolVecConversion(V, ValNumElems, "extractvec");
1958 
1959  return EmitFromMemory(V, Ty);
1960  }
1961 
1962  // Handle vectors of size 3 like size 4 for better performance.
1963  const llvm::Type *EltTy = Addr.getElementType();
1964  const auto *VTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(EltTy);
1965 
1966  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PreserveVec3Type && VTy->getNumElements() == 3) {
1967 
1968  llvm::VectorType *vec4Ty =
1969  llvm::FixedVectorType::get(VTy->getElementType(), 4);
1970  Address Cast = Addr.withElementType(vec4Ty);
1971  // Now load value.
1972  llvm::Value *V = Builder.CreateLoad(Cast, Volatile, "loadVec4");
1973 
1974  // Shuffle vector to get vec3.
1975  V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, ArrayRef<int>{0, 1, 2}, "extractVec");
1976  return EmitFromMemory(V, Ty);
1977  }
1978  }
1979 
1980  // Atomic operations have to be done on integral types.
1981  LValue AtomicLValue =
1982  LValue::MakeAddr(Addr, Ty, getContext(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
1983  if (Ty->isAtomicType() || LValueIsSuitableForInlineAtomic(AtomicLValue)) {
1984  return EmitAtomicLoad(AtomicLValue, Loc).getScalarVal();
1985  }
1986 
1987  llvm::LoadInst *Load = Builder.CreateLoad(Addr, Volatile);
1988  if (isNontemporal) {
1989  llvm::MDNode *Node = llvm::MDNode::get(
1990  Load->getContext(), llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(1)));
1991  Load->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_nontemporal, Node);
1992  }
1993 
1994  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Load, TBAAInfo);
1995 
1996  if (EmitScalarRangeCheck(Load, Ty, Loc)) {
1997  // In order to prevent the optimizer from throwing away the check, don't
1998  // attach range metadata to the load.
1999  } else if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0)
2000  if (llvm::MDNode *RangeInfo = getRangeForLoadFromType(Ty)) {
2001  Load->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_range, RangeInfo);
2002  Load->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_noundef,
2003  llvm::MDNode::get(getLLVMContext(), std::nullopt));
2004  }
2005 
2006  return EmitFromMemory(Load, Ty);
2007 }
2008 
2009 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitToMemory(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty) {
2010  // Bool has a different representation in memory than in registers.
2011  if (hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)) {
2012  // This should really always be an i1, but sometimes it's already
2013  // an i8, and it's awkward to track those cases down.
2014  if (Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(1))
2015  return Builder.CreateZExt(Value, ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), "frombool");
2016  assert(Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty)) &&
2017  "wrong value rep of bool");
2018  }
2019 
2020  return Value;
2021 }
2022 
2023 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitFromMemory(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty) {
2024  // Bool has a different representation in memory than in registers.
2025  if (hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)) {
2026  assert(Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty)) &&
2027  "wrong value rep of bool");
2028  return Builder.CreateTrunc(Value, Builder.getInt1Ty(), "tobool");
2029  }
2030  if (Ty->isExtVectorBoolType()) {
2031  const auto *RawIntTy = Value->getType();
2032  // Bitcast iP --> <P x i1>.
2033  auto *PaddedVecTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
2034  Builder.getInt1Ty(), RawIntTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
2035  auto *V = Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, PaddedVecTy);
2036  // Shuffle <P x i1> --> <N x i1> (N is the actual bit size).
2037  llvm::Type *ValTy = ConvertType(Ty);
2038  unsigned ValNumElems = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(ValTy)->getNumElements();
2039  return emitBoolVecConversion(V, ValNumElems, "extractvec");
2040  }
2041 
2042  return Value;
2043 }
2044 
2045 // Convert the pointer of \p Addr to a pointer to a vector (the value type of
2046 // MatrixType), if it points to a array (the memory type of MatrixType).
2047 static RawAddress MaybeConvertMatrixAddress(RawAddress Addr,
2048  CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2049  bool IsVector = true) {
2050  auto *ArrayTy = dyn_cast<llvm::ArrayType>(Addr.getElementType());
2051  if (ArrayTy && IsVector) {
2052  auto *VectorTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(ArrayTy->getElementType(),
2053  ArrayTy->getNumElements());
2054 
2055  return Addr.withElementType(VectorTy);
2056  }
2057  auto *VectorTy = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(Addr.getElementType());
2058  if (VectorTy && !IsVector) {
2059  auto *ArrayTy = llvm::ArrayType::get(
2060  VectorTy->getElementType(),
2061  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(VectorTy)->getNumElements());
2062 
2063  return Addr.withElementType(ArrayTy);
2064  }
2065 
2066  return Addr;
2067 }
2068 
2069 // Emit a store of a matrix LValue. This may require casting the original
2070 // pointer to memory address (ArrayType) to a pointer to the value type
2071 // (VectorType).
2072 static void EmitStoreOfMatrixScalar(llvm::Value *value, LValue lvalue,
2073  bool isInit, CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
2074  Address Addr = MaybeConvertMatrixAddress(lvalue.getAddress(CGF), CGF,
2075  value->getType()->isVectorTy());
2076  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(value, Addr, lvalue.isVolatile(), lvalue.getType(),
2077  lvalue.getBaseInfo(), lvalue.getTBAAInfo(), isInit,
2078  lvalue.isNontemporal());
2079 }
2080 
2081 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::Value *Value, Address Addr,
2082  bool Volatile, QualType Ty,
2083  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo,
2084  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo,
2085  bool isInit, bool isNontemporal) {
2086  if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Addr.getBasePointer()))
2087  if (GV->isThreadLocal())
2088  Addr = Addr.withPointer(Builder.CreateThreadLocalAddress(GV),
2089  NotKnownNonNull);
2090 
2091  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Value->getType();
2092  if (const auto *ClangVecTy = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
2093  auto *VecTy = dyn_cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SrcTy);
2094  if (VecTy && ClangVecTy->isExtVectorBoolType()) {
2095  auto *MemIntTy = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Addr.getElementType());
2096  // Expand to the memory bit width.
2097  unsigned MemNumElems = MemIntTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
2098  // <N x i1> --> <P x i1>.
2099  Value = emitBoolVecConversion(Value, MemNumElems, "insertvec");
2100  // <P x i1> --> iP.
2101  Value = Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, MemIntTy);
2102  } else if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PreserveVec3Type) {
2103  // Handle vec3 special.
2104  if (VecTy && cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(VecTy)->getNumElements() == 3) {
2105  // Our source is a vec3, do a shuffle vector to make it a vec4.
2106  Value = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Value, ArrayRef<int>{0, 1, 2, -1},
2107  "extractVec");
2108  SrcTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(VecTy->getElementType(), 4);
2109  }
2110  if (Addr.getElementType() != SrcTy) {
2111  Addr = Addr.withElementType(SrcTy);
2112  }
2113  }
2114  }
2115 
2116  Value = EmitToMemory(Value, Ty);
2117 
2118  LValue AtomicLValue =
2119  LValue::MakeAddr(Addr, Ty, getContext(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
2120  if (Ty->isAtomicType() ||
2121  (!isInit && LValueIsSuitableForInlineAtomic(AtomicLValue))) {
2122  EmitAtomicStore(RValue::get(Value), AtomicLValue, isInit);
2123  return;
2124  }
2125 
2126  llvm::StoreInst *Store = Builder.CreateStore(Value, Addr, Volatile);
2127  if (isNontemporal) {
2128  llvm::MDNode *Node =
2129  llvm::MDNode::get(Store->getContext(),
2130  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(1)));
2131  Store->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_nontemporal, Node);
2132  }
2133 
2134  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Store, TBAAInfo);
2135 }
2136 
2137 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::Value *value, LValue lvalue,
2138  bool isInit) {
2139  if (lvalue.getType()->isConstantMatrixType()) {
2140  EmitStoreOfMatrixScalar(value, lvalue, isInit, *this);
2141  return;
2142  }
2143 
2144  EmitStoreOfScalar(value, lvalue.getAddress(*this), lvalue.isVolatile(),
2145  lvalue.getType(), lvalue.getBaseInfo(),
2146  lvalue.getTBAAInfo(), isInit, lvalue.isNontemporal());
2147 }
2148 
2149 // Emit a load of a LValue of matrix type. This may require casting the pointer
2150 // to memory address (ArrayType) to a pointer to the value type (VectorType).
2151 static RValue EmitLoadOfMatrixLValue(LValue LV, SourceLocation Loc,
2152  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
2153  assert(LV.getType()->isConstantMatrixType());
2154  Address Addr = MaybeConvertMatrixAddress(LV.getAddress(CGF), CGF);
2155  LV.setAddress(Addr);
2156  return RValue::get(CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(LV, Loc));
2157 }
2158 
2159 /// EmitLoadOfLValue - Given an expression that represents a value lvalue, this
2160 /// method emits the address of the lvalue, then loads the result as an rvalue,
2161 /// returning the rvalue.
2162 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfLValue(LValue LV, SourceLocation Loc) {
2163  if (LV.isObjCWeak()) {
2164  // load of a __weak object.
2165  Address AddrWeakObj = LV.getAddress(*this);
2166  return RValue::get(CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCWeakRead(*this,
2167  AddrWeakObj));
2168  }
2169  if (LV.getQuals().getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak) {
2170  // In MRC mode, we do a load+autorelease.
2171  if (!getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount) {
2172  return RValue::get(EmitARCLoadWeak(LV.getAddress(*this)));
2173  }
2174 
2175  // In ARC mode, we load retained and then consume the value.
2176  llvm::Value *Object = EmitARCLoadWeakRetained(LV.getAddress(*this));
2177  Object = EmitObjCConsumeObject(LV.getType(), Object);
2178  return RValue::get(Object);
2179  }
2180 
2181  if (LV.isSimple()) {
2182  assert(!LV.getType()->isFunctionType());
2183 
2184  if (LV.getType()->isConstantMatrixType())
2185  return EmitLoadOfMatrixLValue(LV, Loc, *this);
2186 
2187  // Everything needs a load.
2188  return RValue::get(EmitLoadOfScalar(LV, Loc));
2189  }
2190 
2191  if (LV.isVectorElt()) {
2192  llvm::LoadInst *Load = Builder.CreateLoad(LV.getVectorAddress(),
2193  LV.isVolatileQualified());
2194  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateExtractElement(Load, LV.getVectorIdx(),
2195  "vecext"));
2196  }
2197 
2198  // If this is a reference to a subset of the elements of a vector, either
2199  // shuffle the input or extract/insert them as appropriate.
2200  if (LV.isExtVectorElt()) {
2201  return EmitLoadOfExtVectorElementLValue(LV);
2202  }
2203 
2204  // Global Register variables always invoke intrinsics
2205  if (LV.isGlobalReg())
2206  return EmitLoadOfGlobalRegLValue(LV);
2207 
2208  if (LV.isMatrixElt()) {
2209  llvm::Value *Idx = LV.getMatrixIdx();
2210  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0) {
2211  const auto *const MatTy = LV.getType()->castAs<ConstantMatrixType>();
2212  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
2213  MB.CreateIndexAssumption(Idx, MatTy->getNumElementsFlattened());
2214  }
2215  llvm::LoadInst *Load =
2216  Builder.CreateLoad(LV.getMatrixAddress(), LV.isVolatileQualified());
2217  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateExtractElement(Load, Idx, "matrixext"));
2218  }
2219 
2220  assert(LV.isBitField() && "Unknown LValue type!");
2221  return EmitLoadOfBitfieldLValue(LV, Loc);
2222 }
2223 
2224 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfBitfieldLValue(LValue LV,
2225  SourceLocation Loc) {
2226  const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = LV.getBitFieldInfo();
2227 
2228  // Get the output type.
2229  llvm::Type *ResLTy = ConvertType(LV.getType());
2230 
2231  Address Ptr = LV.getBitFieldAddress();
2232  llvm::Value *Val =
2233  Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr, LV.isVolatileQualified(), "bf.load");
2234 
2235  bool UseVolatile = LV.isVolatileQualified() &&
2236  Info.VolatileStorageSize != 0 && isAAPCS(CGM.getTarget());
2237  const unsigned Offset = UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileOffset : Info.Offset;
2238  const unsigned StorageSize =
2239  UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileStorageSize : Info.StorageSize;
2240  if (Info.IsSigned) {
2241  assert(static_cast<unsigned>(Offset + Info.Size) <= StorageSize);
2242  unsigned HighBits = StorageSize - Offset - Info.Size;
2243  if (HighBits)
2244  Val = Builder.CreateShl(Val, HighBits, "bf.shl");
2245  if (Offset + HighBits)
2246  Val = Builder.CreateAShr(Val, Offset + HighBits, "bf.ashr");
2247  } else {
2248  if (Offset)
2249  Val = Builder.CreateLShr(Val, Offset, "bf.lshr");
2250  if (static_cast<unsigned>(Offset) + Info.Size < StorageSize)
2251  Val = Builder.CreateAnd(
2252  Val, llvm::APInt::getLowBitsSet(StorageSize, Info.Size), "bf.clear");
2253  }
2254  Val = Builder.CreateIntCast(Val, ResLTy, Info.IsSigned, "bf.cast");
2255  EmitScalarRangeCheck(Val, LV.getType(), Loc);
2256  return RValue::get(Val);
2257 }
2258 
2259 // If this is a reference to a subset of the elements of a vector, create an
2260 // appropriate shufflevector.
2261 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfExtVectorElementLValue(LValue LV) {
2262  llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(LV.getExtVectorAddress(),
2263  LV.isVolatileQualified());
2264 
2265  // HLSL allows treating scalars as one-element vectors. Converting the scalar
2266  // IR value to a vector here allows the rest of codegen to behave as normal.
2267  if (getLangOpts().HLSL && !Vec->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
2268  llvm::Type *DstTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(Vec->getType(), 1);
2269  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int64Ty);
2270  Vec = Builder.CreateInsertElement(DstTy, Vec, Zero, "cast.splat");
2271  }
2272 
2273  const llvm::Constant *Elts = LV.getExtVectorElts();
2274 
2275  // If the result of the expression is a non-vector type, we must be extracting
2276  // a single element. Just codegen as an extractelement.
2277  const VectorType *ExprVT = LV.getType()->getAs<VectorType>();
2278  if (!ExprVT) {
2279  unsigned InIdx = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
2280  llvm::Value *Elt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, InIdx);
2281  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateExtractElement(Vec, Elt));
2282  }
2283 
2284  // Always use shuffle vector to try to retain the original program structure
2285  unsigned NumResultElts = ExprVT->getNumElements();
2286 
2287  SmallVector<int, 4> Mask;
2288  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumResultElts; ++i)
2289  Mask.push_back(getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts));
2290 
2291  Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, Mask);
2292  return RValue::get(Vec);
2293 }

2295 /// Generates lvalue for partial ext_vector access.
2296 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitExtVectorElementLValue(LValue LV) {
2297  Address VectorAddress = LV.getExtVectorAddress();
2298  QualType EQT = LV.getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
2299  llvm::Type *VectorElementTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(EQT);
2300 
2301  Address CastToPointerElement = VectorAddress.withElementType(VectorElementTy);
2302 
2303  const llvm::Constant *Elts = LV.getExtVectorElts();
2304  unsigned ix = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
2305 
2306  Address VectorBasePtrPlusIx =
2307  Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP(CastToPointerElement, ix,
2308  "vector.elt");
2309 
2310  return VectorBasePtrPlusIx;
2311 }

2313 /// Load of global gamed gegisters are always calls to intrinsics.
2314 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfGlobalRegLValue(LValue LV) {
2315  assert((LV.getType()->isIntegerType() || LV.getType()->isPointerType()) &&
2316  "Bad type for register variable");
2317  llvm::MDNode *RegName = cast<llvm::MDNode>(
2318  cast<llvm::MetadataAsValue>(LV.getGlobalReg())->getMetadata());
2319 
2320  // We accept integer and pointer types only
2321  llvm::Type *OrigTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(LV.getType());
2322  llvm::Type *Ty = OrigTy;
2323  if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2324  Ty = CGM.getTypes().getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(OrigTy);
2325  llvm::Type *Types[] = { Ty };
2326 
2327  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::read_register, Types);
2328  llvm::Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(
2329  F, llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Ty->getContext(), RegName));
2330  if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2331  Call = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Call, OrigTy);
2332  return RValue::get(Call);
2333 }

2335 /// EmitStoreThroughLValue - Store the specified rvalue into the specified
2336 /// lvalue, where both are guaranteed to the have the same type, and that type
2337 /// is 'Ty'.
2338 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst,
2339  bool isInit) {
2340  if (!Dst.isSimple()) {
2341  if (Dst.isVectorElt()) {
2342  // Read/modify/write the vector, inserting the new element.
2343  llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(Dst.getVectorAddress(),
2344  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2345  auto *IRStoreTy = dyn_cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Vec->getType());
2346  if (IRStoreTy) {
2347  auto *IRVecTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
2348  Builder.getInt1Ty(), IRStoreTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
2349  Vec = Builder.CreateBitCast(Vec, IRVecTy);
2350  // iN --> <N x i1>.
2351  }
2352  Vec = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Vec, Src.getScalarVal(),
2353  Dst.getVectorIdx(), "vecins");
2354  if (IRStoreTy) {
2355  // <N x i1> --> <iN>.
2356  Vec = Builder.CreateBitCast(Vec, IRStoreTy);
2357  }
2358  Builder.CreateStore(Vec, Dst.getVectorAddress(),
2359  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2360  return;
2361  }
2362 
2363  // If this is an update of extended vector elements, insert them as
2364  // appropriate.
2365  if (Dst.isExtVectorElt())
2366  return EmitStoreThroughExtVectorComponentLValue(Src, Dst);
2367 
2368  if (Dst.isGlobalReg())
2369  return EmitStoreThroughGlobalRegLValue(Src, Dst);
2370 
2371  if (Dst.isMatrixElt()) {
2372  llvm::Value *Idx = Dst.getMatrixIdx();
2373  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0) {
2374  const auto *const MatTy = Dst.getType()->castAs<ConstantMatrixType>();
2375  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
2376  MB.CreateIndexAssumption(Idx, MatTy->getNumElementsFlattened());
2377  }
2378  llvm::Instruction *Load = Builder.CreateLoad(Dst.getMatrixAddress());
2379  llvm::Value *Vec =
2380  Builder.CreateInsertElement(Load, Src.getScalarVal(), Idx, "matins");
2381  Builder.CreateStore(Vec, Dst.getMatrixAddress(),
2382  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2383  return;
2384  }
2385 
2386  assert(Dst.isBitField() && "Unknown LValue type");
2387  return EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(Src, Dst);
2388  }
2389 
2390  // There's special magic for assigning into an ARC-qualified l-value.
2391  if (Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime = Dst.getQuals().getObjCLifetime()) {
2392  switch (Lifetime) {
2393  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
2394  llvm_unreachable("present but none");
2395 
2396  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
2397  // nothing special
2398  break;
2399 
2400  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
2401  if (isInit) {
2402  Src = RValue::get(EmitARCRetain(Dst.getType(), Src.getScalarVal()));
2403  break;
2404  }
2405  EmitARCStoreStrong(Dst, Src.getScalarVal(), /*ignore*/ true);
2406  return;
2407 
2408  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
2409  if (isInit)
2410  // Initialize and then skip the primitive store.
2411  EmitARCInitWeak(Dst.getAddress(*this), Src.getScalarVal());
2412  else
2413  EmitARCStoreWeak(Dst.getAddress(*this), Src.getScalarVal(),
2414  /*ignore*/ true);
2415  return;
2416 
2417  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
2418  Src = RValue::get(EmitObjCExtendObjectLifetime(Dst.getType(),
2419  Src.getScalarVal()));
2420  // fall into the normal path
2421  break;
2422  }
2423  }
2424 
2425  if (Dst.isObjCWeak() && !Dst.isNonGC()) {
2426  // load of a __weak object.
2427  Address LvalueDst = Dst.getAddress(*this);
2428  llvm::Value *src = Src.getScalarVal();
2429  CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCWeakAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst);
2430  return;
2431  }
2432 
2433  if (Dst.isObjCStrong() && !Dst.isNonGC()) {
2434  // load of a __strong object.
2435  Address LvalueDst = Dst.getAddress(*this);
2436  llvm::Value *src = Src.getScalarVal();
2437  if (Dst.isObjCIvar()) {
2438  assert(Dst.getBaseIvarExp() && "BaseIvarExp is NULL");
2439  llvm::Type *ResultType = IntPtrTy;
2440  Address dst = EmitPointerWithAlignment(Dst.getBaseIvarExp());
2441  llvm::Value *RHS = dst.emitRawPointer(*this);
2442  RHS = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(RHS, ResultType, "sub.ptr.rhs.cast");
2443  llvm::Value *LHS = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(LvalueDst.emitRawPointer(*this),
2444  ResultType, "sub.ptr.lhs.cast");
2445  llvm::Value *BytesBetween = Builder.CreateSub(LHS, RHS, "ivar.offset");
2446  CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCIvarAssign(*this, src, dst, BytesBetween);
2447  } else if (Dst.isGlobalObjCRef()) {
2448  CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCGlobalAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst,
2449  Dst.isThreadLocalRef());
2450  }
2451  else
2452  CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCStrongCastAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst);
2453  return;
2454  }
2455 
2456  assert(Src.isScalar() && "Can't emit an agg store with this method");
2457  EmitStoreOfScalar(Src.getScalarVal(), Dst, isInit);
2458 }
2459 
2460 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst,
2461  llvm::Value **Result) {
2462  const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = Dst.getBitFieldInfo();
2463  llvm::Type *ResLTy = ConvertTypeForMem(Dst.getType());
2464  Address Ptr = Dst.getBitFieldAddress();
2465 
2466  // Get the source value, truncated to the width of the bit-field.
2467  llvm::Value *SrcVal = Src.getScalarVal();
2468 
2469  // Cast the source to the storage type and shift it into place.
2470  SrcVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(SrcVal, Ptr.getElementType(),
2471  /*isSigned=*/false);
2472  llvm::Value *MaskedVal = SrcVal;
2473 
2474  const bool UseVolatile =
2475  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().AAPCSBitfieldWidth && Dst.isVolatileQualified() &&
2476  Info.VolatileStorageSize != 0 && isAAPCS(CGM.getTarget());
2477  const unsigned StorageSize =
2478  UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileStorageSize : Info.StorageSize;
2479  const unsigned Offset = UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileOffset : Info.Offset;
2480  // See if there are other bits in the bitfield's storage we'll need to load
2481  // and mask together with source before storing.
2482  if (StorageSize != Info.Size) {
2483  assert(StorageSize > Info.Size && "Invalid bitfield size.");
2484  llvm::Value *Val =
2485  Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr, Dst.isVolatileQualified(), "bf.load");
2486 
2487  // Mask the source value as needed.
2488  if (!hasBooleanRepresentation(Dst.getType()))
2489  SrcVal = Builder.CreateAnd(
2490  SrcVal, llvm::APInt::getLowBitsSet(StorageSize, Info.Size),
2491  "bf.value");
2492  MaskedVal = SrcVal;
2493  if (Offset)
2494  SrcVal = Builder.CreateShl(SrcVal, Offset, "bf.shl");
2495 
2496  // Mask out the original value.
2497  Val = Builder.CreateAnd(
2498  Val, ~llvm::APInt::getBitsSet(StorageSize, Offset, Offset + Info.Size),
2499  "bf.clear");
2500 
2501  // Or together the unchanged values and the source value.
2502  SrcVal = Builder.CreateOr(Val, SrcVal, "bf.set");
2503  } else {
2504  assert(Offset == 0);
2505  // According to the AACPS:
2506  // When a volatile bit-field is written, and its container does not overlap
2507  // with any non-bit-field member, its container must be read exactly once
2508  // and written exactly once using the access width appropriate to the type
2509  // of the container. The two accesses are not atomic.
2510  if (Dst.isVolatileQualified() && isAAPCS(CGM.getTarget()) &&
2511  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().ForceAAPCSBitfieldLoad)
2512  Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr, true, "bf.load");
2513  }
2514 
2515  // Write the new value back out.
2516  Builder.CreateStore(SrcVal, Ptr, Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2517 
2518  // Return the new value of the bit-field, if requested.
2519  if (Result) {
2520  llvm::Value *ResultVal = MaskedVal;
2521 
2522  // Sign extend the value if needed.
2523  if (Info.IsSigned) {
2524  assert(Info.Size <= StorageSize);
2525  unsigned HighBits = StorageSize - Info.Size;
2526  if (HighBits) {
2527  ResultVal = Builder.CreateShl(ResultVal, HighBits, "bf.result.shl");
2528  ResultVal = Builder.CreateAShr(ResultVal, HighBits, "bf.result.ashr");
2529  }
2530  }
2531 
2532  ResultVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(ResultVal, ResLTy, Info.IsSigned,
2533  "bf.result.cast");
2534  *Result = EmitFromMemory(ResultVal, Dst.getType());
2535  }
2536 }
2537 
2538 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughExtVectorComponentLValue(RValue Src,
2539  LValue Dst) {
2540  // HLSL allows storing to scalar values through ExtVector component LValues.
2541  // To support this we need to handle the case where the destination address is
2542  // a scalar.
2543  Address DstAddr = Dst.getExtVectorAddress();
2544  if (!DstAddr.getElementType()->isVectorTy()) {
2545  assert(!Dst.getType()->isVectorType() &&
2546  "this should only occur for non-vector l-values");
2547  Builder.CreateStore(Src.getScalarVal(), DstAddr, Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2548  return;
2549  }
2550 
2551  // This access turns into a read/modify/write of the vector. Load the input
2552  // value now.
2553  llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(DstAddr, Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2554  const llvm::Constant *Elts = Dst.getExtVectorElts();
2555 
2556  llvm::Value *SrcVal = Src.getScalarVal();
2557 
2558  if (const VectorType *VTy = Dst.getType()->getAs<VectorType>()) {
2559  unsigned NumSrcElts = VTy->getNumElements();
2560  unsigned NumDstElts =
2561  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType())->getNumElements();
2562  if (NumDstElts == NumSrcElts) {
2563  // Use shuffle vector is the src and destination are the same number of
2564  // elements and restore the vector mask since it is on the side it will be
2565  // stored.
2566  SmallVector<int, 4> Mask(NumDstElts);
2567  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
2568  Mask[getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts)] = i;
2569 
2570  Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(SrcVal, Mask);
2571  } else if (NumDstElts > NumSrcElts) {
2572  // Extended the source vector to the same length and then shuffle it
2573  // into the destination.
2574  // FIXME: since we're shuffling with undef, can we just use the indices
2575  // into that? This could be simpler.
2576  SmallVector<int, 4> ExtMask;
2577  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
2578  ExtMask.push_back(i);
2579  ExtMask.resize(NumDstElts, -1);
2580  llvm::Value *ExtSrcVal = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(SrcVal, ExtMask);
2581  // build identity
2582  SmallVector<int, 4> Mask;
2583  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumDstElts; ++i)
2584  Mask.push_back(i);
2585 
2586  // When the vector size is odd and .odd or .hi is used, the last element
2587  // of the Elts constant array will be one past the size of the vector.
2588  // Ignore the last element here, if it is greater than the mask size.
2589  if (getAccessedFieldNo(NumSrcElts - 1, Elts) == Mask.size())
2590  NumSrcElts--;
2591 
2592  // modify when what gets shuffled in
2593  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
2594  Mask[getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts)] = i + NumDstElts;
2595  Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, ExtSrcVal, Mask);
2596  } else {
2597  // We should never shorten the vector
2598  llvm_unreachable("unexpected shorten vector length");
2599  }
2600  } else {
2601  // If the Src is a scalar (not a vector), and the target is a vector it must
2602  // be updating one element.
2603  unsigned InIdx = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
2604  llvm::Value *Elt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, InIdx);
2605  Vec = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Vec, SrcVal, Elt);
2606  }
2607 
2608  Builder.CreateStore(Vec, Dst.getExtVectorAddress(),
2609  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2610 }
2611 
2612 /// Store of global named registers are always calls to intrinsics.
2613 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughGlobalRegLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst) {
2614  assert((Dst.getType()->isIntegerType() || Dst.getType()->isPointerType()) &&
2615  "Bad type for register variable");
2616  llvm::MDNode *RegName = cast<llvm::MDNode>(
2617  cast<llvm::MetadataAsValue>(Dst.getGlobalReg())->getMetadata());
2618  assert(RegName && "Register LValue is not metadata");
2619 
2620  // We accept integer and pointer types only
2621  llvm::Type *OrigTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(Dst.getType());
2622  llvm::Type *Ty = OrigTy;
2623  if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2624  Ty = CGM.getTypes().getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(OrigTy);
2625  llvm::Type *Types[] = { Ty };
2626 
2627  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::write_register, Types);
2628  llvm::Value *Value = Src.getScalarVal();
2629  if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2630  Value = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Value, Ty);
2631  Builder.CreateCall(
2632  F, {llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Ty->getContext(), RegName), Value});
2633 }
2634 
2635 // setObjCGCLValueClass - sets class of the lvalue for the purpose of
2636 // generating write-barries API. It is currently a global, ivar,
2637 // or neither.
2638 static void setObjCGCLValueClass(const ASTContext &Ctx, const Expr *E,
2639  LValue &LV,
2640  bool IsMemberAccess=false) {
2641  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC)
2642  return;
2643 
2644  if (isa<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E)) {
2645  QualType ExpTy = E->getType();
2646  if (IsMemberAccess && ExpTy->isPointerType()) {
2647  // If ivar is a structure pointer, assigning to field of
2648  // this struct follows gcc's behavior and makes it a non-ivar
2649  // writer-barrier conservatively.
2650  ExpTy = ExpTy->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
2651  if (ExpTy->isRecordType()) {
2652  LV.setObjCIvar(false);
2653  return;
2654  }
2655  }
2656  LV.setObjCIvar(true);
2657  auto *Exp = cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
2658  LV.setBaseIvarExp(Exp->getBase());
2659  LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
2660  return;
2661  }
2662 
2663  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
2664  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Exp->getDecl())) {
2665  if (VD->hasGlobalStorage()) {
2666  LV.setGlobalObjCRef(true);
2667  LV.setThreadLocalRef(VD->getTLSKind() != VarDecl::TLS_None);
2668  }
2669  }
2670  LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
2671  return;
2672  }
2673 
2674  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
2675  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2676  return;
2677  }
2678 
2679  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
2680  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2681  if (LV.isObjCIvar()) {
2682  // If cast is to a structure pointer, follow gcc's behavior and make it
2683  // a non-ivar write-barrier.
2684  QualType ExpTy = E->getType();
2685  if (ExpTy->isPointerType())
2686  ExpTy = ExpTy->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
2687  if (ExpTy->isRecordType())
2688  LV.setObjCIvar(false);
2689  }
2690  return;
2691  }
2692 
2693  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)) {
2694  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getResultExpr(), LV);
2695  return;
2696  }
2697 
2698  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
2699  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2700  return;
2701  }
2702 
2703  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<CStyleCastExpr>(E)) {
2704  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2705  return;
2706  }
2707 
2708  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ObjCBridgedCastExpr>(E)) {
2709  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2710  return;
2711  }
2712 
2713  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E)) {
2714  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getBase(), LV);
2715  if (LV.isObjCIvar() && !LV.isObjCArray())
2716  // Using array syntax to assigning to what an ivar points to is not
2717  // same as assigning to the ivar itself. {id *Names;} Names[i] = 0;
2718  LV.setObjCIvar(false);
2719  else if (LV.isGlobalObjCRef() && !LV.isObjCArray())
2720  // Using array syntax to assigning to what global points to is not
2721  // same as assigning to the global itself. {id *G;} G[i] = 0;
2722  LV.setGlobalObjCRef(false);
2723  return;
2724  }
2725 
2726  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
2727  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getBase(), LV, true);
2728  // We don't know if member is an 'ivar', but this flag is looked at
2729  // only in the context of LV.isObjCIvar().
2730  LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
2731  return;
2732  }
2733 }
2734 
2735 static LValue EmitThreadPrivateVarDeclLValue(
2736  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const VarDecl *VD, QualType T, Address Addr,
2737  llvm::Type *RealVarTy, SourceLocation Loc) {
2738  if (CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIRBuilder)
2739  Addr = CodeGenFunction::OMPBuilderCBHelpers::getAddrOfThreadPrivate(
2740  CGF, VD, Addr, Loc);
2741  else
2742  Addr =
2743  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfThreadPrivate(CGF, VD, Addr, Loc);
2744 
2745  Addr = Addr.withElementType(RealVarTy);
2746  return CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2747 }
2748 
2749 static Address emitDeclTargetVarDeclLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2750  const VarDecl *VD, QualType T) {
2751  std::optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MapTypeTy> Res =
2752  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD);
2753  // Return an invalid address if variable is MT_To (or MT_Enter starting with
2754  // OpenMP 5.2) and unified memory is not enabled. For all other cases: MT_Link
2755  // and MT_To (or MT_Enter) with unified memory, return a valid address.
2756  if (!Res || ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To ||
2757  *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Enter) &&
2758  !CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory()))
2759  return Address::invalid();
2760  assert(((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link) ||
2761  ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To ||
2762  *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Enter) &&
2763  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory())) &&
2764  "Expected link clause OR to clause with unified memory enabled.");
2765  QualType PtrTy = CGF.getContext().getPointerType(VD->getType());
2766  Address Addr = CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfDeclareTargetVar(VD);
2767  return CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(Addr, PtrTy->castAs<PointerType>());
2768 }
2769 
2770 Address
2771 CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfReference(LValue RefLVal,
2772  LValueBaseInfo *PointeeBaseInfo,
2773  TBAAAccessInfo *PointeeTBAAInfo) {
2774  llvm::LoadInst *Load =
2775  Builder.CreateLoad(RefLVal.getAddress(*this), RefLVal.isVolatile());
2776  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Load, RefLVal.getTBAAInfo());
2777  return makeNaturalAddressForPointer(Load, RefLVal.getType()->getPointeeType(),
2778  CharUnits(), /*ForPointeeType=*/true,
2779  PointeeBaseInfo, PointeeTBAAInfo);
2780 }

2782 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(LValue RefLVal) {
2783  LValueBaseInfo PointeeBaseInfo;
2784  TBAAAccessInfo PointeeTBAAInfo;
2785  Address PointeeAddr = EmitLoadOfReference(RefLVal, &PointeeBaseInfo,
2786  &PointeeTBAAInfo);
2787  return MakeAddrLValue(PointeeAddr, RefLVal.getType()->getPointeeType(),
2788  PointeeBaseInfo, PointeeTBAAInfo);
2789 }

2791 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfPointer(Address Ptr,
2792  const PointerType *PtrTy,
2793  LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
2794  TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
2795  llvm::Value *Addr = Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr);
2796  return makeNaturalAddressForPointer(Addr, PtrTy->getPointeeType(),
2797  CharUnits(), /*ForPointeeType=*/true,
2798  BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
2799 }

2801 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfPointerLValue(Address PtrAddr,
2802  const PointerType *PtrTy) {
2803  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
2804  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
2805  Address Addr = EmitLoadOfPointer(PtrAddr, PtrTy, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);

2809 static LValue EmitGlobalVarDeclLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2810  const Expr *E, const VarDecl *VD) {
2811  QualType T = E->getType();
2812 
2813  // If it's thread_local, emit a call to its wrapper function instead.
2814  if (VD->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic &&
2815  CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().usesThreadWrapperFunction(VD))
2816  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitThreadLocalVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T);
2817  // Check if the variable is marked as declare target with link clause in
2818  // device codegen.
2819  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice) {
2820  Address Addr = emitDeclTargetVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T);
2821  if (Addr.isValid())
2822  return CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2823  }
2824 
2825  llvm::Value *V = CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
2826 
2827  if (VD->getTLSKind() != VarDecl::TLS_None)
2828  V = CGF.Builder.CreateThreadLocalAddress(V);
2829 
2830  llvm::Type *RealVarTy = CGF.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType());
2831  CharUnits Alignment = CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
2832  Address Addr(V, RealVarTy, Alignment);
2833  // Emit reference to the private copy of the variable if it is an OpenMP
2834  // threadprivate variable.
2835  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP && !CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd &&
2836  VD->hasAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()) {
2837  return EmitThreadPrivateVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T, Addr, RealVarTy,
2838  E->getExprLoc());
2839  }
2840  LValue LV = VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ?
2841  CGF.EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(Addr, VD->getType(),
2842  AlignmentSource::Decl) :
2843  CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2844  setObjCGCLValueClass(CGF.getContext(), E, LV);
2845  return LV;
2846 }

2848 static llvm::Constant *EmitFunctionDeclPointer(CodeGenModule &CGM,
2849  GlobalDecl GD) {
2850  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2851  if (FD->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>()) {
2852  ConstantAddress aliasee = CGM.GetWeakRefReference(FD);
2853  return aliasee.getPointer();
2854  }
2855 
2856  llvm::Constant *V = CGM.GetAddrOfFunction(GD);
2857  return V;
2858 }

2860 static LValue EmitFunctionDeclLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E,
2861  GlobalDecl GD) {
2862  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2863  llvm::Value *V = EmitFunctionDeclPointer(CGF.CGM, GD);
2864  CharUnits Alignment = CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(FD);
2865  return CGF.MakeAddrLValue(V, E->getType(), Alignment,
2866  AlignmentSource::Decl);
2867 }

2869 static LValue EmitCapturedFieldLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const FieldDecl *FD,
