2875 /// Named Registers are named metadata pointing to the register name
2876 /// which will be read from/written to as an argument to the intrinsic
2877 /// @llvm.read/write_register.
2878 /// So far, only the name is being passed down, but other options such as
2879 /// register type, allocation type or even optimization options could be
2880 /// passed down via the metadata node.
2881 static LValue EmitGlobalNamedRegister(const VarDecl *VD, CodeGenModule &CGM) {
2882  SmallString<64> Name("llvm.named.register.");
2883  AsmLabelAttr *Asm = VD->getAttr<AsmLabelAttr>();
2884  assert(Asm->getLabel().size() < 64-Name.size() &&
2885  "Register name too big");
2886  Name.append(Asm->getLabel());
2887  llvm::NamedMDNode *M =
2888  CGM.getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata(Name);
2889  if (M->getNumOperands() == 0) {
2890  llvm::MDString *Str = llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
2891  Asm->getLabel());
2892  llvm::Metadata *Ops[] = {Str};
2893  M->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Ops));
2894  }
2895 
2896  CharUnits Alignment = CGM.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
2897 
2898  llvm::Value *Ptr =
2899  llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), M->getOperand(0));
2900  return LValue::MakeGlobalReg(Ptr, Alignment, VD->getType());
2901 }
2902 
2903 /// Determine whether we can emit a reference to \p VD from the current
2904 /// context, despite not necessarily having seen an odr-use of the variable in
2905 /// this context.
2906 static bool canEmitSpuriousReferenceToVariable(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2907  const DeclRefExpr *E,
2908  const VarDecl *VD) {
2909  // For a variable declared in an enclosing scope, do not emit a spurious
2910  // reference even if we have a capture, as that will emit an unwarranted
2911  // reference to our capture state, and will likely generate worse code than
2912  // emitting a local copy.
2913  if (E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture())
2914  return false;
2915 
2916  // For a local declaration declared in this function, we can always reference
2917  // it even if we don't have an odr-use.
2918  if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
2919  return VD->getDeclContext() ==
2920  dyn_cast_or_null<DeclContext>(CGF.CurCodeDecl);
2921  }
2922 
2923  // For a global declaration, we can emit a reference to it if we know
2924  // for sure that we are able to emit a definition of it.
2925  VD = VD->getDefinition(CGF.getContext());
2926  if (!VD)
2927  return false;
2928 
2929  // Don't emit a spurious reference if it might be to a variable that only
2930  // exists on a different device / target.
2931  // FIXME: This is unnecessarily broad. Check whether this would actually be a
2932  // cross-target reference.
2933  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP || CGF.getLangOpts().CUDA ||
2934  CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
2935  return false;
2936  }
2937 
2938  // We can emit a spurious reference only if the linkage implies that we'll
2939  // be emitting a non-interposable symbol that will be retained until link
2940  // time.
2941  switch (CGF.CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD)) {
2942  case llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage:
2943  case llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage:
2944  case llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage:
2945  case llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage:
2946  case llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage:
2947  return true;
2948  default:
2949  return false;
2950  }
2951 }
2952 
2953 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitDeclRefLValue(const DeclRefExpr *E) {
2954  const NamedDecl *ND = E->getDecl();
2955  QualType T = E->getType();
2956 
2957  assert(E->isNonOdrUse() != NOUR_Unevaluated &&
2958  "should not emit an unevaluated operand");
2959 
2960  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ND)) {
2961  // Global Named registers access via intrinsics only
2962  if (VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Register &&
2963  VD->hasAttr<AsmLabelAttr>() && !VD->isLocalVarDecl())
2964  return EmitGlobalNamedRegister(VD, CGM);
2965 
2966  // If this DeclRefExpr does not constitute an odr-use of the variable,
2967  // we're not permitted to emit a reference to it in general, and it might
2968  // not be captured if capture would be necessary for a use. Emit the
2969  // constant value directly instead.
2970  if (E->isNonOdrUse() == NOUR_Constant &&
2971  (VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ||
2972  !canEmitSpuriousReferenceToVariable(*this, E, VD))) {
2973  VD->getAnyInitializer(VD);
2974  llvm::Constant *Val = ConstantEmitter(*this).emitAbstract(
2975  E->getLocation(), *VD->evaluateValue(), VD->getType());
2976  assert(Val && "failed to emit constant expression");
2977 
2978  Address Addr = Address::invalid();
2979  if (!VD->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
2980  // Spill the constant value to a global.
2981  Addr = CGM.createUnnamedGlobalFrom(*VD, Val,
2982  getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
2983  llvm::Type *VarTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType());
2984  auto *PTy = llvm::PointerType::get(
2985  VarTy, getTypes().getTargetAddressSpace(VD->getType()));
2986  Addr = Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Addr, PTy, VarTy);
2987  } else {
2988  // Should we be using the alignment of the constant pointer we emitted?
2989  CharUnits Alignment =
2990  CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(E->getType(),
2991  /* BaseInfo= */ nullptr,
2992  /* TBAAInfo= */ nullptr,
2993  /* forPointeeType= */ true);
2994  Addr = makeNaturalAddressForPointer(Val, T, Alignment);
2995  }
2996  return MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2997  }
2998 
2999  // FIXME: Handle other kinds of non-odr-use DeclRefExprs.
3000 
3001  // Check for captured variables.
3002  if (E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture()) {
3003  VD = VD->getCanonicalDecl();
3004  if (auto *FD = LambdaCaptureFields.lookup(VD))
3005  return EmitCapturedFieldLValue(*this, FD, CXXABIThisValue);
3006  if (CapturedStmtInfo) {
3007  auto I = LocalDeclMap.find(VD);
3008  if (I != LocalDeclMap.end()) {
3009  LValue CapLVal;
3010  if (VD->getType()->isReferenceType())
3011  CapLVal = EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(I->second, VD->getType(),
3012  AlignmentSource::Decl);
3013  else
3014  CapLVal = MakeAddrLValue(I->second, T);
3015  // Mark lvalue as nontemporal if the variable is marked as nontemporal
3016  // in simd context.
3017  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP &&
3018  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().isNontemporalDecl(VD))
3019  CapLVal.setNontemporal(/*Value=*/true);
3020  return CapLVal;
3021  }
3022  LValue CapLVal =
3023  EmitCapturedFieldLValue(*this, CapturedStmtInfo->lookup(VD),
3024  CapturedStmtInfo->getContextValue());
3025  Address LValueAddress = CapLVal.getAddress(*this);
3026  CapLVal = MakeAddrLValue(Address(LValueAddress.emitRawPointer(*this),
3027  LValueAddress.getElementType(),
3028  getContext().getDeclAlign(VD)),
3029  CapLVal.getType(),
3030  LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::Decl),
3031  CapLVal.getTBAAInfo());
3032  // Mark lvalue as nontemporal if the variable is marked as nontemporal
3033  // in simd context.
3034  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP &&
3035  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().isNontemporalDecl(VD))
3036  CapLVal.setNontemporal(/*Value=*/true);
3037  return CapLVal;
3038  }
3039 
3040  assert(isa<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl));
3041  Address addr = GetAddrOfBlockDecl(VD);
3042  return MakeAddrLValue(addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3043  }
3044  }
3045 
3046  // FIXME: We should be able to assert this for FunctionDecls as well!
3047  // FIXME: We should be able to assert this for all DeclRefExprs, not just
3048  // those with a valid source location.
3049  assert((ND->isUsed(false) || !isa<VarDecl>(ND) || E->isNonOdrUse() ||
3050  !E->getLocation().isValid()) &&
3051  "Should not use decl without marking it used!");
3052 
3053  if (ND->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>()) {
3054  const auto *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(ND);
3055  ConstantAddress Aliasee = CGM.GetWeakRefReference(VD);
3056  return MakeAddrLValue(Aliasee, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3057  }
3058 
3059  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ND)) {
3060  // Check if this is a global variable.
3061  if (VD->hasLinkage() || VD->isStaticDataMember())
3062  return EmitGlobalVarDeclLValue(*this, E, VD);
3063 
3064  Address addr = Address::invalid();
3065 
3066  // The variable should generally be present in the local decl map.
3067  auto iter = LocalDeclMap.find(VD);
3068  if (iter != LocalDeclMap.end()) {
3069  addr = iter->second;
3070 
3071  // Otherwise, it might be static local we haven't emitted yet for
3072  // some reason; most likely, because it's in an outer function.
3073  } else if (VD->isStaticLocal()) {
3074  llvm::Constant *var = CGM.getOrCreateStaticVarDecl(
3075  *VD, CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD));
3076 
3077  // Force completion of static variable for SYCL since if it wasn't emitted
3078  // already that means it is defined in host code and its parent function
3079  // won't be emitted.
3080  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
3081  EmitStaticVarDecl(
3082  *VD, CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD));
3083 
3084  addr = Address(
3085  var, ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType()), getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
3086 
3087  // No other cases for now.
3088  } else {
3089  llvm_unreachable("DeclRefExpr for Decl not entered in LocalDeclMap?");
3090  }
3091 
3092  // Handle threadlocal function locals.
3093  if (VD->getTLSKind() != VarDecl::TLS_None)
3094  addr = addr.withPointer(
3095  Builder.CreateThreadLocalAddress(addr.getBasePointer()),
3096  NotKnownNonNull);
3097 
3098  // Check for OpenMP threadprivate variables.
3099  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && !getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd &&
3100  VD->hasAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()) {
3101  return EmitThreadPrivateVarDeclLValue(
3102  *this, VD, T, addr, getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType()),
3103  E->getExprLoc());
3104  }
3105 
3106  // Drill into block byref variables.
3107  bool isBlockByref = VD->isEscapingByref();
3108  if (isBlockByref) {
3109  addr = emitBlockByrefAddress(addr, VD);
3110  }
3111 
3112  // Drill into reference types.
3113  LValue LV = VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ?
3114  EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(addr, VD->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl) :
3115  MakeAddrLValue(addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3116 
3117  bool isLocalStorage = VD->hasLocalStorage();
3118 
3119  bool NonGCable = isLocalStorage &&
3120  !VD->getType()->isReferenceType() &&
3121  !isBlockByref;
3122  if (NonGCable) {
3123  LV.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
3124  LV.setNonGC(true);
3125  }
3126 
3127  bool isImpreciseLifetime =
3128  (isLocalStorage && !VD->hasAttr<ObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr>());
3129  if (isImpreciseLifetime)
3130  LV.setARCPreciseLifetime(ARCImpreciseLifetime);
3131  setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
3132  return LV;
3133  }
3134 
3135  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND)) {
3136  LValue LV = EmitFunctionDeclLValue(*this, E, FD);
3137 
3138  // Emit debuginfo for the function declaration if the target wants to.
3139  if (getContext().getTargetInfo().allowDebugInfoForExternalRef()) {
3140  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = CGM.getModuleDebugInfo()) {
3141  auto *Fn =
3142  cast<llvm::Function>(LV.getPointer(*this)->stripPointerCasts());
3143  if (!Fn->getSubprogram())
3144  DI->EmitFunctionDecl(FD, FD->getLocation(), T, Fn);
3145  }
3146  }
3147 
3148  return LV;
3149  }
3150 
3151  // FIXME: While we're emitting a binding from an enclosing scope, all other
3152  // DeclRefExprs we see should be implicitly treated as if they also refer to
3153  // an enclosing scope.
3154  if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BindingDecl>(ND)) {
3155  if (E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture()) {
3156  auto *FD = LambdaCaptureFields.lookup(BD);
3157  return EmitCapturedFieldLValue(*this, FD, CXXABIThisValue);
3158  }
3159  return EmitLValue(BD->getBinding());
3160  }
3161 
3162  // We can form DeclRefExprs naming GUID declarations when reconstituting
3163  // non-type template parameters into expressions.
3164  if (const auto *GD = dyn_cast<MSGuidDecl>(ND))
3165  return MakeAddrLValue(CGM.GetAddrOfMSGuidDecl(GD), T,
3166  AlignmentSource::Decl);
3167 
3168  if (const auto *TPO = dyn_cast<TemplateParamObjectDecl>(ND)) {
3169  auto ATPO = CGM.GetAddrOfTemplateParamObject(TPO);
3170  auto AS = getLangASFromTargetAS(ATPO.getAddressSpace());
3171 
3172  if (AS != T.getAddressSpace()) {
3173  auto TargetAS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(T.getAddressSpace());
3174  auto PtrTy = ATPO.getElementType()->getPointerTo(TargetAS);
3175  auto ASC = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
3176  CGM, ATPO.getPointer(), AS, T.getAddressSpace(), PtrTy);
3177  ATPO = ConstantAddress(ASC, ATPO.getElementType(), ATPO.getAlignment());
3178  }
3179 
3180  return MakeAddrLValue(ATPO, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
3181  }
3182 
3183  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled DeclRefExpr");
3184 }
3185 
3186 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitUnaryOpLValue(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3187  // __extension__ doesn't affect lvalue-ness.
3188  if (E->getOpcode() == UO_Extension)
3189  return EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
3190 
3191  QualType ExprTy = getContext().getCanonicalType(E->getSubExpr()->getType());
3192  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
3193  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown unary operator lvalue!");
3194  case UO_Deref: {
3195  QualType T = E->getSubExpr()->getType()->getPointeeType();
3196  assert(!T.isNull() && "CodeGenFunction::EmitUnaryOpLValue: Illegal type");
3197 
3198  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
3199  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
3200  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getSubExpr(), &BaseInfo,
3201  &TBAAInfo);
3202  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
3203  LV.getQuals().setAddressSpace(ExprTy.getAddressSpace());
3204 
3205  // We should not generate __weak write barrier on indirect reference
3206  // of a pointer to object; as in void foo (__weak id *param); *param = 0;
3207  // But, we continue to generate __strong write barrier on indirect write
3208  // into a pointer to object.
3209  if (getLangOpts().ObjC &&
3210  getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC &&
3211  LV.isObjCWeak())
3212  LV.setNonGC(!E->isOBJCGCCandidate(getContext()));
3213  return LV;
3214  }
3215  case UO_Real:
3216  case UO_Imag: {
3217  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
3218  assert(LV.isSimple() && "real/imag on non-ordinary l-value");
3219 
3220  // __real is valid on scalars. This is a faster way of testing that.
3221  // __imag can only produce an rvalue on scalars.
3222  if (E->getOpcode() == UO_Real &&
3223  !LV.getAddress(*this).getElementType()->isStructTy()) {
3224  assert(E->getSubExpr()->getType()->isArithmeticType());
3225  return LV;
3226  }
3227 
3228  QualType T = ExprTy->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
3229 
3230  Address Component =
3231  (E->getOpcode() == UO_Real
3232  ? emitAddrOfRealComponent(LV.getAddress(*this), LV.getType())
3233  : emitAddrOfImagComponent(LV.getAddress(*this), LV.getType()));
3234  LValue ElemLV = MakeAddrLValue(Component, T, LV.getBaseInfo(),
3235  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, T));
3236  ElemLV.getQuals().addQualifiers(LV.getQuals());
3237  return ElemLV;
3238  }
3239  case UO_PreInc:
3240  case UO_PreDec: {
3241  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
3242  bool isInc = E->getOpcode() == UO_PreInc;
3243 
3244  if (E->getType()->isAnyComplexType())
3245  EmitComplexPrePostIncDec(E, LV, isInc, true/*isPre*/);
3246  else
3247  EmitScalarPrePostIncDec(E, LV, isInc, true/*isPre*/);
3248  return LV;
3249  }
3250  }
3251 }
3252 
3253 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitStringLiteralLValue(const StringLiteral *E) {
3254  return MakeAddrLValue(CGM.GetAddrOfConstantStringFromLiteral(E),
3255  E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3256 }

3258 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCEncodeExprLValue(const ObjCEncodeExpr *E) {
3259  return MakeAddrLValue(CGM.GetAddrOfConstantStringFromObjCEncode(E),
3260  E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3261 }
3262 
3263 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPredefinedLValue(const PredefinedExpr *E) {
3264  auto SL = E->getFunctionName();
3265  assert(SL != nullptr && "No StringLiteral name in PredefinedExpr");
3266  StringRef FnName = CurFn->getName();
3267  if (FnName.starts_with("\01"))
3268  FnName = FnName.substr(1);
3269  StringRef NameItems[] = {
3270  PredefinedExpr::getIdentKindName(E->getIdentKind()), FnName};
3271  std::string GVName = llvm::join(NameItems, NameItems + 2, ".");
3272  if (auto *BD = dyn_cast_or_null<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl)) {
3273  std::string Name = std::string(SL->getString());
3274  if (!Name.empty()) {
3275  unsigned Discriminator =
3276  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().getBlockId(BD, true);
3277  if (Discriminator)
3278  Name += "_" + Twine(Discriminator + 1).str();
3279  auto C = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(Name, GVName.c_str());
3280  return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3281  } else {
3282  auto C =
3283  CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(std::string(FnName), GVName.c_str());
3284  return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3285  }
3286  }
3287  auto C = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantStringFromLiteral(SL, GVName);
3288  return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3289 }
3290 
3291 /// Emit a type description suitable for use by a runtime sanitizer library. The
3292 /// format of a type descriptor is
3293 ///
3294 /// \code
3295 /// { i16 TypeKind, i16 TypeInfo }
3296 /// \endcode
3297 ///
3298 /// followed by an array of i8 containing the type name. TypeKind is 0 for an
3299 /// integer, 1 for a floating point value, and -1 for anything else.
3300 llvm::Constant *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType T) {
3301  // Only emit each type's descriptor once.
3302  if (llvm::Constant *C = CGM.getTypeDescriptorFromMap(T))
3303  return C;
3304 
3305  uint16_t TypeKind = -1;
3306  uint16_t TypeInfo = 0;
3307 
3308  if (T->isIntegerType()) {
3309  TypeKind = 0;
3310  TypeInfo = (llvm::Log2_32(getContext().getTypeSize(T)) << 1) |
3311  (T->isSignedIntegerType() ? 1 : 0);
3312  } else if (T->isFloatingType()) {
3313  TypeKind = 1;
3314  TypeInfo = getContext().getTypeSize(T);
3315  }
3316 
3317  // Format the type name as if for a diagnostic, including quotes and
3318  // optionally an 'aka'.
3319  SmallString<32> Buffer;
3320  CGM.getDiags().ConvertArgToString(
3321  DiagnosticsEngine::ak_qualtype, (intptr_t)T.getAsOpaquePtr(), StringRef(),
3322  StringRef(), std::nullopt, Buffer, std::nullopt);
3323 
3324  llvm::Constant *Components[] = {
3325  Builder.getInt16(TypeKind), Builder.getInt16(TypeInfo),
3326  llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(getLLVMContext(), Buffer)
3327  };
3328  llvm::Constant *Descriptor = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Components);
3329 
3330  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3331  CGM.getModule(), Descriptor->getType(),
3332  /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Descriptor);
3333  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3334  CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(GV);
3335 
3336  // Remember the descriptor for this type.
3337  CGM.setTypeDescriptorInMap(T, GV);
3338 
3339  return GV;
3340 }
3341 
3342 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckValue(llvm::Value *V) {
3343  llvm::Type *TargetTy = IntPtrTy;
3344 
3345  if (V->getType() == TargetTy)
3346  return V;
3347 
3348  // Floating-point types which fit into intptr_t are bitcast to integers
3349  // and then passed directly (after zero-extension, if necessary).
3350  if (V->getType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
3351  unsigned Bits = V->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getFixedValue();
3352  if (Bits <= TargetTy->getIntegerBitWidth())
3353  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getLLVMContext(),
3354  Bits));
3355  }
3356 
3357  // Integers which fit in intptr_t are zero-extended and passed directly.
3358  if (V->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
3359  V->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth() <= TargetTy->getIntegerBitWidth())
3360  return Builder.CreateZExt(V, TargetTy);
3361 
3362  // Pointers are passed directly, everything else is passed by address.
3363  if (!V->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
3364  RawAddress Ptr = CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(V->getType());
3365  Builder.CreateStore(V, Ptr);
3366  V = Ptr.getPointer();
3367  }
3368  return Builder.CreatePtrToInt(V, TargetTy);
3369 }
3370 
3371 /// Emit a representation of a SourceLocation for passing to a handler
3372 /// in a sanitizer runtime library. The format for this data is:
3373 /// \code
3374 /// struct SourceLocation {
3375 /// const char *Filename;
3376 /// int32_t Line, Column;
3377 /// };
3378 /// \endcode
3379 /// For an invalid SourceLocation, the Filename pointer is null.
3380 llvm::Constant *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckSourceLocation(SourceLocation Loc) {
3381  llvm::Constant *Filename;
3382  int Line, Column;
3383 
3384  PresumedLoc PLoc = getContext().getSourceManager().getPresumedLoc(Loc);
3385  if (PLoc.isValid()) {
3386  StringRef FilenameString = PLoc.getFilename();
3387 
3388  int PathComponentsToStrip =
3389  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCheckPathComponentsToStrip;
3390  if (PathComponentsToStrip < 0) {
3391  assert(PathComponentsToStrip != INT_MIN);
3392  int PathComponentsToKeep = -PathComponentsToStrip;
3393  auto I = llvm::sys::path::rbegin(FilenameString);
3394  auto E = llvm::sys::path::rend(FilenameString);
3395  while (I != E && --PathComponentsToKeep)
3396  ++I;
3397 
3398  FilenameString = FilenameString.substr(I - E);
3399  } else if (PathComponentsToStrip > 0) {
3400  auto I = llvm::sys::path::begin(FilenameString);
3401  auto E = llvm::sys::path::end(FilenameString);
3402  while (I != E && PathComponentsToStrip--)
3403  ++I;
3404 
3405  if (I != E)
3406  FilenameString =
3407  FilenameString.substr(I - llvm::sys::path::begin(FilenameString));
3408  else
3409  FilenameString = llvm::sys::path::filename(FilenameString);
3410  }
3411 
3412  auto FilenameGV =
3413  CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(std::string(FilenameString), ".src");
3414  CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(
3415  cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
3416  FilenameGV.getPointer()->stripPointerCasts()));
3417  Filename = FilenameGV.getPointer();
3418  Line = PLoc.getLine();
3419  Column = PLoc.getColumn();
3420  } else {
3421  Filename = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Int8PtrTy);
3422  Line = Column = 0;
3423  }
3424 
3425  llvm::Constant *Data[] = {Filename, Builder.getInt32(Line),
3426  Builder.getInt32(Column)};
3427 
3428  return llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Data);
3429 }
3430 
3431 namespace {
3432 /// Specify under what conditions this check can be recovered
3433 enum class CheckRecoverableKind {
3434  /// Always terminate program execution if this check fails.
3435  Unrecoverable,
3436  /// Check supports recovering, runtime has both fatal (noreturn) and
3437  /// non-fatal handlers for this check.
3438  Recoverable,
3439  /// Runtime conditionally aborts, always need to support recovery.
3440  AlwaysRecoverable
3441 };
3442 }
3443 
3444 static CheckRecoverableKind getRecoverableKind(SanitizerMask Kind) {
3445  assert(Kind.countPopulation() == 1);
3446  if (Kind == SanitizerKind::Vptr)
3447  return CheckRecoverableKind::AlwaysRecoverable;
3448  else if (Kind == SanitizerKind::Return || Kind == SanitizerKind::Unreachable)
3449  return CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable;
3450  else
3451  return CheckRecoverableKind::Recoverable;
3452 }
3453 
3454 namespace {
3455 struct SanitizerHandlerInfo {
3456  char const *const Name;
3457  unsigned Version;
3458 };
3459 }
3460 
3461 const SanitizerHandlerInfo SanitizerHandlers[] = {
3462 #define SANITIZER_CHECK(Enum, Name, Version) {#Name, Version},
3463  LIST_SANITIZER_CHECKS
3464 #undef SANITIZER_CHECK
3465 };
3466 
3467 static void emitCheckHandlerCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3468  llvm::FunctionType *FnType,
3469  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> FnArgs,
3470  SanitizerHandler CheckHandler,
3471  CheckRecoverableKind RecoverKind, bool IsFatal,
3472  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB) {
3473  assert(IsFatal || RecoverKind != CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable);
3474  std::optional<ApplyDebugLocation> DL;
3475  if (!CGF.Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation()) {
3476  // Ensure that the call has at least an artificial debug location.
3477  DL.emplace(CGF, SourceLocation());
3478  }
3479  bool NeedsAbortSuffix =
3480  IsFatal && RecoverKind != CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable;
3481  bool MinimalRuntime = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMinimalRuntime;
3482  const SanitizerHandlerInfo &CheckInfo = SanitizerHandlers[CheckHandler];
3483  const StringRef CheckName = CheckInfo.Name;
3484  std::string FnName = "__ubsan_handle_" + CheckName.str();
3485  if (CheckInfo.Version && !MinimalRuntime)
3486  FnName += "_v" + llvm::utostr(CheckInfo.Version);
3487  if (MinimalRuntime)
3488  FnName += "_minimal";
3489  if (NeedsAbortSuffix)
3490  FnName += "_abort";
3491  bool MayReturn =
3492  !IsFatal || RecoverKind == CheckRecoverableKind::AlwaysRecoverable;
3493 
3494  llvm::AttrBuilder B(CGF.getLLVMContext());
3495  if (!MayReturn) {
3496  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn)
3497  .addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
3498  }
3499  B.addUWTableAttr(llvm::UWTableKind::Default);
3500 
3501  llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
3502  FnType, FnName,
3503  llvm::AttributeList::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(),
3504  llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, B),
3505  /*Local=*/true);
3506  llvm::CallInst *HandlerCall = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(Fn, FnArgs);
3507  if (!MayReturn) {
3508  HandlerCall->setDoesNotReturn();
3509  CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3510  } else {
3511  CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
3512  }
3513 }
3514 
3515 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCheck(
3516  ArrayRef<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>> Checked,
3517  SanitizerHandler CheckHandler, ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> StaticArgs,
3518  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> DynamicArgs) {
3519  assert(IsSanitizerScope);
3520  assert(Checked.size() > 0);
3521  assert(CheckHandler >= 0 &&
3522  size_t(CheckHandler) < std::size(SanitizerHandlers));
3523  const StringRef CheckName = SanitizerHandlers[CheckHandler].Name;
3524 
3525  llvm::Value *FatalCond = nullptr;
3526  llvm::Value *RecoverableCond = nullptr;
3527  llvm::Value *TrapCond = nullptr;
3528  for (int i = 0, n = Checked.size(); i < n; ++i) {
3529  llvm::Value *Check = Checked[i].first;
3530  // -fsanitize-trap= overrides -fsanitize-recover=.
3531  llvm::Value *&Cond =
3532  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(Checked[i].second)
3533  ? TrapCond
3534  : CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeRecover.has(Checked[i].second)
3535  ? RecoverableCond
3536  : FatalCond;
3537  Cond = Cond ? Builder.CreateAnd(Cond, Check) : Check;
3538  }
3539 
3540  if (ClSanitizeGuardChecks) {
3541  llvm::Value *Allow =
3542  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::allow_ubsan_check),
3543  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, CheckHandler));
3544 
3545  for (llvm::Value **Cond : {&FatalCond, &RecoverableCond, &TrapCond}) {
3546  if (*Cond)
3547  *Cond = Builder.CreateOr(*Cond, Builder.CreateNot(Allow));
3548  }
3549  }
3550 
3551  if (TrapCond)
3552  EmitTrapCheck(TrapCond, CheckHandler);
3553  if (!FatalCond && !RecoverableCond)
3554  return;
3555 
3556  llvm::Value *JointCond;
3557  if (FatalCond && RecoverableCond)
3558  JointCond = Builder.CreateAnd(FatalCond, RecoverableCond);
3559  else
3560  JointCond = FatalCond ? FatalCond : RecoverableCond;
3561  assert(JointCond);
3562 
3563  CheckRecoverableKind RecoverKind = getRecoverableKind(Checked[0].second);
3564  assert(SanOpts.has(Checked[0].second));
3565 #ifndef NDEBUG
3566  for (int i = 1, n = Checked.size(); i < n; ++i) {
3567  assert(RecoverKind == getRecoverableKind(Checked[i].second) &&
3568  "All recoverable kinds in a single check must be same!");
3569  assert(SanOpts.has(Checked[i].second));
3570  }
3571 #endif
3572 
3573  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
3574  llvm::BasicBlock *Handlers = createBasicBlock("handler." + CheckName);
3575  llvm::Instruction *Branch = Builder.CreateCondBr(JointCond, Cont, Handlers);
3576  // Give hint that we very much don't expect to execute the handler
3577  // Value chosen to match UR_NONTAKEN_WEIGHT, see BranchProbabilityInfo.cpp
3578  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
3579  llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createBranchWeights((1U << 20) - 1, 1);
3580  Branch->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_prof, Node);
3581  EmitBlock(Handlers);
3582 
3583  // Handler functions take an i8* pointing to the (handler-specific) static
3584  // information block, followed by a sequence of intptr_t arguments
3585  // representing operand values.
3586  SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 4> Args;
3587  SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 4> ArgTypes;
3588  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMinimalRuntime) {
3589  Args.reserve(DynamicArgs.size() + 1);
3590  ArgTypes.reserve(DynamicArgs.size() + 1);
3591 
3592  // Emit handler arguments and create handler function type.
3593  if (!StaticArgs.empty()) {
3594  llvm::Constant *Info = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(StaticArgs);
3595  auto *InfoPtr = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3596  CGM.getModule(), Info->getType(), false,
3597  llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Info, "", nullptr,
3598  llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
3599  CGM.getDataLayout().getDefaultGlobalsAddressSpace());
3600  InfoPtr->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3601  CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(InfoPtr);
3602  Args.push_back(InfoPtr);
3603  ArgTypes.push_back(Args.back()->getType());
3604  }
3605 
3606  for (size_t i = 0, n = DynamicArgs.size(); i != n; ++i) {
3607  Args.push_back(EmitCheckValue(DynamicArgs[i]));
3608  ArgTypes.push_back(IntPtrTy);
3609  }
3610  }
3611 
3612  llvm::FunctionType *FnType =
3613  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, ArgTypes, false);
3614 
3615  if (!FatalCond || !RecoverableCond) {
3616  // Simple case: we need to generate a single handler call, either
3617  // fatal, or non-fatal.
3618  emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind,
3619  (FatalCond != nullptr), Cont);
3620  } else {
3621  // Emit two handler calls: first one for set of unrecoverable checks,
3622  // another one for recoverable.
3623  llvm::BasicBlock *NonFatalHandlerBB =
3624  createBasicBlock("non_fatal." + CheckName);
3625  llvm::BasicBlock *FatalHandlerBB = createBasicBlock("fatal." + CheckName);
3626  Builder.CreateCondBr(FatalCond, NonFatalHandlerBB, FatalHandlerBB);
3627  EmitBlock(FatalHandlerBB);
3628  emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind, true,
3629  NonFatalHandlerBB);
3630  EmitBlock(NonFatalHandlerBB);
3631  emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind, false,
3632  Cont);
3633  }
3634 
3635  EmitBlock(Cont);
3636 }
3637 
3638 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiSlowPathCheck(
3639  SanitizerMask Kind, llvm::Value *Cond, llvm::ConstantInt *TypeId,
3640  llvm::Value *Ptr, ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> StaticArgs) {
3641  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cfi.cont");
3642 
3643  llvm::BasicBlock *CheckBB = createBasicBlock("cfi.slowpath");
3644  llvm::BranchInst *BI = Builder.CreateCondBr(Cond, Cont, CheckBB);
3645 
3646  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
3647  llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createBranchWeights((1U << 20) - 1, 1);
3648  BI->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_prof, Node);
3649 
3650  EmitBlock(CheckBB);
3651 
3652  bool WithDiag = !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(Kind);
3653 
3654  llvm::CallInst *CheckCall;
3655  llvm::FunctionCallee SlowPathFn;
3656  if (WithDiag) {
3657  llvm::Constant *Info = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(StaticArgs);
3658  auto *InfoPtr =
3659  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Info->getType(), false,
3660  llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Info);
3661  InfoPtr->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3662  CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(InfoPtr);
3663 
3664  SlowPathFn = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertFunction(
3665  "__cfi_slowpath_diag",
3666  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy},
3667  false));
3668  CheckCall = Builder.CreateCall(SlowPathFn, {TypeId, Ptr, InfoPtr});
3669  } else {
3670  SlowPathFn = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertFunction(
3671  "__cfi_slowpath",
3672  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, Int8PtrTy}, false));
3673  CheckCall = Builder.CreateCall(SlowPathFn, {TypeId, Ptr});
3674  }
3675 
3676  CGM.setDSOLocal(
3677  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(SlowPathFn.getCallee()->stripPointerCasts()));
3678  CheckCall->setDoesNotThrow();
3679 
3680  EmitBlock(Cont);
3681 }
3682 
3683 // Emit a stub for __cfi_check function so that the linker knows about this
3684 // symbol in LTO mode.
3685 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiCheckStub() {
3686  llvm::Module *M = &CGM.getModule();
3687  ASTContext &C = getContext();
3688  QualType QInt64Ty = C.getIntTypeForBitwidth(64, false);
3689 
3690  FunctionArgList FnArgs;
3691  ImplicitParamDecl ArgCallsiteTypeId(C, QInt64Ty, ImplicitParamKind::Other);
3692  ImplicitParamDecl ArgAddr(C, C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamKind::Other);
3693  ImplicitParamDecl ArgCFICheckFailData(C, C.VoidPtrTy,
3694  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
3695  FnArgs.push_back(&ArgCallsiteTypeId);
3696  FnArgs.push_back(&ArgAddr);
3697  FnArgs.push_back(&ArgCFICheckFailData);
3698  const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
3699  CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(C.VoidTy, FnArgs);
3700 
3701  llvm::Function *F = llvm::Function::Create(
3702  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, VoidPtrTy, VoidPtrTy}, false),
3703  llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, "__cfi_check", M);
3704  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI, F, /*IsThunk=*/false);
3705  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(nullptr, F);
3706  F->setAlignment(llvm::Align(4096));
3707  CGM.setDSOLocal(F);
3708 
3709  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = M->getContext();
3710  llvm::BasicBlock *BB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "entry", F);
3711  // CrossDSOCFI pass is not executed if there is no executable code.
3712  SmallVector<llvm::Value*> Args{F->getArg(2), F->getArg(1)};
3713  llvm::CallInst::Create(M->getFunction("__cfi_check_fail"), Args, "", BB);
3714  llvm::ReturnInst::Create(Ctx, nullptr, BB);
3715 }
3716 
3717 // This function is basically a switch over the CFI failure kind, which is
3718 // extracted from CFICheckFailData (1st function argument). Each case is either
3719 // llvm.trap or a call to one of the two runtime handlers, based on
3720 // -fsanitize-trap and -fsanitize-recover settings. Default case (invalid
3721 // failure kind) traps, but this should really never happen. CFICheckFailData
3722 // can be nullptr if the calling module has -fsanitize-trap behavior for this
3723 // check kind; in this case __cfi_check_fail traps as well.
3724 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiCheckFail() {
3725  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3726  FunctionArgList Args;
3727  ImplicitParamDecl ArgData(getContext(), getContext().VoidPtrTy,
3728  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
3729  ImplicitParamDecl ArgAddr(getContext(), getContext().VoidPtrTy,
3730  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
3731  Args.push_back(&ArgData);
3732  Args.push_back(&ArgAddr);
3733 
3734  const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
3735  CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(getContext().VoidTy, Args);
3736 
3737  llvm::Function *F = llvm::Function::Create(
3738  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {VoidPtrTy, VoidPtrTy}, false),
3739  llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage, "__cfi_check_fail", &CGM.getModule());
3740 
3741  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI, F, /*IsThunk=*/false);
3742  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(nullptr, F);
3743  F->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
3744 
3745  StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), CGM.getContext().VoidTy, F, FI, Args,
3746  SourceLocation());
3747 
3748  // This function is not affected by NoSanitizeList. This function does
3749  // not have a source location, but "src:*" would still apply. Revert any
3750  // changes to SanOpts made in StartFunction.
3751  SanOpts = CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize;
3752 
3753  llvm::Value *Data =
3754  EmitLoadOfScalar(GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ArgData), /*Volatile=*/false,
3755  CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy, ArgData.getLocation());
3756  llvm::Value *Addr =
3757  EmitLoadOfScalar(GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ArgAddr), /*Volatile=*/false,
3758  CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy, ArgAddr.getLocation());
3759 
3760  // Data == nullptr means the calling module has trap behaviour for this check.
3761  llvm::Value *DataIsNotNullPtr =
3762  Builder.CreateICmpNE(Data, llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(Int8PtrTy));
3763  EmitTrapCheck(DataIsNotNullPtr, SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail);
3764 
3765  llvm::StructType *SourceLocationTy =
3766  llvm::StructType::get(VoidPtrTy, Int32Ty, Int32Ty);
3767  llvm::StructType *CfiCheckFailDataTy =
3768  llvm::StructType::get(Int8Ty, SourceLocationTy, VoidPtrTy);
3769 
3770  llvm::Value *V = Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(
3771  CfiCheckFailDataTy,
3772  Builder.CreatePointerCast(Data, CfiCheckFailDataTy->getPointerTo(0)), 0,
3773  0);
3774 
3775  Address CheckKindAddr(V, Int8Ty, getIntAlign());
3776  llvm::Value *CheckKind = Builder.CreateLoad(CheckKindAddr);
3777 
3778  llvm::Value *AllVtables = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(
3779  CGM.getLLVMContext(),
3780  llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "all-vtables"));
3781  llvm::Value *ValidVtable = Builder.CreateZExt(
3782  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test),
3783  {Addr, AllVtables}),
3784  IntPtrTy);
3785 
3786  const std::pair<int, SanitizerMask> CheckKinds[] = {
3787  {CFITCK_VCall, SanitizerKind::CFIVCall},
3788  {CFITCK_NVCall, SanitizerKind::CFINVCall},
3789  {CFITCK_DerivedCast, SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast},
3790  {CFITCK_UnrelatedCast, SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast},
3791  {CFITCK_ICall, SanitizerKind::CFIICall}};
3792 
3793  SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 5> Checks;
3794  for (auto CheckKindMaskPair : CheckKinds) {
3795  int Kind = CheckKindMaskPair.first;
3796  SanitizerMask Mask = CheckKindMaskPair.second;
3797  llvm::Value *Cond =
3798  Builder.CreateICmpNE(CheckKind, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, Kind));
3799  if (CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(Mask))
3800  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, Mask), SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, {},
3801  {Data, Addr, ValidVtable});
3802  else
3803  EmitTrapCheck(Cond, SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail);
3804  }
3805 
3806  FinishFunction();
3807  // The only reference to this function will be created during LTO link.
3808  // Make sure it survives until then.
3809  CGM.addUsedGlobal(F);
3810 }
3811 
3812 void CodeGenFunction::EmitUnreachable(SourceLocation Loc) {
3813  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Unreachable)) {
3814  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3815  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(static_cast<llvm::Value *>(Builder.getFalse()),
3816  SanitizerKind::Unreachable),
3817  SanitizerHandler::BuiltinUnreachable,
3818  EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc), std::nullopt);
3819  }
3820  Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3821 }
3822 
3823 void CodeGenFunction::EmitTrapCheck(llvm::Value *Checked,
3824  SanitizerHandler CheckHandlerID) {
3825  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
3826 
3827  // If we're optimizing, collapse all calls to trap down to just one per
3828  // check-type per function to save on code size.
3829  if ((int)TrapBBs.size() <= CheckHandlerID)
3830  TrapBBs.resize(CheckHandlerID + 1);
3831 
3832  llvm::BasicBlock *&TrapBB = TrapBBs[CheckHandlerID];
3833 
3834  if (!ClSanitizeDebugDeoptimization &&
3835  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel && TrapBB &&
3836  (!CurCodeDecl || !CurCodeDecl->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>())) {
3837  auto Call = TrapBB->begin();
3838  assert(isa<llvm::CallInst>(Call) && "Expected call in trap BB");
3839 
3840  Call->applyMergedLocation(Call->getDebugLoc(),
3841  Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation());
3842  Builder.CreateCondBr(Checked, Cont, TrapBB);
3843  } else {
3844  TrapBB = createBasicBlock("trap");
3845  Builder.CreateCondBr(Checked, Cont, TrapBB);
3846  EmitBlock(TrapBB);
3847 
3848  llvm::CallInst *TrapCall = Builder.CreateCall(
3849  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::ubsantrap),
3850  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, ClSanitizeDebugDeoptimization
3851  ? TrapBB->getParent()->size()
3852  : CheckHandlerID));
3853 
3854  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName.empty()) {
3855  auto A = llvm::Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), "trap-func-name",
3856  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName);
3857  TrapCall->addFnAttr(A);
3858  }
3859  TrapCall->setDoesNotReturn();
3860  TrapCall->setDoesNotThrow();
3861  Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3862  }
3863 
3864  EmitBlock(Cont);
3865 }
3866 
3867 llvm::CallInst *CodeGenFunction::EmitTrapCall(llvm::Intrinsic::ID IntrID) {
3868  llvm::CallInst *TrapCall =
3869  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrID));
3870 
3871  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName.empty()) {
3872  auto A = llvm::Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), "trap-func-name",
3873  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName);
3874  TrapCall->addFnAttr(A);
3875  }
3876 
3877  return TrapCall;
3878 }
3879 
3880 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitArrayToPointerDecay(const Expr *E,
3881  LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
3882  TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
3883  assert(E->getType()->isArrayType() &&
3884  "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
3885 
3886  // Expressions of array type can't be bitfields or vector elements.
3887  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E);
3888  Address Addr = LV.getAddress(*this);
3889 
3890  // If the array type was an incomplete type, we need to make sure
3891  // the decay ends up being the right type.
3892  llvm::Type *NewTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
3893  Addr = Addr.withElementType(NewTy);
3894 
3895  // Note that VLA pointers are always decayed, so we don't need to do
3896  // anything here.
3897  if (!E->getType()->isVariableArrayType()) {
3898  assert(isa<llvm::ArrayType>(Addr.getElementType()) &&
3899  "Expected pointer to array");
3900  Addr = Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(Addr, 0, "arraydecay");
3901  }
3902 
3903  // The result of this decay conversion points to an array element within the
3904  // base lvalue. However, since TBAA currently does not support representing
3905  // accesses to elements of member arrays, we conservatively represent accesses
3906  // to the pointee object as if it had no any base lvalue specified.
3907  // TODO: Support TBAA for member arrays.
3908  QualType EltType = E->getType()->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe()->getElementType();
3909  if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = LV.getBaseInfo();
3910  if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAAccessInfo(EltType);
3911 
3912  return Addr.withElementType(ConvertTypeForMem(EltType));
3913 }
3914 
3915 /// isSimpleArrayDecayOperand - If the specified expr is a simple decay from an
3916 /// array to pointer, return the array subexpression.
3917 static const Expr *isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(const Expr *E) {
3918  // If this isn't just an array->pointer decay, bail out.
3919  const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(E);
3920  if (!CE || CE->getCastKind() != CK_ArrayToPointerDecay)
3921  return nullptr;
3922 
3923  // If this is a decay from variable width array, bail out.
3924  const Expr *SubExpr = CE->getSubExpr();
3925  if (SubExpr->getType()->isVariableArrayType())
3926  return nullptr;
3927 
3928  return SubExpr;
3929 }
3930 
3931 static llvm::Value *emitArraySubscriptGEP(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3932  llvm::Type *elemType,
3933  llvm::Value *ptr,
3934  ArrayRef<llvm::Value*> indices,
3935  bool inbounds,
3936  bool signedIndices,
3937  SourceLocation loc,
3938  const llvm::Twine &name = "arrayidx") {
3939  if (inbounds) {
3940  return CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(elemType, ptr, indices, signedIndices,
3941  CodeGenFunction::NotSubtraction, loc,
3942  name);
3943  } else {
3944  return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(elemType, ptr, indices, name);
3945  }
3946 }
3947 
3948 static Address emitArraySubscriptGEP(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address addr,
3949  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> indices,
3950  llvm::Type *elementType, bool inbounds,
3951  bool signedIndices, SourceLocation loc,
3952  CharUnits align,
3953  const llvm::Twine &name = "arrayidx") {
3954  if (inbounds) {
3955  return CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(addr, indices, elementType, signedIndices,
3956  CodeGenFunction::NotSubtraction, loc,
3957  align, name);
3958  } else {
3959  return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(addr, indices, elementType, align, name);
3960  }
3961 }
3962 
3963 static CharUnits getArrayElementAlign(CharUnits arrayAlign,
3964  llvm::Value *idx,
3965  CharUnits eltSize) {
3966  // If we have a constant index, we can use the exact offset of the
3967  // element we're accessing.
3968  if (auto constantIdx = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx)) {
3969  CharUnits offset = constantIdx->getZExtValue() * eltSize;
3970  return arrayAlign.alignmentAtOffset(offset);
3971 
3972  // Otherwise, use the worst-case alignment for any element.
3973  } else {
3974  return arrayAlign.alignmentOfArrayElement(eltSize);
3975  }
3976 }
3977 
3978 static QualType getFixedSizeElementType(const ASTContext &ctx,
3979  const VariableArrayType *vla) {
3980  QualType eltType;
3981  do {
3982  eltType = vla->getElementType();
3983  } while ((vla = ctx.getAsVariableArrayType(eltType)));
3984  return eltType;
3985 }
3986 
3987 static void AddIVDepMetadata(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const ValueDecl *ArrayDecl,
3988  llvm::Value *EltPtr) {
3989  if (!ArrayDecl)
3990  return;
3991 
3992  // Only handle actual GEPs, ConstantExpr GEPs don't have metadata.
3993  if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<llvm::GetElementPtrInst>(EltPtr))
3994  CGF.LoopStack.addIVDepMetadata(ArrayDecl, GEP);
3995 }
3996 
3997 static bool hasBPFPreserveStaticOffset(const RecordDecl *D) {
3998  return D && D->hasAttr<BPFPreserveStaticOffsetAttr>();
3999 }
4000 
4001 static bool hasBPFPreserveStaticOffset(const Expr *E) {
4002  if (!E)
4003  return false;
4004  QualType PointeeType = E->getType()->getPointeeType();
4005  if (PointeeType.isNull())
4006  return false;
4007  if (const auto *BaseDecl = PointeeType->getAsRecordDecl())
4008  return hasBPFPreserveStaticOffset(BaseDecl);
4009  return false;
4010 }
4011 
4012 // Wraps Addr with a call to llvm.preserve.static.offset intrinsic.
4013 static Address wrapWithBPFPreserveStaticOffset(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4014  Address &Addr) {
4015  if (!CGF.getTarget().getTriple().isBPF())
4016  return Addr;
4017 
4018  llvm::Function *Fn =
4019  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::preserve_static_offset);
4020  llvm::CallInst *Call = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(Fn, {Addr.emitRawPointer(CGF)});
4021  return Address(Call, Addr.getElementType(), Addr.getAlignment());
4022 }
4023 
4024 /// Given an array base, check whether its member access belongs to a record
4025 /// with preserve_access_index attribute or not.
4026 static bool IsPreserveAIArrayBase(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *ArrayBase) {
4027  if (!ArrayBase || !CGF.getDebugInfo())
4028  return false;
4029 
4030  // Only support base as either a MemberExpr or DeclRefExpr.
4031  // DeclRefExpr to cover cases like:
4032  // struct s { int a; int b[10]; };
4033  // struct s *p;
4034  // p[1].a
4035  // p[1] will generate a DeclRefExpr and p[1].a is a MemberExpr.
4036  // p->b[5] is a MemberExpr example.
4037  const Expr *E = ArrayBase->IgnoreImpCasts();
4038  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E))
4039  return ME->getMemberDecl()->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>();
4040 
4041  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
4042  const auto *VarDef = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
4043  if (!VarDef)
4044  return false;
4045 
4046  const auto *PtrT = VarDef->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
4047  if (!PtrT)
4048  return false;
4049 
4050  const auto *PointeeT = PtrT->getPointeeType()
4051  ->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
4052  if (const auto *RecT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(PointeeT))
4053  return RecT->getDecl()->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>();
4054  return false;
4055  }
4056 
4057  return false;
4058 }
4059 
4060 static Address emitArraySubscriptGEP(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address addr,
4061  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> indices,
4062  QualType eltType, bool inbounds,
4063  bool signedIndices, SourceLocation loc,
4064  QualType *arrayType = nullptr,
4065  const Expr *Base = nullptr,
4066  const llvm::Twine &name = "arrayidx",
4067  const ValueDecl *arrayDecl = nullptr) {
4068  // All the indices except that last must be zero.
4069 #ifndef NDEBUG
4070  for (auto *idx : indices.drop_back())
4071  assert(isa<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx) &&
4072  cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx)->isZero());
4073 #endif
4074 
4075  // Determine the element size of the statically-sized base. This is
4076  // the thing that the indices are expressed in terms of.
4077  if (auto vla = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(eltType)) {
4078  eltType = getFixedSizeElementType(CGF.getContext(), vla);
4079  }
4080 
4081  // We can use that to compute the best alignment of the element.
4082  CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(eltType);
4083  CharUnits eltAlign =
4084  getArrayElementAlign(addr.getAlignment(), indices.back(), eltSize);
4085 
4086  if (hasBPFPreserveStaticOffset(Base))
4087  addr = wrapWithBPFPreserveStaticOffset(CGF, addr);
4088 
4089  llvm::Value *eltPtr;
4090  auto LastIndex = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(indices.back());
4091  if (!LastIndex ||
4092  (!CGF.IsInPreservedAIRegion && !IsPreserveAIArrayBase(CGF, Base))) {
4093  addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(CGF, addr, indices,
4094  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(eltType), inbounds,
4095  signedIndices, loc, eltAlign, name);
4096  AddIVDepMetadata(CGF, arrayDecl, addr.emitRawPointer(CGF));
4097  return addr;
4098  } else {
4099  // Remember the original array subscript for bpf target
4100  unsigned idx = LastIndex->getZExtValue();
4101  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = nullptr;
4102  if (arrayType)
4103  DbgInfo = CGF.getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateStandaloneType(*arrayType, loc);
4104  eltPtr = CGF.Builder.CreatePreserveArrayAccessIndex(
4105  addr.getElementType(), addr.emitRawPointer(CGF), indices.size() - 1,
4106  idx, DbgInfo);
4107  }
4108 
4109  return Address(eltPtr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(eltType), eltAlign);
4110 }
4111 
4112 /// The offset of a field from the beginning of the record.
4113 static bool getFieldOffsetInBits(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const RecordDecl *RD,
4114  const FieldDecl *FD, int64_t &Offset) {
4115  ASTContext &Ctx = CGF.getContext();
4116  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
4117  unsigned FieldNo = 0;
4118 
4119  for (const Decl *D : RD->decls()) {
4120  if (const auto *Record = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(D))
4121  if (getFieldOffsetInBits(CGF, Record, FD, Offset)) {
4122  Offset += Layout.getFieldOffset(FieldNo);
4123  return true;
4124  }
4125 
4126  if (const auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D))
4127  if (FD == Field) {
4128  Offset += Layout.getFieldOffset(FieldNo);
4129  return true;
4130  }
4131 
4132  if (isa<FieldDecl>(D))
4133  ++FieldNo;
4134  }
4135 
4136  return false;
4137 }
4138 
4139 /// Returns the relative offset difference between \p FD1 and \p FD2.
4140 /// \code
4141 /// offsetof(struct foo, FD1) - offsetof(struct foo, FD2)
4142 /// \endcode
4143 /// Both fields must be within the same struct.
4144 static std::optional<int64_t> getOffsetDifferenceInBits(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4145  const FieldDecl *FD1,
4146  const FieldDecl *FD2) {
4147  const RecordDecl *FD1OuterRec =
4148  FD1->getParent()->getOuterLexicalRecordContext();
4149  const RecordDecl *FD2OuterRec =
4150  FD2->getParent()->getOuterLexicalRecordContext();
4151 
4152  if (FD1OuterRec != FD2OuterRec)
4153  // Fields must be within the same RecordDecl.
4154  return std::optional<int64_t>();
4155 
4156  int64_t FD1Offset = 0;
4157  if (!getFieldOffsetInBits(CGF, FD1OuterRec, FD1, FD1Offset))
4158  return std::optional<int64_t>();
4159 
4160  int64_t FD2Offset = 0;
4161  if (!getFieldOffsetInBits(CGF, FD2OuterRec, FD2, FD2Offset))
4162  return std::optional<int64_t>();
4163 
4164  return std::make_optional<int64_t>(FD1Offset - FD2Offset);
4165 }
4166 
4167 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitArraySubscriptExpr(const ArraySubscriptExpr *E,
4168  bool Accessed) {
4169  // The index must always be an integer, which is not an aggregate. Emit it
4170  // in lexical order (this complexity is, sadly, required by C++17).
4171  llvm::Value *IdxPre =
4172  (E->getLHS() == E->getIdx()) ? EmitScalarExpr(E->getIdx()) : nullptr;
4173  bool SignedIndices = false;
4174  auto EmitIdxAfterBase = [&, IdxPre](bool Promote) -> llvm::Value * {
4175  auto *Idx = IdxPre;
4176  if (E->getLHS() != E->getIdx()) {
4177  assert(E->getRHS() == E->getIdx() && "index was neither LHS nor RHS");
4178  Idx = EmitScalarExpr(E->getIdx());
4179  }
4180 
4181  QualType IdxTy = E->getIdx()->getType();
4182  bool IdxSigned = IdxTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
4183  SignedIndices |= IdxSigned;
4184 
4185  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds))
4186  EmitBoundsCheck(E, E->getBase(), Idx, IdxTy, Accessed);
4187 
4188  // Extend or truncate the index type to 32 or 64-bits.
4189  if (Promote && Idx->getType() != IntPtrTy)
4190  Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(Idx, IntPtrTy, IdxSigned, "idxprom");
4191 
4192  return Idx;
4193  };
4194  IdxPre = nullptr;
4195 
4196  // If the base is a vector type, then we are forming a vector element lvalue
4197  // with this subscript.
4198  if (E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType() &&
4199  !isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E->getBase())) {
4200  // Emit the vector as an lvalue to get its address.
4201  LValue LHS = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
4202  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/false);
4203  assert(LHS.isSimple() && "Can only subscript lvalue vectors here!");
4204  return LValue::MakeVectorElt(LHS.getAddress(*this), Idx,
4205  E->getBase()->getType(), LHS.getBaseInfo(),
4206  TBAAAccessInfo());
4207  }
4208 
4209  // All the other cases basically behave like simple offsetting.
4210 
4211  // Handle the extvector case we ignored above.
4212  if (isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E->getBase())) {
4213  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
4214  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4215  Address Addr = EmitExtVectorElementLValue(LV);
4216 
4217  QualType EltType = LV.getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
4218  Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, EltType, /*inbounds*/ true,
4219  SignedIndices, E->getExprLoc());
4220  return MakeAddrLValue(Addr, EltType, LV.getBaseInfo(),
4221  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, EltType));
4222  }
4223 
4224  LValueBaseInfo EltBaseInfo;
4225  TBAAAccessInfo EltTBAAInfo;
4226  Address Addr = Address::invalid();
4227  if (const VariableArrayType *vla =
4228  getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(E->getType())) {
4229  // The base must be a pointer, which is not an aggregate. Emit
4230  // it. It needs to be emitted first in case it's what captures
4231  // the VLA bounds.
4232  Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
4233  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4234 
4235  // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
4236  llvm::Value *numElements = getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
4237 
4238  // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
4239  // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
4240  // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
4241  // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
4242  if (getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined()) {
4243  Idx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, numElements);
4244  } else {
4245  Idx = Builder.CreateNSWMul(Idx, numElements);
4246  }
4247 
4248  Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, vla->getElementType(),
4249  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4250  SignedIndices, E->getExprLoc());
4251 
4252  } else if (const ObjCObjectType *OIT = E->getType()->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()){
4253  // Indexing over an interface, as in "NSString *P; P[4];"
4254 
4255  // Emit the base pointer.
4256  Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
4257  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4258 
4259  CharUnits InterfaceSize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(OIT);
4260  llvm::Value *InterfaceSizeVal =
4261  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Idx->getType(), InterfaceSize.getQuantity());
4262 
4263  llvm::Value *ScaledIdx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, InterfaceSizeVal);
4264 
4265  // We don't necessarily build correct LLVM struct types for ObjC
4266  // interfaces, so we can't rely on GEP to do this scaling
4267  // correctly, so we need to cast to i8*. FIXME: is this actually
4268  // true? A lot of other things in the fragile ABI would break...
4269  llvm::Type *OrigBaseElemTy = Addr.getElementType();
4270 
4271  // Do the GEP.
4272  CharUnits EltAlign =
4273  getArrayElementAlign(Addr.getAlignment(), Idx, InterfaceSize);
4274  llvm::Value *EltPtr =
4275  emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Int8Ty, Addr.emitRawPointer(*this),
4276  ScaledIdx, false, SignedIndices, E->getExprLoc());
4277  Addr = Address(EltPtr, OrigBaseElemTy, EltAlign);
4278  } else if (const Expr *Array = isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(E->getBase())) {
4279  // If this is A[i] where A is an array, the frontend will have decayed the
4280  // base to be a ArrayToPointerDecay implicit cast. While correct, it is
4281  // inefficient at -O0 to emit a "gep A, 0, 0" when codegen'ing it, then a
4282  // "gep x, i" here. Emit one "gep A, 0, i".
4283  assert(Array->getType()->isArrayType() &&
4284  "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
4285  LValue ArrayLV;
4286  // For simple multidimensional array indexing, set the 'accessed' flag for
4287  // better bounds-checking of the base expression.
4288  if (const auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Array))
4289  ArrayLV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(ASE, /*Accessed*/ true);
4290  else
4291  ArrayLV = EmitLValue(Array);
4292  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4293 
4294  const ValueDecl *ArrayDecl = nullptr;
4295  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Array->IgnoreParenCasts()))
4296  ArrayDecl = DRE->getDecl();
4297  else if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(Array->IgnoreParenCasts()))
4298  ArrayDecl = ME->getMemberDecl();
4299 
4300  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds)) {
4301  // If the array being accessed has a "counted_by" attribute, generate
4302  // bounds checking code. The "count" field is at the top level of the
4303  // struct or in an anonymous struct, that's also at the top level. Future
4304  // expansions may allow the "count" to reside at any place in the struct,
4305  // but the value of "counted_by" will be a "simple" path to the count,
4306  // i.e. "a.b.count", so we shouldn't need the full force of EmitLValue or
4307  // similar to emit the correct GEP.
4308  const LangOptions::StrictFlexArraysLevelKind StrictFlexArraysLevel =
4309  getLangOpts().getStrictFlexArraysLevel();
4310 
4311  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(Array);
4312  ME &&
4313  ME->isFlexibleArrayMemberLike(getContext(), StrictFlexArraysLevel) &&
4314  ME->getMemberDecl()->getType()->isCountAttributedType()) {
4315  const FieldDecl *FAMDecl = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl());
4316  if (const FieldDecl *CountFD = FindCountedByField(FAMDecl)) {
4317  if (std::optional<int64_t> Diff =
4318  getOffsetDifferenceInBits(*this, CountFD, FAMDecl)) {
4319  CharUnits OffsetDiff = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(*Diff);
4320 
4321  // Create a GEP with a byte offset between the FAM and count and
4322  // use that to load the count value.
4323  Addr = Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
4324  ArrayLV.getAddress(*this), Int8PtrTy, Int8Ty);
4325 
4326  llvm::Type *CountTy = ConvertType(CountFD->getType());
4327  llvm::Value *Res = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(
4328  Int8Ty, Addr.emitRawPointer(*this),
4329  Builder.getInt32(OffsetDiff.getQuantity()), ".counted_by.gep");
4330  Res = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(CountTy, Res, getIntAlign(),
4331  ".counted_by.load");
4332 
4333  // Now emit the bounds checking.
4334  EmitBoundsCheckImpl(E, Res, Idx, E->getIdx()->getType(),
4335  Array->getType(), Accessed);
4336  }
4337  }
4338  }
4339  }
4340 
4341  // Propagate the alignment from the array itself to the result.
4342  QualType arrayType = Array->getType();
4343  Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(
4344  *this, ArrayLV.getAddress(*this), {CGM.getSize(CharUnits::Zero()), Idx},
4345  E->getType(), !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(), SignedIndices,
4346  E->getExprLoc(), &arrayType, E->getBase(), "arrayidx", ArrayDecl);
4347  EltBaseInfo = ArrayLV.getBaseInfo();
4348  EltTBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(ArrayLV, E->getType());
4349  } else {
4350  // The base must be a pointer; emit it with an estimate of its alignment.
4351  Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
4352  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
4353  QualType ptrType = E->getBase()->getType();
4354 
4355  const ValueDecl *PtrDecl = nullptr;
4356  if (const auto *DRE =
4357  dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->getBase()->IgnoreParenCasts()))
4358  PtrDecl = DRE->getDecl();
4359  else if (const auto *ME =
4360  dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E->getBase()->IgnoreParenCasts()))
4361  PtrDecl = ME->getMemberDecl();
4362 
4363  Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, E->getType(),
4364  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4365  SignedIndices, E->getExprLoc(), &ptrType,
4366  E->getBase(), "arrayidx", PtrDecl);
4367  }
4368 
4369  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, E->getType(), EltBaseInfo, EltTBAAInfo);
4370 
4371  if (getLangOpts().ObjC &&
4372  getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
4373  LV.setNonGC(!E->isOBJCGCCandidate(getContext()));
4374  setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
4375  }
4376  return LV;
4377 }
4378 
4379 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitMatrixSubscriptExpr(const MatrixSubscriptExpr *E) {
4380  assert(
4381  !E->isIncomplete() &&
4382  "incomplete matrix subscript expressions should be rejected during Sema");
4383  LValue Base = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
4384  llvm::Value *RowIdx = EmitScalarExpr(E->getRowIdx());
4385  llvm::Value *ColIdx = EmitScalarExpr(E->getColumnIdx());
4386  llvm::Value *NumRows = Builder.getIntN(
4387  RowIdx->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits(),
4388  E->getBase()->getType()->castAs<ConstantMatrixType>()->getNumRows());
4389  llvm::Value *FinalIdx =
4390  Builder.CreateAdd(Builder.CreateMul(ColIdx, NumRows), RowIdx);
4391  return LValue::MakeMatrixElt(
4392  MaybeConvertMatrixAddress(Base.getAddress(*this), *this), FinalIdx,
4393  E->getBase()->getType(), Base.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
4394 }
4395 
4396 static Address emitOMPArraySectionBase(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *Base,
4397  LValueBaseInfo &BaseInfo,
4398  TBAAAccessInfo &TBAAInfo,
4399  QualType BaseTy, QualType ElTy,
4400  bool IsLowerBound) {
4401  LValue BaseLVal;
4402  if (auto *ASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(Base->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) {
4403  BaseLVal = CGF.EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(ASE, IsLowerBound);
4404  if (BaseTy->isArrayType()) {
4405  Address Addr = BaseLVal.getAddress(CGF);
4406  BaseInfo = BaseLVal.getBaseInfo();
4407 
4408  // If the array type was an incomplete type, we need to make sure
4409  // the decay ends up being the right type.
4410  llvm::Type *NewTy = CGF.ConvertType(BaseTy);
4411  Addr = Addr.withElementType(NewTy);
4412 
4413  // Note that VLA pointers are always decayed, so we don't need to do
4414  // anything here.
4415  if (!BaseTy->isVariableArrayType()) {
4416  assert(isa<llvm::ArrayType>(Addr.getElementType()) &&
4417  "Expected pointer to array");
4418  Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(Addr, 0, "arraydecay");
4419  }
4420 
4421  return Addr.withElementType(CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ElTy));
4422  }
4423  LValueBaseInfo TypeBaseInfo;
4424  TBAAAccessInfo TypeTBAAInfo;
4425  CharUnits Align =
4426  CGF.CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(ElTy, &TypeBaseInfo, &TypeTBAAInfo);
4427  BaseInfo.mergeForCast(TypeBaseInfo);
4428  TBAAInfo = CGF.CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForCast(TBAAInfo, TypeTBAAInfo);
4429  return Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(BaseLVal.getAddress(CGF)),
4430  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ElTy), Align);
4431  }
4432  return CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(Base, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4433 }
4434 
4435 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(const OMPArraySectionExpr *E,
4436  bool IsLowerBound) {
4437  QualType BaseTy = OMPArraySectionExpr::getBaseOriginalType(E->getBase());
4438  QualType ResultExprTy;
4439  if (auto *AT = getContext().getAsArrayType(BaseTy))
4440  ResultExprTy = AT->getElementType();
4441  else
4442  ResultExprTy = BaseTy->getPointeeType();
4443  llvm::Value *Idx = nullptr;
4444  if (IsLowerBound || E->getColonLocFirst().isInvalid()) {
4445  // Requesting lower bound or upper bound, but without provided length and
4446  // without ':' symbol for the default length -> length = 1.
4447  // Idx = LowerBound ?: 0;
4448  if (auto *LowerBound = E->getLowerBound()) {
4449  Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(
4450  EmitScalarExpr(LowerBound), IntPtrTy,
4451  LowerBound->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation());
4452  } else
4453  Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy);
4454  } else {
4455  // Try to emit length or lower bound as constant. If this is possible, 1
4456  // is subtracted from constant length or lower bound. Otherwise, emit LLVM
4457  // IR (LB + Len) - 1.
4458  auto &C = CGM.getContext();
4459  auto *Length = E->getLength();
4460  llvm::APSInt ConstLength;
4461  if (Length) {
4462  // Idx = LowerBound + Length - 1;
4463  if (std::optional<llvm::APSInt> CL = Length->getIntegerConstantExpr(C)) {
4464  ConstLength = CL->zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4465  Length = nullptr;
4466  }
4467  auto *LowerBound = E->getLowerBound();
4468  llvm::APSInt ConstLowerBound(PointerWidthInBits, /*isUnsigned=*/false);
4469  if (LowerBound) {
4470  if (std::optional<llvm::APSInt> LB =
4471  LowerBound->getIntegerConstantExpr(C)) {
4472  ConstLowerBound = LB->zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4473  LowerBound = nullptr;
4474  }
4475  }
4476  if (!Length)
4477  --ConstLength;
4478  else if (!LowerBound)
4479  --ConstLowerBound;
4480 
4481  if (Length || LowerBound) {
4482  auto *LowerBoundVal =
4483  LowerBound
4484  ? Builder.CreateIntCast(
4485  EmitScalarExpr(LowerBound), IntPtrTy,
4486  LowerBound->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation())
4487  : llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLowerBound);
4488  auto *LengthVal =
4489  Length
4490  ? Builder.CreateIntCast(
4491  EmitScalarExpr(Length), IntPtrTy,
4492  Length->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation())
4493  : llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength);
4494  Idx = Builder.CreateAdd(LowerBoundVal, LengthVal, "lb_add_len",
4495  /*HasNUW=*/false,
4496  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4497  if (Length && LowerBound) {
4498  Idx = Builder.CreateSub(
4499  Idx, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, /*V=*/1), "idx_sub_1",
4500  /*HasNUW=*/false, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4501  }
4502  } else
4503  Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength + ConstLowerBound);
4504  } else {
4505  // Idx = ArraySize - 1;
4506  QualType ArrayTy = BaseTy->isPointerType()
4507  ? E->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts()->getType()
4508  : BaseTy;
4509  if (auto *VAT = C.getAsVariableArrayType(ArrayTy)) {
4510  Length = VAT->getSizeExpr();
4511  if (std::optional<llvm::APSInt> L = Length->getIntegerConstantExpr(C)) {
4512  ConstLength = *L;
4513  Length = nullptr;
4514  }
4515  } else {
4516  auto *CAT = C.getAsConstantArrayType(ArrayTy);
4517  assert(CAT && "unexpected type for array initializer");
4518  ConstLength = CAT->getSize();
4519  }
4520  if (Length) {
4521  auto *LengthVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(
4522  EmitScalarExpr(Length), IntPtrTy,
4523  Length->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation());
4524  Idx = Builder.CreateSub(
4525  LengthVal, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, /*V=*/1), "len_sub_1",
4526  /*HasNUW=*/false, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4527  } else {
4528  ConstLength = ConstLength.zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4529  --ConstLength;
4530  Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength);
4531  }
4532  }
4533  }
4534  assert(Idx);
4535 
4536  Address EltPtr = Address::invalid();
4537  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4538  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4539  if (auto *VLA = getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(ResultExprTy)) {
4540  // The base must be a pointer, which is not an aggregate. Emit
4541  // it. It needs to be emitted first in case it's what captures
4542  // the VLA bounds.
4543  Address Base =
4544  emitOMPArraySectionBase(*this, E->getBase(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo,
4545  BaseTy, VLA->getElementType(), IsLowerBound);
4546  // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
4547  llvm::Value *NumElements = getVLASize(VLA).NumElts;
4548 
4549  // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
4550  // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
4551  // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
4552  // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
4553  if (getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
4554  Idx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, NumElements);
4555  else
4556  Idx = Builder.CreateNSWMul(Idx, NumElements);
4557  EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Base, Idx, VLA->getElementType(),
4558  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4559  /*signedIndices=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
4560  } else if (const Expr *Array = isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(E->getBase())) {
4561  // If this is A[i] where A is an array, the frontend will have decayed the
4562  // base to be a ArrayToPointerDecay implicit cast. While correct, it is
4563  // inefficient at -O0 to emit a "gep A, 0, 0" when codegen'ing it, then a
4564  // "gep x, i" here. Emit one "gep A, 0, i".
4565  assert(Array->getType()->isArrayType() &&
4566  "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
4567  LValue ArrayLV;
4568  // For simple multidimensional array indexing, set the 'accessed' flag for
4569  // better bounds-checking of the base expression.
4570  if (const auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Array))
4571  ArrayLV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(ASE, /*Accessed*/ true);
4572  else
4573  ArrayLV = EmitLValue(Array);
4574 
4575  // Propagate the alignment from the array itself to the result.
4576  EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(
4577  *this, ArrayLV.getAddress(*this), {CGM.getSize(CharUnits::Zero()), Idx},
4578  ResultExprTy, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4579  /*signedIndices=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
4580  BaseInfo = ArrayLV.getBaseInfo();
4581  TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(ArrayLV, ResultExprTy);
4582  } else {
4583  Address Base =
4584  emitOMPArraySectionBase(*this, E->getBase(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo, BaseTy,
4585  ResultExprTy, IsLowerBound);
4586  EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Base, Idx, ResultExprTy,
4587  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4588  /*signedIndices=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
4589  }
4590 
4591  return MakeAddrLValue(EltPtr, ResultExprTy, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4592 }
4593 
4594 LValue CodeGenFunction::
4595 EmitExtVectorElementExpr(const ExtVectorElementExpr *E) {
4596  // Emit the base vector as an l-value.
4597  LValue Base;
4598 
4599  // ExtVectorElementExpr's base can either be a vector or pointer to vector.
4600  if (E->isArrow()) {
4601  // If it is a pointer to a vector, emit the address and form an lvalue with
4602  // it.
4603  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4604  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4605  Address Ptr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4606  const auto *PT = E->getBase()->getType()->castAs<PointerType>();
4607  Base = MakeAddrLValue(Ptr, PT->getPointeeType(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4608  Base.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
4609  } else if (E->getBase()->isGLValue()) {
4610  // Otherwise, if the base is an lvalue ( as in the case of foo.x.x),
4611  // emit the base as an lvalue.
4612  assert(E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType());
4613  Base = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
4614  } else {
4615  // Otherwise, the base is a normal rvalue (as in (V+V).x), emit it as such.
4616  assert(E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType() &&
4617  "Result must be a vector");
4618  llvm::Value *Vec = EmitScalarExpr(E->getBase());
4619 
4620  // Store the vector to memory (because LValue wants an address).
4621  Address VecMem = CreateMemTemp(E->getBase()->getType());
4622  Builder.CreateStore(Vec, VecMem);
4623  Base = MakeAddrLValue(VecMem, E->getBase()->getType(),
4624  AlignmentSource::Decl);
4625  }
4626 
4627  QualType type =
4628  E->getType().withCVRQualifiers(Base.getQuals().getCVRQualifiers());
4629 
4630  // Encode the element access list into a vector of unsigned indices.
4631  SmallVector<uint32_t, 4> Indices;
4632  E->getEncodedElementAccess(Indices);
4633 
4634  if (Base.isSimple()) {
4635  llvm::Constant *CV =
4636  llvm::ConstantDataVector::get(getLLVMContext(), Indices);
4637  return LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(Base.getAddress(*this), CV, type,
4638  Base.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
4639  }
4640  assert(Base.isExtVectorElt() && "Can only subscript lvalue vec elts here!");
4641 
4642  llvm::Constant *BaseElts = Base.getExtVectorElts();
4643  SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> CElts;
4644 
4645  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Indices.size(); i != e; ++i)
4646  CElts.push_back(BaseElts->getAggregateElement(Indices[i]));
4647  llvm::Constant *CV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(CElts);
4648  return LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(Base.getExtVectorAddress(), CV, type,
4649  Base.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
4650 }
4651 
4652 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitMemberExpr(const MemberExpr *E) {
4653  if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(*this, E)) {
4654  EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getBase());
4655  return EmitDeclRefLValue(DRE);
4656  }
4657 
4658  Expr *BaseExpr = E->getBase();
4659  // If this is s.x, emit s as an lvalue. If it is s->x, emit s as a scalar.
4660  LValue BaseLV;
4661  if (E->isArrow()) {
4662  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4663  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4664  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(BaseExpr, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4665  QualType PtrTy = BaseExpr->getType()->getPointeeType();
4666  SanitizerSet SkippedChecks;
4667  bool IsBaseCXXThis = IsWrappedCXXThis(BaseExpr);
4668  if (IsBaseCXXThis)
4669  SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Alignment, true);
4670  if (IsBaseCXXThis || isa<DeclRefExpr>(BaseExpr))
4671  SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Null, true);
4672  EmitTypeCheck(TCK_MemberAccess, E->getExprLoc(), Addr, PtrTy,
4673  /*Alignment=*/CharUnits::Zero(), SkippedChecks);
4674  BaseLV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, PtrTy, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4675  } else
4676  BaseLV = EmitCheckedLValue(BaseExpr, TCK_MemberAccess);
4677 
4678  NamedDecl *ND = E->getMemberDecl();
4679  if (auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ND)) {
4680  LValue LV = EmitLValueForField(BaseLV, Field);
4681  setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
4682  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP) {
4683  // If the member was explicitly marked as nontemporal, mark it as
4684  // nontemporal. If the base lvalue is marked as nontemporal, mark access
4685  // to children as nontemporal too.
4686  if ((IsWrappedCXXThis(BaseExpr) &&
4687  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().isNontemporalDecl(Field)) ||
4688  BaseLV.isNontemporal())
4689  LV.setNontemporal(/*Value=*/true);
4690  }
4691  return LV;
4692  }
4693 
4694  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND))
4695  return EmitFunctionDeclLValue(*this, E, FD);
4696 
4697  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled member declaration!");
4698 }
4699 
4700 /// Given that we are currently emitting a lambda, emit an l-value for
4701 /// one of its members.
4702 ///
4703 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForLambdaField(const FieldDecl *Field,
4704  llvm::Value *ThisValue) {
4705  bool HasExplicitObjectParameter = false;
4706  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast_if_present<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl)) {
4707  HasExplicitObjectParameter = MD->isExplicitObjectMemberFunction();
4708  assert(MD->getParent()->isLambda());
4709  assert(MD->getParent() == Field->getParent());
4710  }
4711  LValue LambdaLV;
4712  if (HasExplicitObjectParameter) {
4713  const VarDecl *D = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl)->getParamDecl(0);
4714  auto It = LocalDeclMap.find(D);
4715  assert(It != LocalDeclMap.end() && "explicit parameter not loaded?");
4716  Address AddrOfExplicitObject = It->getSecond();
4717  if (D->getType()->isReferenceType())
4718  LambdaLV = EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(AddrOfExplicitObject, D->getType(),
4719  AlignmentSource::Decl);
4720  else
4721  LambdaLV = MakeAddrLValue(AddrOfExplicitObject,
4722  D->getType().getNonReferenceType());
4723  } else {
4724  QualType LambdaTagType = getContext().getTagDeclType(Field->getParent());
4725  LambdaLV = MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(ThisValue, LambdaTagType);
4726  }
4727  return EmitLValueForField(LambdaLV, Field);
4728 }
4729 
4730 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForLambdaField(const FieldDecl *Field) {
4731  return EmitLValueForLambdaField(Field, CXXABIThisValue);
4732 }
4733 
4734 /// Get the field index in the debug info. The debug info structure/union
4735 /// will ignore the unnamed bitfields.
4736 unsigned CodeGenFunction::getDebugInfoFIndex(const RecordDecl *Rec,
4737  unsigned FieldIndex) {
4738  unsigned I = 0, Skipped = 0;
4739 
4740  for (auto *F : Rec->getDefinition()->fields()) {
4741  if (I == FieldIndex)
4742  break;
4743  if (F->isUnnamedBitField())
4744  Skipped++;
4745  I++;
4746  }
4747 
4748  return FieldIndex - Skipped;
4749 }
