4751 /// Get the address of a zero-sized field within a record. The resulting
4752 /// address doesn't necessarily have the right type.
4753 static Address emitAddrOfZeroSizeField(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Base,
4754  const FieldDecl *Field) {
4755  CharUnits Offset = CGF.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(
4756  CGF.getContext().getFieldOffset(Field));
4757  if (Offset.isZero())
4758  return Base;
4759  Base = Base.withElementType(CGF.Int8Ty);
4760  return CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Base, Offset);
4761 }
4762 
4763 /// Drill down to the storage of a field without walking into
4764 /// reference types.
4765 ///
4766 /// The resulting address doesn't necessarily have the right type.
4767 static Address emitAddrOfFieldStorage(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address base,
4768  const FieldDecl *field) {
4769  if (field->isZeroSize(CGF.getContext()))
4770  return emitAddrOfZeroSizeField(CGF, base, field);
4771 
4772  const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4773 
4774  unsigned idx =
4775  CGF.CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(rec).getLLVMFieldNo(field);
4776 
4777  return CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(base, idx, field->getName());
4778 }
4779 
4780 static Address emitPreserveStructAccess(CodeGenFunction &CGF, LValue base,
4781  Address addr, const FieldDecl *field) {
4782  const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4783  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = CGF.getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateStandaloneType(
4784  base.getType(), rec->getLocation());
4785 
4786  unsigned idx =
4787  CGF.CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(rec).getLLVMFieldNo(field);
4788 
4789  return CGF.Builder.CreatePreserveStructAccessIndex(
4790  addr, idx, CGF.getDebugInfoFIndex(rec, field->getFieldIndex()), DbgInfo);
4791 }
4792 
4793 static bool hasAnyVptr(const QualType Type, const ASTContext &Context) {
4794  const auto *RD = Type.getTypePtr()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4795  if (!RD)
4796  return false;
4797 
4798  if (RD->isDynamicClass())
4799  return true;
4800 
4801  for (const auto &Base : RD->bases())
4802  if (hasAnyVptr(Base.getType(), Context))
4803  return true;
4804 
4805  for (const FieldDecl *Field : RD->fields())
4806  if (hasAnyVptr(Field->getType(), Context))
4807  return true;
4808 
4809  return false;
4810 }
4811 
4812 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForField(LValue base,
4813  const FieldDecl *field) {
4814  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo = base.getBaseInfo();
4815 
4816  if (field->isBitField()) {
4817  const CGRecordLayout &RL =
4818  CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(field->getParent());
4819  const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = RL.getBitFieldInfo(field);
4820  const bool UseVolatile = isAAPCS(CGM.getTarget()) &&
4821  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().AAPCSBitfieldWidth &&
4822  Info.VolatileStorageSize != 0 &&
4823  field->getType()
4824  .withCVRQualifiers(base.getVRQualifiers())
4825  .isVolatileQualified();
4826  Address Addr = base.getAddress(*this);
4827  unsigned Idx = RL.getLLVMFieldNo(field);
4828  const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4829  if (hasBPFPreserveStaticOffset(rec))
4830  Addr = wrapWithBPFPreserveStaticOffset(*this, Addr);
4831  if (!UseVolatile) {
4832  if (!IsInPreservedAIRegion &&
4833  (!getDebugInfo() || !rec->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>())) {
4834  if (Idx != 0)
4835  // For structs, we GEP to the field that the record layout suggests.
4836  Addr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(Addr, Idx, field->getName());
4837  } else {
4838  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateRecordType(
4839  getContext().getRecordType(rec), rec->getLocation());
4840  Addr = Builder.CreatePreserveStructAccessIndex(
4841  Addr, Idx, getDebugInfoFIndex(rec, field->getFieldIndex()),
4842  DbgInfo);
4843  }
4844  }
4845  const unsigned SS =
4846  UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileStorageSize : Info.StorageSize;
4847  // Get the access type.
4848  llvm::Type *FieldIntTy = llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getLLVMContext(), SS);
4849  Addr = Addr.withElementType(FieldIntTy);
4850  if (UseVolatile) {
4851  const unsigned VolatileOffset = Info.VolatileStorageOffset.getQuantity();
4852  if (VolatileOffset)
4853  Addr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP(Addr, VolatileOffset);
4854  }
4855 
4856  QualType fieldType =
4857  field->getType().withCVRQualifiers(base.getVRQualifiers());
4858  // TODO: Support TBAA for bit fields.
4859  LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource());
4860  return LValue::MakeBitfield(Addr, Info, fieldType, FieldBaseInfo,
4861  TBAAAccessInfo());
4862  }
4863 
4864  // Fields of may-alias structures are may-alias themselves.
4865  // FIXME: this should get propagated down through anonymous structs
4866  // and unions.
4867  QualType FieldType = field->getType();
4868  const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4869  AlignmentSource BaseAlignSource = BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource();
4870  LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(getFieldAlignmentSource(BaseAlignSource));
4871  TBAAAccessInfo FieldTBAAInfo;
4872  if (base.getTBAAInfo().isMayAlias() ||
4873  rec->hasAttr<MayAliasAttr>() || FieldType->isVectorType()) {
4874  FieldTBAAInfo = TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo();
4875  } else if (rec->isUnion()) {
4876  // TODO: Support TBAA for unions.
4877  FieldTBAAInfo = TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo();
4878  } else {
4879  // If no base type been assigned for the base access, then try to generate
4880  // one for this base lvalue.
4881  FieldTBAAInfo = base.getTBAAInfo();
4882  if (!FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType) {
4883  FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType = CGM.getTBAABaseTypeInfo(base.getType());
4884  assert(!FieldTBAAInfo.Offset &&
4885  "Nonzero offset for an access with no base type!");
4886  }
4887 
4888  // Adjust offset to be relative to the base type.
4889  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
4890  getContext().getASTRecordLayout(field->getParent());
4891  unsigned CharWidth = getContext().getCharWidth();
4892  if (FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType)
4893  FieldTBAAInfo.Offset +=
4894  Layout.getFieldOffset(field->getFieldIndex()) / CharWidth;
4895 
4896  // Update the final access type and size.
4897  FieldTBAAInfo.AccessType = CGM.getTBAATypeInfo(FieldType);
4898  FieldTBAAInfo.Size =
4899  getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(FieldType).getQuantity();
4900  }
4901 
4902  Address addr = base.getAddress(*this);
4903  if (hasBPFPreserveStaticOffset(rec))
4904  addr = wrapWithBPFPreserveStaticOffset(*this, addr);
4905  if (auto *ClassDef = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(rec)) {
4906  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4907  ClassDef->isDynamicClass()) {
4908  // Getting to any field of dynamic object requires stripping dynamic
4909  // information provided by invariant.group. This is because accessing
4910  // fields may leak the real address of dynamic object, which could result
4911  // in miscompilation when leaked pointer would be compared.
4912  auto *stripped =
4913  Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(addr.emitRawPointer(*this));
4914  addr = Address(stripped, addr.getElementType(), addr.getAlignment());
4915  }
4916  }
4917 
4918  unsigned RecordCVR = base.getVRQualifiers();
4919  if (rec->isUnion()) {
4920  // For unions, there is no pointer adjustment.
4921  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4922  hasAnyVptr(FieldType, getContext()))
4923  // Because unions can easily skip invariant.barriers, we need to add
4924  // a barrier every time CXXRecord field with vptr is referenced.
4925  addr = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(addr);
4926 
4927  if (IsInPreservedAIRegion ||
4928  (getDebugInfo() && rec->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>())) {
4929  // Remember the original union field index
4930  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateStandaloneType(base.getType(),
4931  rec->getLocation());
4932  addr =
4933  Address(Builder.CreatePreserveUnionAccessIndex(
4934  addr.emitRawPointer(*this),
4935  getDebugInfoFIndex(rec, field->getFieldIndex()), DbgInfo),
4936  addr.getElementType(), addr.getAlignment());
4937  }
4938 
4939  if (FieldType->isReferenceType())
4940  addr = addr.withElementType(CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(FieldType));
4941  } else {
4942  if (!IsInPreservedAIRegion &&
4943  (!getDebugInfo() || !rec->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>()))
4944  // For structs, we GEP to the field that the record layout suggests.
4945  addr = emitAddrOfFieldStorage(*this, addr, field);
4946  else
4947  // Remember the original struct field index
4948  addr = emitPreserveStructAccess(*this, base, addr, field);
4949  }
4950 
4951  // If this is a reference field, load the reference right now.
4952  if (FieldType->isReferenceType()) {
4953  LValue RefLVal =
4954  MakeAddrLValue(addr, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo, FieldTBAAInfo);
4955  if (RecordCVR & Qualifiers::Volatile)
4956  RefLVal.getQuals().addVolatile();
4957  addr = EmitLoadOfReference(RefLVal, &FieldBaseInfo, &FieldTBAAInfo);
4958 
4959  // Qualifiers on the struct don't apply to the referencee.
4960  RecordCVR = 0;
4961  FieldType = FieldType->getPointeeType();
4962  }
4963 
4964  // Make sure that the address is pointing to the right type. This is critical
4965  // for both unions and structs.
4966  addr = addr.withElementType(CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(FieldType));
4967 
4968  if (field->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>())
4969  addr = EmitFieldAnnotations(field, addr);
4970 
4971  // Emit attribute annotation for a field.
4972  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
4973  if (field->hasAttr<SYCLAddIRAnnotationsMemberAttr>())
4974  addr = EmitFieldSYCLAnnotations(field, addr);
4975 
4976  SmallString<256> AnnotStr;
4977  CGM.generateIntelFPGAAnnotation(field, AnnotStr);
4978  if (!AnnotStr.empty())
4979  addr = EmitIntelFPGAFieldAnnotations(field, addr, AnnotStr);
4980  }
4981 
4982  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(addr, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo, FieldTBAAInfo);
4983  LV.getQuals().addCVRQualifiers(RecordCVR);
4984 
4985  // __weak attribute on a field is ignored.
4986  if (LV.getQuals().getObjCGCAttr() == Qualifiers::Weak)
4987  LV.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
4988 
4989  return LV;
4990 }
4991 
4992 LValue
4993 CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(LValue Base,
4994  const FieldDecl *Field) {
4995  QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
4996 
4997  if (!FieldType->isReferenceType())
4998  return EmitLValueForField(Base, Field);
4999 
5000  Address V = emitAddrOfFieldStorage(*this, Base.getAddress(*this), Field);
5001 
5002  // Make sure that the address is pointing to the right type.
5003  llvm::Type *llvmType = ConvertTypeForMem(FieldType);
5004  V = V.withElementType(llvmType);
5005 
5006  // TODO: Generate TBAA information that describes this access as a structure
5007  // member access and not just an access to an object of the field's type. This
5008  // should be similar to what we do in EmitLValueForField().
5009  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo = Base.getBaseInfo();
5010  AlignmentSource FieldAlignSource = BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource();
5011  LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(getFieldAlignmentSource(FieldAlignSource));
5012  return MakeAddrLValue(V, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo,
5013  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(Base, FieldType));
5014 }
5015 
5016 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCompoundLiteralLValue(const CompoundLiteralExpr *E){
5017  if (E->isFileScope()) {
5018  ConstantAddress GlobalPtr = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCompoundLiteral(E);
5019  return MakeAddrLValue(GlobalPtr, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
5020  }
5021  if (E->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType())
5022  // make sure to emit the VLA size.
5023  EmitVariablyModifiedType(E->getType());
5024 
5025  Address DeclPtr = CreateMemTemp(E->getType(), ".compoundliteral");
5026  const Expr *InitExpr = E->getInitializer();
5027  LValue Result = MakeAddrLValue(DeclPtr, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
5028 
5029  EmitAnyExprToMem(InitExpr, DeclPtr, E->getType().getQualifiers(),
5030  /*Init*/ true);
5031 
5032  // Block-scope compound literals are destroyed at the end of the enclosing
5033  // scope in C.
5034  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
5035  if (QualType::DestructionKind DtorKind = E->getType().isDestructedType())
5036  pushLifetimeExtendedDestroy(getCleanupKind(DtorKind), DeclPtr,
5037  E->getType(), getDestroyer(DtorKind),
5038  DtorKind & EHCleanup);
5039 
5040  return Result;
5041 }

5043 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitInitListLValue(const InitListExpr *E) {
5044  if (!E->isGLValue())
5045  // Initializing an aggregate temporary in C++11: T{...}.
5046  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5047 
5048  // An lvalue initializer list must be initializing a reference.
5049  assert(E->isTransparent() && "non-transparent glvalue init list");
5050  return EmitLValue(E->getInit(0));
5051 }

5053 /// Emit the operand of a glvalue conditional operator. This is either a glvalue
5054 /// or a (possibly-parenthesized) throw-expression. If this is a throw, no
5055 /// LValue is returned and the current block has been terminated.
5056 static std::optional<LValue> EmitLValueOrThrowExpression(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5057  const Expr *Operand) {
5058  if (auto *ThrowExpr = dyn_cast<CXXThrowExpr>(Operand->IgnoreParens())) {
5059  CGF.EmitCXXThrowExpr(ThrowExpr, /*KeepInsertionPoint*/false);
5060  return std::nullopt;
5061  }
5062 
5063  return CGF.EmitLValue(Operand);
5064 }
5065 
5066 namespace {
5067 // Handle the case where the condition is a constant evaluatable simple integer,
5068 // which means we don't have to separately handle the true/false blocks.
5069 std::optional<LValue> HandleConditionalOperatorLValueSimpleCase(
5070  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const AbstractConditionalOperator *E) {
5071  const Expr *condExpr = E->getCond();
5072  bool CondExprBool;
5073  if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(condExpr, CondExprBool)) {
5074  const Expr *Live = E->getTrueExpr(), *Dead = E->getFalseExpr();
5075  if (!CondExprBool)
5076  std::swap(Live, Dead);
5077 
5078  if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(Dead)) {
5079  // If the true case is live, we need to track its region.
5080  if (CondExprBool)
5081  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5082  // If a throw expression we emit it and return an undefined lvalue
5083  // because it can't be used.
5084  if (auto *ThrowExpr = dyn_cast<CXXThrowExpr>(Live->IgnoreParens())) {
5085  CGF.EmitCXXThrowExpr(ThrowExpr);
5086  llvm::Type *ElemTy = CGF.ConvertType(Dead->getType());
5087  llvm::Type *Ty = CGF.UnqualPtrTy;
5088  return CGF.MakeAddrLValue(
5089  Address(llvm::UndefValue::get(Ty), ElemTy, CharUnits::One()),
5090  Dead->getType());
5091  }
5092  return CGF.EmitLValue(Live);
5093  }
5094  }
5095  return std::nullopt;
5096 }
5097 struct ConditionalInfo {
5098  llvm::BasicBlock *lhsBlock, *rhsBlock;
5099  std::optional<LValue> LHS, RHS;
5100 };
5101 
5102 // Create and generate the 3 blocks for a conditional operator.
5103 // Leaves the 'current block' in the continuation basic block.
5104 template<typename FuncTy>
5105 ConditionalInfo EmitConditionalBlocks(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5106  const AbstractConditionalOperator *E,
5107  const FuncTy &BranchGenFunc) {
5108  ConditionalInfo Info{CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.true"),
5109  CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.false"), std::nullopt,
5110  std::nullopt};
5111  llvm::BasicBlock *endBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.end");
5112 
5113  CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
5114  CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(E->getCond(), Info.lhsBlock, Info.rhsBlock,
5115  CGF.getProfileCount(E));
5116 
5117  // Any temporaries created here are conditional.
5118  CGF.EmitBlock(Info.lhsBlock);
5119  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5120  eval.begin(CGF);
5121  Info.LHS = BranchGenFunc(CGF, E->getTrueExpr());
5122  eval.end(CGF);
5123  Info.lhsBlock = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
5124 
5125  if (Info.LHS)
5126  CGF.Builder.CreateBr(endBlock);
5127 
5128  // Any temporaries created here are conditional.
5129  CGF.EmitBlock(Info.rhsBlock);
5130  eval.begin(CGF);
5131  Info.RHS = BranchGenFunc(CGF, E->getFalseExpr());
5132  eval.end(CGF);
5133  Info.rhsBlock = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
5134  CGF.EmitBlock(endBlock);
5135 
5136  return Info;
5137 }
5138 } // namespace
5139 
5140 void CodeGenFunction::EmitIgnoredConditionalOperator(
5141  const AbstractConditionalOperator *E) {
5142  if (!E->isGLValue()) {
5143  // ?: here should be an aggregate.
5144  assert(hasAggregateEvaluationKind(E->getType()) &&
5145  "Unexpected conditional operator!");
5146  return (void)EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5147  }
5148 
5149  OpaqueValueMapping binding(*this, E);
5150  if (HandleConditionalOperatorLValueSimpleCase(*this, E))
5151  return;
5152 
5153  EmitConditionalBlocks(*this, E, [](CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E) {
5154  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E);
5155  return LValue{};
5156  });
5157 }
5158 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(
5159  const AbstractConditionalOperator *expr) {
5160  if (!expr->isGLValue()) {
5161  // ?: here should be an aggregate.
5162  assert(hasAggregateEvaluationKind(expr->getType()) &&
5163  "Unexpected conditional operator!");
5164  return EmitAggExprToLValue(expr);
5165  }
5166 
5167  OpaqueValueMapping binding(*this, expr);
5168  if (std::optional<LValue> Res =
5169  HandleConditionalOperatorLValueSimpleCase(*this, expr))
5170  return *Res;
5171 
5172  ConditionalInfo Info = EmitConditionalBlocks(
5173  *this, expr, [](CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E) {
5174  return EmitLValueOrThrowExpression(CGF, E);
5175  });
5176 
5177  if ((Info.LHS && !Info.LHS->isSimple()) ||
5178  (Info.RHS && !Info.RHS->isSimple()))
5179  return EmitUnsupportedLValue(expr, "conditional operator");
5180 
5181  if (Info.LHS && Info.RHS) {
5182  Address lhsAddr = Info.LHS->getAddress(*this);
5183  Address rhsAddr = Info.RHS->getAddress(*this);
5184  Address result = mergeAddressesInConditionalExpr(
5185  lhsAddr, rhsAddr, Info.lhsBlock, Info.rhsBlock,
5186  Builder.GetInsertBlock(), expr->getType());
5187  AlignmentSource alignSource =
5188  std::max(Info.LHS->getBaseInfo().getAlignmentSource(),
5189  Info.RHS->getBaseInfo().getAlignmentSource());
5190  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo = CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForConditionalOperator(
5191  Info.LHS->getTBAAInfo(), Info.RHS->getTBAAInfo());
5192  return MakeAddrLValue(result, expr->getType(), LValueBaseInfo(alignSource),
5193  TBAAInfo);
5194  } else {
5195  assert((Info.LHS || Info.RHS) &&
5196  "both operands of glvalue conditional are throw-expressions?");
5197  return Info.LHS ? *Info.LHS : *Info.RHS;
5198  }
5199 }
5200 
5201 /// EmitCastLValue - Casts are never lvalues unless that cast is to a reference
5202 /// type. If the cast is to a reference, we can have the usual lvalue result,
5203 /// otherwise if a cast is needed by the code generator in an lvalue context,
5204 /// then it must mean that we need the address of an aggregate in order to
5205 /// access one of its members. This can happen for all the reasons that casts
5206 /// are permitted with aggregate result, including noop aggregate casts, and
5207 /// cast from scalar to union.
5208 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCastLValue(const CastExpr *E) {
5209  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
5210  case CK_ToVoid:
5211  case CK_BitCast:
5212  case CK_LValueToRValueBitCast:
5213  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
5214  case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
5215  case CK_NullToMemberPointer:
5216  case CK_NullToPointer:
5217  case CK_IntegralToPointer:
5218  case CK_PointerToIntegral:
5219  case CK_PointerToBoolean:
5220  case CK_IntegralCast:
5221  case CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral:
5222  case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
5223  case CK_IntegralToFloating:
5224  case CK_FloatingToIntegral:
5225  case CK_FloatingToBoolean:
5226  case CK_FloatingCast:
5227  case CK_FloatingRealToComplex:
5228  case CK_FloatingComplexToReal:
5229  case CK_FloatingComplexToBoolean:
5230  case CK_FloatingComplexCast:
5231  case CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex:
5232  case CK_IntegralRealToComplex:
5233  case CK_IntegralComplexToReal:
5234  case CK_IntegralComplexToBoolean:
5235  case CK_IntegralComplexCast:
5236  case CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex:
5237  case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer:
5238  case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer:
5239  case CK_MemberPointerToBoolean:
5240  case CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer:
5241  case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
5242  case CK_ARCProduceObject:
5243  case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
5244  case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
5245  case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
5246  case CK_CopyAndAutoreleaseBlockObject:
5247  case CK_IntToOCLSampler:
5248  case CK_FloatingToFixedPoint:
5249  case CK_FixedPointToFloating:
5250  case CK_FixedPointCast:
5251  case CK_FixedPointToBoolean:
5252  case CK_FixedPointToIntegral:
5253  case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint:
5254  case CK_MatrixCast:
5255  case CK_HLSLVectorTruncation:
5256  case CK_HLSLArrayRValue:
5257  return EmitUnsupportedLValue(E, "unexpected cast lvalue");
5258 
5259  case CK_Dependent:
5260  llvm_unreachable("dependent cast kind in IR gen!");
5261 
5262  case CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr:
5263  llvm_unreachable("builtin functions are handled elsewhere");
5264 
5265  // These are never l-values; just use the aggregate emission code.
5266  case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
5267  case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
5268  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5269 
5270  case CK_Dynamic: {
5271  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5272  Address V = LV.getAddress(*this);
5273  const auto *DCE = cast<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(E);
5274  return MakeNaturalAlignRawAddrLValue(EmitDynamicCast(V, DCE), E->getType());
5275  }
5276 
5277  case CK_ConstructorConversion:
5278  case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
5279  case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
5280  case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
5281  case CK_LValueToRValue:
5282  return EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5283 
5284  case CK_NoOp: {
5285  // CK_NoOp can model a qualification conversion, which can remove an array
5286  // bound and change the IR type.
5287  // FIXME: Once pointee types are removed from IR, remove this.
5288  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5289  // Propagate the volatile qualifer to LValue, if exist in E.
5290  if (E->changesVolatileQualification())
5291  LV.getQuals() = E->getType().getQualifiers();
5292  if (LV.isSimple()) {
5293  Address V = LV.getAddress(*this);
5294  if (V.isValid()) {
5295  llvm::Type *T = ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType());
5296  if (V.getElementType() != T)
5297  LV.setAddress(V.withElementType(T));
5298  }
5299  }
5300  return LV;
5301  }
5302 
5303  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
5304  case CK_DerivedToBase: {
5305  const auto *DerivedClassTy =
5306  E->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<RecordType>();
5307  auto *DerivedClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DerivedClassTy->getDecl());
5308 
5309  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5310  Address This = LV.getAddress(*this);
5311 
5312  // Perform the derived-to-base conversion
5313  Address Base = GetAddressOfBaseClass(
5314  This, DerivedClassDecl, E->path_begin(), E->path_end(),
5315  /*NullCheckValue=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
5316 
5317  // TODO: Support accesses to members of base classes in TBAA. For now, we
5318  // conservatively pretend that the complete object is of the base class
5319  // type.
5320  return MakeAddrLValue(Base, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
5321  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
5322  }
5323  case CK_ToUnion:
5324  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5325  case CK_BaseToDerived: {
5326  const auto *DerivedClassTy = E->getType()->castAs<RecordType>();
5327  auto *DerivedClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DerivedClassTy->getDecl());
5328 
5329  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5330 
5331  // Perform the base-to-derived conversion
5332  Address Derived = GetAddressOfDerivedClass(
5333  LV.getAddress(*this), DerivedClassDecl, E->path_begin(), E->path_end(),
5334  /*NullCheckValue=*/false);
5335 
5336  // C++11 [expr.static.cast]p2: Behavior is undefined if a downcast is
5337  // performed and the object is not of the derived type.
5338  if (sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
5339  EmitTypeCheck(TCK_DowncastReference, E->getExprLoc(), Derived,
5340  E->getType());
5341 
5342  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast))
5343  EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(E->getType(), Derived,
5344  /*MayBeNull=*/false, CFITCK_DerivedCast,
5345  E->getBeginLoc());
5346 
5347  return MakeAddrLValue(Derived, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
5348  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
5349  }
5350  case CK_LValueBitCast: {
5351  // This must be a reinterpret_cast (or c-style equivalent).
5352  const auto *CE = cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(E);
5353 
5354  CGM.EmitExplicitCastExprType(CE, this);
5355  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5356  Address V = LV.getAddress(*this).withElementType(
5357  ConvertTypeForMem(CE->getTypeAsWritten()->getPointeeType()));
5358 
5359  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast))
5360  EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(E->getType(), V,
5361  /*MayBeNull=*/false, CFITCK_UnrelatedCast,
5362  E->getBeginLoc());
5363 
5364  return MakeAddrLValue(V, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
5365  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
5366  }
5367  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion: {
5368  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5369  QualType DestTy = getContext().getPointerType(E->getType());
5370  llvm::Value *V = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
5371  *this, LV.getPointer(*this),
5372  E->getSubExpr()->getType().getAddressSpace(),
5373  E->getType().getAddressSpace(), ConvertType(DestTy));
5374  return MakeAddrLValue(Address(V, ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType()),
5375  LV.getAddress(*this).getAlignment()),
5376  E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(), LV.getTBAAInfo());
5377  }
5378  case CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast: {
5379  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5380  Address V = LV.getAddress(*this).withElementType(ConvertType(E->getType()));
5381  return MakeAddrLValue(V, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
5382  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
5383  }
5384  case CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType:
5385  llvm_unreachable("NULL to OpenCL opaque type lvalue cast is not valid");
5386 
5387  case CK_VectorSplat: {
5388  // LValue results of vector splats are only supported in HLSL.
5389  if (!getLangOpts().HLSL)
5390  return EmitUnsupportedLValue(E, "unexpected cast lvalue");
5391  return EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
5392  }
5393  }
5394 
5395  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled lvalue cast kind?");
5396 }
5397 
5398 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitOpaqueValueLValue(const OpaqueValueExpr *e) {
5399  assert(OpaqueValueMappingData::shouldBindAsLValue(e));
5400  return getOrCreateOpaqueLValueMapping(e);
5401 }
5402 
5403 LValue
5404 CodeGenFunction::getOrCreateOpaqueLValueMapping(const OpaqueValueExpr *e) {
5405  assert(OpaqueValueMapping::shouldBindAsLValue(e));
5406 
5407  llvm::DenseMap<const OpaqueValueExpr*,LValue>::iterator
5408  it = OpaqueLValues.find(e);
5409 
5410  if (it != OpaqueLValues.end())
5411  return it->second;
5412 
5413  assert(e->isUnique() && "LValue for a nonunique OVE hasn't been emitted");
5414  return EmitLValue(e->getSourceExpr());
5415 }
5416 
5417 RValue
5418 CodeGenFunction::getOrCreateOpaqueRValueMapping(const OpaqueValueExpr *e) {
5419  assert(!OpaqueValueMapping::shouldBindAsLValue(e));
5420 
5421  llvm::DenseMap<const OpaqueValueExpr*,RValue>::iterator
5422  it = OpaqueRValues.find(e);
5423 
5424  if (it != OpaqueRValues.end())
5425  return it->second;
5426 
5427  assert(e->isUnique() && "RValue for a nonunique OVE hasn't been emitted");
5428  return EmitAnyExpr(e->getSourceExpr());
5429 }
5430 
5431 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitRValueForField(LValue LV,
5432  const FieldDecl *FD,
5433  SourceLocation Loc) {
5434  QualType FT = FD->getType();
5435  LValue FieldLV = EmitLValueForField(LV, FD);
5436  switch (getEvaluationKind(FT)) {
5437  case TEK_Complex:
5438  return RValue::getComplex(EmitLoadOfComplex(FieldLV, Loc));
5439  case TEK_Aggregate:
5440  return FieldLV.asAggregateRValue(*this);
5441  case TEK_Scalar:
5442  // This routine is used to load fields one-by-one to perform a copy, so
5443  // don't load reference fields.
5444  if (FD->getType()->isReferenceType())
5445  return RValue::get(FieldLV.getPointer(*this));
5446  // Call EmitLoadOfScalar except when the lvalue is a bitfield to emit a
5447  // primitive load.
5448  if (FieldLV.isBitField())
5449  return EmitLoadOfLValue(FieldLV, Loc);
5450  return RValue::get(EmitLoadOfScalar(FieldLV, Loc));
5451  }
5452  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5453 }

5455 //===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5456 // Expression Emission
5457 //===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5458 
5459 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E,
5460  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
5461  // Builtins never have block type.
5462  if (E->getCallee()->getType()->isBlockPointerType())
5463  return EmitBlockCallExpr(E, ReturnValue);
5464 
5465  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CXXMemberCallExpr>(E))
5466  return EmitCXXMemberCallExpr(CE, ReturnValue);
5467 
5468  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CUDAKernelCallExpr>(E))
5469  return EmitCUDAKernelCallExpr(CE, ReturnValue);
5470 
5471  // A CXXOperatorCallExpr is created even for explicit object methods, but
5472  // these should be treated like static function call.
5473  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E))
5474  if (const auto *MD =
5475  dyn_cast_if_present<CXXMethodDecl>(CE->getCalleeDecl());
5476  MD && MD->isImplicitObjectMemberFunction())
5477  return EmitCXXOperatorMemberCallExpr(CE, MD, ReturnValue);
5478 
5479  CGCallee callee = EmitCallee(E->getCallee());
5480 
5481  if (callee.isBuiltin()) {
5482  return EmitBuiltinExpr(callee.getBuiltinDecl(), callee.getBuiltinID(),
5483  E, ReturnValue);
5484  }
5485 
5486  if (callee.isPseudoDestructor()) {
5487  return EmitCXXPseudoDestructorExpr(callee.getPseudoDestructorExpr());
5488  }
5489 
5490  return EmitCall(E->getCallee()->getType(), callee, E, ReturnValue);
5491 }
5492 
5493 /// Emit a CallExpr without considering whether it might be a subclass.
5494 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitSimpleCallExpr(const CallExpr *E,
5495  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
5496  CGCallee Callee = EmitCallee(E->getCallee());
5497  return EmitCall(E->getCallee()->getType(), Callee, E, ReturnValue);
5498 }
5499 
5500 // Detect the unusual situation where an inline version is shadowed by a
5501 // non-inline version. In that case we should pick the external one
5502 // everywhere. That's GCC behavior too.
5503 static bool OnlyHasInlineBuiltinDeclaration(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
5504  for (const FunctionDecl *PD = FD; PD; PD = PD->getPreviousDecl())
5505  if (!PD->isInlineBuiltinDeclaration())
5506  return false;
5507  return true;
5508 }
5509 
5510 static CGCallee EmitDirectCallee(CodeGenFunction &CGF, GlobalDecl GD) {
5511  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
5512 
5513  if (auto builtinID = FD->getBuiltinID()) {
5514  std::string NoBuiltinFD = ("no-builtin-" + FD->getName()).str();
5515  std::string NoBuiltins = "no-builtins";
5516 
5517  StringRef Ident = CGF.CGM.getMangledName(GD);
5518  std::string FDInlineName = (Ident + ".inline").str();
5519 
5520  bool IsPredefinedLibFunction =
5521  CGF.getContext().BuiltinInfo.isPredefinedLibFunction(builtinID);
5522  bool HasAttributeNoBuiltin =
5523  CGF.CurFn->getAttributes().hasFnAttr(NoBuiltinFD) ||
5524  CGF.CurFn->getAttributes().hasFnAttr(NoBuiltins);
5525 
5526  // When directing calling an inline builtin, call it through it's mangled
5527  // name to make it clear it's not the actual builtin.
5528  if (CGF.CurFn->getName() != FDInlineName &&
5529  OnlyHasInlineBuiltinDeclaration(FD)) {
5530  llvm::Constant *CalleePtr = EmitFunctionDeclPointer(CGF.CGM, GD);
5531  llvm::Function *Fn = llvm::cast<llvm::Function>(CalleePtr);
5532  llvm::Module *M = Fn->getParent();
5533  llvm::Function *Clone = M->getFunction(FDInlineName);
5534  if (!Clone) {
5535  Clone = llvm::Function::Create(Fn->getFunctionType(),
5536  llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
5537  Fn->getAddressSpace(), FDInlineName, M);
5538  Clone->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
5539  }
5540  return CGCallee::forDirect(Clone, GD);
5541  }
5542 
5543  // Replaceable builtins provide their own implementation of a builtin. If we
5544  // are in an inline builtin implementation, avoid trivial infinite
5545  // recursion. Honor __attribute__((no_builtin("foo"))) or
5546  // __attribute__((no_builtin)) on the current function unless foo is
5547  // not a predefined library function which means we must generate the
5548  // builtin no matter what.
5549  else if (!IsPredefinedLibFunction || !HasAttributeNoBuiltin)
5550  return CGCallee::forBuiltin(builtinID, FD);
5551  }
5552 
5553  llvm::Constant *CalleePtr = EmitFunctionDeclPointer(CGF.CGM, GD);
5554  if (CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA && !CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
5555  FD->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>())
5556  CalleePtr = CGF.CGM.getCUDARuntime().getKernelStub(
5557  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CalleePtr->stripPointerCasts()));
5558 
5559  return CGCallee::forDirect(CalleePtr, GD);
5560 }
5561 
5562 CGCallee CodeGenFunction::EmitCallee(const Expr *E) {
5563  E = E->IgnoreParens();
5564 
5565  // Look through function-to-pointer decay.
5566  if (auto ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
5567  if (ICE->getCastKind() == CK_FunctionToPointerDecay ||
5568  ICE->getCastKind() == CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr) {
5569  return EmitCallee(ICE->getSubExpr());
5570  }
5571 
5572  // Resolve direct calls.
5573  } else if (auto DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
5574  if (auto FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
5575  return EmitDirectCallee(*this, FD);
5576  }
5577  } else if (auto ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
5578  if (auto FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
5579  EmitIgnoredExpr(ME->getBase());
5580  return EmitDirectCallee(*this, FD);
5581  }
5582 
5583  // Look through template substitutions.
5584  } else if (auto NTTP = dyn_cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)) {
5585  return EmitCallee(NTTP->getReplacement());
5586 
5587  // Treat pseudo-destructor calls differently.
5588  } else if (auto PDE = dyn_cast<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(E)) {
5589  return CGCallee::forPseudoDestructor(PDE);
5590  }
5591 
5592  // Otherwise, we have an indirect reference.
5593  llvm::Value *calleePtr;
5594  QualType functionType;
5595  if (auto ptrType = E->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
5596  calleePtr = EmitScalarExpr(E);
5597  functionType = ptrType->getPointeeType();
5598  } else {
5599  functionType = E->getType();
5600  calleePtr = EmitLValue(E, KnownNonNull).getPointer(*this);
5601  }
5602  assert(functionType->isFunctionType());
5603 
5604  GlobalDecl GD;
5605  if (const auto *VD =
5606  dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(E->getReferencedDeclOfCallee()))
5607  GD = GlobalDecl(VD);
5608 
5609  CGCalleeInfo calleeInfo(functionType->getAs<FunctionProtoType>(), GD);
5610  CGCallee callee(calleeInfo, calleePtr);
5611  return callee;
5612 }
5613 
5614 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitBinaryOperatorLValue(const BinaryOperator *E) {
5615  // Comma expressions just emit their LHS then their RHS as an l-value.
5616  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
5617  EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getLHS());
5618  EnsureInsertPoint();
5619  return EmitLValue(E->getRHS());
5620  }
5621 
5622  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemD ||
5623  E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI)
5624  return EmitPointerToDataMemberBinaryExpr(E);
5625 
5626  assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_Assign && "unexpected binary l-value");
5627 
5628  // Note that in all of these cases, __block variables need the RHS
5629  // evaluated first just in case the variable gets moved by the RHS.
5630 
5631  switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
5632  case TEK_Scalar: {
5633  switch (E->getLHS()->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
5634  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
5635  return EmitARCStoreStrong(E, /*ignored*/ false).first;
5636 
5637  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
5638  return EmitARCStoreAutoreleasing(E).first;
5639 
5640  // No reason to do any of these differently.
5641  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
5642  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
5643  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
5644  break;
5645  }
5646 
5647  // TODO: Can we de-duplicate this code with the corresponding code in
5648  // CGExprScalar, similar to the way EmitCompoundAssignmentLValue works?
5649  RValue RV;
5650  llvm::Value *Previous = nullptr;
5651  QualType SrcType = E->getRHS()->getType();
5652  // Check if LHS is a bitfield, if RHS contains an implicit cast expression
5653  // we want to extract that value and potentially (if the bitfield sanitizer
5654  // is enabled) use it to check for an implicit conversion.
5655  if (E->getLHS()->refersToBitField()) {
5656  llvm::Value *RHS =
5657  EmitWithOriginalRHSBitfieldAssignment(E, &Previous, &SrcType);
5658  RV = RValue::get(RHS);
5659  } else
5660  RV = EmitAnyExpr(E->getRHS());
5661 
5662  LValue LV = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), TCK_Store);
5663 
5664  if (RV.isScalar())
5665  EmitNullabilityCheck(LV, RV.getScalarVal(), E->getExprLoc());
5666 
5667  if (LV.isBitField()) {
5668  llvm::Value *Result = nullptr;
5669  // If bitfield sanitizers are enabled we want to use the result
5670  // to check whether a truncation or sign change has occurred.
5671  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ImplicitBitfieldConversion))
5672  EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RV, LV, &Result);
5673  else
5674  EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RV, LV);
5675 
5676  // If the expression contained an implicit conversion, make sure
5677  // to use the value before the scalar conversion.
5678  llvm::Value *Src = Previous ? Previous : RV.getScalarVal();
5679  QualType DstType = E->getLHS()->getType();
5680  EmitBitfieldConversionCheck(Src, SrcType, Result, DstType,
5681  LV.getBitFieldInfo(), E->getExprLoc());
5682  } else
5683  EmitStoreThroughLValue(RV, LV);
5684 
5685  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP)
5686  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().checkAndEmitLastprivateConditional(*this,
5687  E->getLHS());
5688  return LV;
5689  }
5690 
5691  case TEK_Complex:
5692  return EmitComplexAssignmentLValue(E);
5693 
5694  case TEK_Aggregate:
5695  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5696  }
5697  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5698 }
5699

5705  AlignmentSource::Decl);
5706 
5707  assert(E->getCallReturnType(getContext())->isReferenceType() &&
5708  "Can't have a scalar return unless the return type is a "
5709  "reference type!");
5710 
5711  return MakeNaturalAlignPointeeAddrLValue(RV.getScalarVal(), E->getType());
5712 }

5793 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCIvarRefLValue(const ObjCIvarRefExpr *E) {

5795  llvm::Value *BaseValue = nullptr;

5807  BaseQuals = ObjectTy.getQualifiers();
5808  }

5811  EmitLValueForIvar(ObjectTy, BaseValue, E->getDecl(),
5812  BaseQuals.getCVRQualifiers());

5823 
5824 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCall(QualType CalleeType, const CGCallee &OrigCallee,
5825  const CallExpr *E, ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
5826  llvm::Value *Chain) {
5827  // Get the actual function type. The callee type will always be a pointer to
5828  // function type or a block pointer type.
5829  assert(CalleeType->isFunctionPointerType() &&
5830  "Call must have function pointer type!");
5831 
5832  const Decl *TargetDecl =
5833  OrigCallee.getAbstractInfo().getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
5834 
5835  assert((!isa_and_present<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl) ||
5836  !cast<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)->isImmediateFunction()) &&
5837  "trying to emit a call to an immediate function");
5838 
5839  CalleeType = getContext().getCanonicalType(CalleeType);
5840 
5841  auto PointeeType = cast<PointerType>(CalleeType)->getPointeeType();
5842 
5843  CGCallee Callee = OrigCallee;
5844 
5845  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Function) &&
5846  (!TargetDecl || !isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) &&
5847  !isa<FunctionNoProtoType>(PointeeType)) {
5848  if (llvm::Constant *PrefixSig =
5849  CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getUBSanFunctionSignature(CGM)) {
5850  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5851  auto *TypeHash = getUBSanFunctionTypeHash(PointeeType);
5852 
5853  llvm::Type *PrefixSigType = PrefixSig->getType();
5854  llvm::StructType *PrefixStructTy = llvm::StructType::get(
5855  CGM.getLLVMContext(), {PrefixSigType, Int32Ty}, /*isPacked=*/true);
5856 
5857  llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5858 
5859  // On 32-bit Arm, the low bit of a function pointer indicates whether
5860  // it's using the Arm or Thumb instruction set. The actual first
5861  // instruction lives at the same address either way, so we must clear
5862  // that low bit before using the function address to find the prefix
5863  // structure.
5864  //
5865  // This applies to both Arm and Thumb target triples, because
5866  // either one could be used in an interworking context where it
5867  // might be passed function pointers of both types.
5868  llvm::Value *AlignedCalleePtr;
5869  if (CGM.getTriple().isARM() || CGM.getTriple().isThumb()) {
5870  llvm::Value *CalleeAddress =
5871  Builder.CreatePtrToInt(CalleePtr, IntPtrTy);
5872  llvm::Value *Mask = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ~1);
5873  llvm::Value *AlignedCalleeAddress =
5874  Builder.CreateAnd(CalleeAddress, Mask);
5875  AlignedCalleePtr =
5876  Builder.CreateIntToPtr(AlignedCalleeAddress, CalleePtr->getType());
5877  } else {
5878  AlignedCalleePtr = CalleePtr;
5879  }
5880 
5881  llvm::Value *CalleePrefixStruct = AlignedCalleePtr;
5882  llvm::Value *CalleeSigPtr =
5883  Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(PrefixStructTy, CalleePrefixStruct, -1, 0);
5884  llvm::Value *CalleeSig =
5885  Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(PrefixSigType, CalleeSigPtr, getIntAlign());
5886  llvm::Value *CalleeSigMatch = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CalleeSig, PrefixSig);
5887 
5888  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
5889  llvm::BasicBlock *TypeCheck = createBasicBlock("typecheck");
5890  Builder.CreateCondBr(CalleeSigMatch, TypeCheck, Cont);
5891 
5892  EmitBlock(TypeCheck);
5893  llvm::Value *CalleeTypeHash = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
5894  Int32Ty,
5895  Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(PrefixStructTy, CalleePrefixStruct, -1, 1),
5896  getPointerAlign());
5897  llvm::Value *CalleeTypeHashMatch =
5898  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CalleeTypeHash, TypeHash);
5899  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getBeginLoc()),
5900  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(CalleeType)};
5901  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(CalleeTypeHashMatch, SanitizerKind::Function),
5902  SanitizerHandler::FunctionTypeMismatch, StaticData,
5903  {CalleePtr});
5904 
5905  Builder.CreateBr(Cont);
5906  EmitBlock(Cont);
5907  }
5908  }
5909 
5910  const auto *FnType = cast<FunctionType>(PointeeType);
5911 
5912  // If we are checking indirect calls and this call is indirect, check that the
5913  // function pointer is a member of the bit set for the function type.
5914  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIICall) &&
5915  (!TargetDecl || !isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))) {
5916  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5917  EmitSanitizerStatReport(llvm::SanStat_CFI_ICall);
5918 
5919  llvm::Metadata *MD;
5920  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiICallGeneralizePointers)
5921  MD = CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierGeneralized(QualType(FnType, 0));
5922  else
5923  MD = CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType(FnType, 0));
5924 
5925  llvm::Value *TypeId = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(getLLVMContext(), MD);
5926 
5927  llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5928  llvm::Value *TypeTest = Builder.CreateCall(
5929  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test), {CalleePtr, TypeId});
5930 
5931  auto CrossDsoTypeId = CGM.CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(MD);
5932  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
5933  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, CFITCK_ICall),
5934  EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getBeginLoc()),
5935  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType(FnType, 0)),
5936  };
5937  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiCrossDso && CrossDsoTypeId) {
5938  EmitCfiSlowPathCheck(SanitizerKind::CFIICall, TypeTest, CrossDsoTypeId,
5939  CalleePtr, StaticData);
5940  } else {
5941  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(TypeTest, SanitizerKind::CFIICall),
5942  SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, StaticData,
5943  {CalleePtr, llvm::UndefValue::get(IntPtrTy)});
5944  }
5945  }
5946 
5947  CallArgList Args;
5948  if (Chain)
5949  Args.add(RValue::get(Chain), CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
5950 
5951  // C++17 requires that we evaluate arguments to a call using assignment syntax
5952  // right-to-left, and that we evaluate arguments to certain other operators
5953  // left-to-right. Note that we allow this to override the order dictated by
5954  // the calling convention on the MS ABI, which means that parameter
5955  // destruction order is not necessarily reverse construction order.
5956  // FIXME: Revisit this based on C++ committee response to unimplementability.
5957  EvaluationOrder Order = EvaluationOrder::Default;
5958  bool StaticOperator = false;
5959  if (auto *OCE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E)) {
5960  if (OCE->isAssignmentOp())
5961  Order = EvaluationOrder::ForceRightToLeft;
5962  else {
5963  switch (OCE->getOperator()) {
5964  case OO_LessLess:
5965  case OO_GreaterGreater:
5966  case OO_AmpAmp:
5967  case OO_PipePipe:
5968  case OO_Comma:
5969  case OO_ArrowStar:
5970  Order = EvaluationOrder::ForceLeftToRight;
5971  break;
5972  default:
5973  break;
5974  }
5975  }
5976 
5977  if (const auto *MD =
5978  dyn_cast_if_present<CXXMethodDecl>(OCE->getCalleeDecl());
5979  MD && MD->isStatic())
5980  StaticOperator = true;
5981  }
5982 
5983  auto Arguments = E->arguments();
5984  if (StaticOperator) {
5985  // If we're calling a static operator, we need to emit the object argument
5986  // and ignore it.
5987  EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getArg(0));
5988  Arguments = drop_begin(Arguments, 1);
5989  }
5990  EmitCallArgs(Args, dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType), Arguments,
5991  E->getDirectCallee(), /*ParamsToSkip=*/0, Order);
5992 
5993  const CGFunctionInfo &FnInfo = CGM.getTypes().arrangeFreeFunctionCall(
5994  Args, FnType, /*ChainCall=*/Chain);
5995 
5996  // C99 6.5.2.2p6:
5997  // If the expression that denotes the called function has a type
5998  // that does not include a prototype, [the default argument
5999  // promotions are performed]. If the number of arguments does not
6000  // equal the number of parameters, the behavior is undefined. If
6001  // the function is defined with a type that includes a prototype,
6002  // and either the prototype ends with an ellipsis (, ...) or the
6003  // types of the arguments after promotion are not compatible with
6004  // the types of the parameters, the behavior is undefined. If the
6005  // function is defined with a type that does not include a
6006  // prototype, and the types of the arguments after promotion are
6007  // not compatible with those of the parameters after promotion,
6008  // the behavior is undefined [except in some trivial cases].
6009  // That is, in the general case, we should assume that a call
6010  // through an unprototyped function type works like a *non-variadic*
6011  // call. The way we make this work is to cast to the exact type
6012  // of the promoted arguments.
6013  //
6014  // Chain calls use this same code path to add the invisible chain parameter
6015  // to the function type.
6016  if (isa<FunctionNoProtoType>(FnType) || Chain) {
6017  llvm::Type *CalleeTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
6018  int AS = Callee.getFunctionPointer()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
6019  CalleeTy = CalleeTy->getPointerTo(AS);
6020 
6021  llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
6022  CalleePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(CalleePtr, CalleeTy, "callee.knr.cast");
6023  Callee.setFunctionPointer(CalleePtr);
6024  }
6025 
6026  // HIP function pointer contains kernel handle when it is used in triple
6027  // chevron. The kernel stub needs to be loaded from kernel handle and used
6028  // as callee.
6029  if (CGM.getLangOpts().HIP && !CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
6030  isa<CUDAKernelCallExpr>(E) &&
6031  (!TargetDecl || !isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))) {
6032  llvm::Value *Handle = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
6033  auto *Stub = Builder.CreateLoad(
6034  Address(Handle, Handle->getType(), CGM.getPointerAlign()));
6035  Callee.setFunctionPointer(Stub);
6036  }
6037  llvm::CallBase *CallOrInvoke = nullptr;
6038  RValue Call = EmitCall(FnInfo, Callee, ReturnValue, Args, &CallOrInvoke,
6039  E == MustTailCall, E->getExprLoc());
6040 
6041  // Generate function declaration DISuprogram in order to be used
6042  // in debug info about call sites.
6043  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getDebugInfo()) {
6044  if (auto *CalleeDecl = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
6045  FunctionArgList Args;
6046  QualType ResTy = BuildFunctionArgList(CalleeDecl, Args);
6047  DI->EmitFuncDeclForCallSite(CallOrInvoke,
6048  DI->getFunctionType(CalleeDecl, ResTy, Args),
6049  CalleeDecl);
6050  }
6051  }
6052 
6053  return Call;
6054 }

6056 LValue CodeGenFunction::
6057 EmitPointerToDataMemberBinaryExpr(const BinaryOperator *E) {
6058  Address BaseAddr = Address::invalid();
6059  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI) {
6060  BaseAddr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getLHS());
6061  } else {
6062  BaseAddr = EmitLValue(E->getLHS()).getAddress(*this);
6063  }
6064 
6065  llvm::Value *OffsetV = EmitScalarExpr(E->getRHS());
6066  const auto *MPT = E->getRHS()->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
6067 
6068  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
6069  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
6070  Address MemberAddr =
6071  EmitCXXMemberDataPointerAddress(E, BaseAddr, OffsetV, MPT, &BaseInfo,
6072  &TBAAInfo);
6073 
6074  return MakeAddrLValue(MemberAddr, MPT->getPointeeType(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
6075 }

6077 /// Given the address of a temporary variable, produce an r-value of
6078 /// its type.
6079 RValue CodeGenFunction::convertTempToRValue(Address addr,
6080  QualType type,
6081  SourceLocation loc) {
6082  LValue lvalue = MakeAddrLValue(addr, type, AlignmentSource::Decl);
6083  switch (getEvaluationKind(type)) {
6084  case TEK_Complex:
6085  return RValue::getComplex(EmitLoadOfComplex(lvalue, loc));
6086  case TEK_Aggregate:
6087  return lvalue.asAggregateRValue(*this);
6088  case TEK_Scalar:
6089  return RValue::get(EmitLoadOfScalar(lvalue, loc));
6090  }
6091  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
6092 }

6094 void CodeGenFunction::SetFPAccuracy(llvm::Value *Val, float Accuracy) {
6095  assert(Val->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy());
6096  if (Accuracy == 0.0 || !isa<llvm::Instruction>(Val))
6097  return;
6098 
6099  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
6100  llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createFPMath(Accuracy);
6101 
6102  cast<llvm::Instruction>(Val)->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_fpmath, Node);
6103 }
6104 
6105 void CodeGenFunction::SetSqrtFPAccuracy(llvm::Value *Val) {
6106  llvm::Type *EltTy = Val->getType()->getScalarType();
6107  if (!EltTy->isFloatTy())
6108  return;
6109 
6110  if ((getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
6111  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OpenCLCorrectlyRoundedDivSqrt) ||
6112  (getLangOpts().HIP && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
6113  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().HIPCorrectlyRoundedDivSqrt)) {
6114  // OpenCL v1.1 s7.4: minimum accuracy of single precision / is 3ulp
6115  //
6116  // OpenCL v1.2 s5.6.4.2: The -cl-fp32-correctly-rounded-divide-sqrt
6117  // build option allows an application to specify that single precision
6118  // floating-point divide (x/y and 1/x) and sqrt used in the program
6119  // source are correctly rounded.
6120  //
6121  // TODO: CUDA has a prec-sqrt flag
6122  SetFPAccuracy(Val, 3.0f);
6123  }
6124 }
6125 
6126 void CodeGenFunction::SetDivFPAccuracy(llvm::Value *Val) {
6127  llvm::Type *EltTy = Val->getType()->getScalarType();
6128  if (!EltTy->isFloatTy())
6129  return;
6130 
6131  if ((getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
6132  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OpenCLCorrectlyRoundedDivSqrt) ||
6133  (getLangOpts().HIP && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
6134  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().HIPCorrectlyRoundedDivSqrt)) {
6135  // OpenCL v1.1 s7.4: minimum accuracy of single precision / is 2.5ulp
6136  //
6137  // OpenCL v1.2 s5.6.4.2: The -cl-fp32-correctly-rounded-divide-sqrt
6138  // build option allows an application to specify that single precision
6139  // floating-point divide (x/y and 1/x) and sqrt used in the program
6140  // source are correctly rounded.
6141  //
6142  // TODO: CUDA has a prec-div flag
6143  SetFPAccuracy(Val, 2.5f);
6144  }
6145 }

6147 namespace {
6148  struct LValueOrRValue {
6149  LValue LV;
6150  RValue RV;
6151  };
6152 }
6153 
6154 static LValueOrRValue emitPseudoObjectExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
6155  const PseudoObjectExpr *E,
6156  bool forLValue,
6157  AggValueSlot slot) {
6158  SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMappingData, 4> opaques;
6159 
6160  // Find the result expression, if any.
6161  const Expr *resultExpr = E->getResultExpr();
6162  LValueOrRValue result;
6163 
6164  for (PseudoObjectExpr::const_semantics_iterator
6165  i = E->semantics_begin(), e = E->semantics_end(); i != e; ++i) {
6166  const Expr *semantic = *i;
6167 
6168  // If this semantic expression is an opaque value, bind it
6169  // to the result of its source expression.
6170  if (const auto *ov = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(semantic)) {
6171  // Skip unique OVEs.
6172  if (ov->isUnique()) {
6173  assert(ov != resultExpr &&
6174  "A unique OVE cannot be used as the result expression");
6175  continue;
6176  }
6177 
6178  // If this is the result expression, we may need to evaluate
6179  // directly into the slot.
6180  typedef CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMappingData OVMA;
6181  OVMA opaqueData;
6182  if (ov == resultExpr && ov->isPRValue() && !forLValue &&
6183  CodeGenFunction::hasAggregateEvaluationKind(ov->getType())) {
6184  CGF.EmitAggExpr(ov->getSourceExpr(), slot);
6185  LValue LV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(slot.getAddress(), ov->getType(),
6186  AlignmentSource::Decl);
6187  opaqueData = OVMA::bind(CGF, ov, LV);
6188  result.RV = slot.asRValue();
6189 
6190  // Otherwise, emit as normal.
6191  } else {
6192  opaqueData = OVMA::bind(CGF, ov, ov->getSourceExpr());
6193 
6194  // If this is the result, also evaluate the result now.
6195  if (ov == resultExpr) {
6196  if (forLValue)
6197  result.LV = CGF.EmitLValue(ov);
6198  else
6199  result.RV = CGF.EmitAnyExpr(ov, slot);
6200  }
6201  }
6202 
6203  opaques.push_back(opaqueData);
6204 
6205  // Otherwise, if the expression is the result, evaluate it
6206  // and remember the result.
6207  } else if (semantic == resultExpr) {
6208  if (forLValue)
6209  result.LV = CGF.EmitLValue(semantic);
6210  else
6211  result.RV = CGF.EmitAnyExpr(semantic, slot);
6212 
6213  // Otherwise, evaluate the expression in an ignored context.
6214  } else {
6215  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(semantic);
6216  }
6217  }
6218 
6219  // Unbind all the opaques now.
6220  for (unsigned i = 0, e = opaques.size(); i != e; ++i)
6221  opaques[i].unbind(CGF);
6222 
6223  return result;
6224 }
6225 
6226 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPseudoObjectRValue(const PseudoObjectExpr *E,
6227  AggValueSlot slot) {
6228  return emitPseudoObjectExpr(*this, E, false, slot).RV;
6229 }
6230 
6231 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPseudoObjectLValue(const PseudoObjectExpr *E) {
6232  return emitPseudoObjectExpr(*this, E, true, AggValueSlot::ignored()).LV;
6233 }
